<BLOCKQUOTE>
<H3>THE MARKETPLACE</H3>

Corporate counsel, law firm members, business owners and consumers are looking for lawyers in Corporate Counsel Queries, Law Firm Queries, and the Quick and Consumer Request for Proposals forums, DISCUSS.

<ul>
<li>A corporate counsel member needs counsel to handle a <B>401K DISPUTE</B> with a Fortune 50 company.

<p>

<li>An individual needs Rhode Island counsel to pursue a <B>WRONGFUL TERMINATION</B> matter.
<p>

<li>A law firm member seeks Maryland counsel to handle a <B>CHAPTER 7 BANKRUPTCY</B> for a closely-held corporation.
<p>

<li>A corporate counsel member needs a Massachusetts attorney experienced in federal litigation and ocean <B>FREIGHT DAMAGE LIABILITY</B>.
<P>
<li>An individual needs California counsel to assist in filing for a <B>GREEN CARD</B>.<p>
<li> A corporate counsel member needs <B>COMMERCIAL LANDLORD-TENANT</B> counsel in Atlanta.
<li>A law firm member needs local attorney in <B>SANTIAGO, CHILE</B> with expertise in real estate, timberland, timber contracts and forest practices regulations.
<p>
<li>A corporate counsel member seeks New York <B>ANTITRUST DEFENSE</B> counsel.
<p>
<li> A corporate counsel member needs <B>REAL ESTATE</B> counsel in Louisiana to handle several closings.
<p>
<li> A law firm member needs Ohio counsel to assist in the <B>SALE OF A COMMERCIAL BUILDING</B>.
<p>
<li> An individual needs Arizona counsel to handle a <B>$100,000 COLLECTIONS</B> matter.
<p>

<li>A law firm member needs New Jersey counsel to defend a Superior Court case involving an equipment lease <B>BREACH OF CONTRACT</B> complaint.
<p>

<li> A law firm member seeks <B>COMMERCIAL ARBITRATORS</B> in Pittsburgh.
<p>

</ul>

<HR WIDTH=50%>

<H3>AND DON'T MISS THIS...</H3>
(Join these conversations in DISCUSS.)
<p>
<b>WHAT ARE FIRST-YEARS GOOD FOR?</b> Should clients refuse to use first-year associates as a matter of course? "If a first-year person can do 'X' in 5 hours, a good third-year person can do it better... in three hours (or less). I save money and get a better product. Sounds like a good deal to me," says Jeff Bernfeld of American Science and Engineering. (Brill's Law Biz, General Interest)
<p>

<b>MEMO OF THE WEEK:</b>Jon Van Horne of McDermott, Will & Emery analyzes the impact of the Boeing/ McDonnell Douglas merger on government contracts. (Government Contracts, National Topical Forums)
<p>

<b>CERCLA -- TWO FACILITIES:</b> Can a contaminated facility be divided into two facilities for CERCLA liability purposes? Members examine recent case law on what one calls "the next hot CERCLA issue." (Environmental Law, National Topical Forums)
<p>

<b>LOOKING BACK:</b> From the Telecommunications Act of 1996 to skyrocketing associate salaries, members propose their candidates for the most significant legal and political events of 1996. (Brill's Law Biz, General Interest)

<p>

<HR WIDTH=50%>

<H3>
A COUNSEL CONNECT DEBATE<P>

CHARLES KEATING, INNOCENT MAN?</H3>


That's what Keating's lawyer, Stephen Neal, is calling his client in the wake of a Dec. 2 decision by a Los Angeles federal judge overturning the former Lincoln Savings & Loan Association chairman's convictions for racketeering and fraud.

<p>

Join experts, including Keating's lawyer and prosecutor, to debate whether the most vilified figure of the S&L debacle was a scapegoat, con man or both, in the Criminal Law forum (National Topical Forums, DISCUSS).
<p>

<HR WIDTH=50%>
<p>


