<H2>PLI's Current Trends In Elder Law<BR>

ONLINE: October 16 -- November 6
</H2>
<P>Presented by Counsel Connect and the Practising Law Institute   Stay abreast of recent critical changes in the law and learn the planning strategies used by leaders in this growing field. The issues to
be addressed during this seminar affect general practitioners as well as
specialists. </P>

Please join our panelists in providing perspective on: 

<UL TYPE=DISC>
 
        <LI>Health care and financial planning, especially new restrictions on 
                asset transfers for Medicaid eligibility 
        <LI>Health care decision-making by families and institutions  
        <LI>Capacity and guardianship issues
        <LI>Quality of life issues, health care rationing and nursing home reform 
</UL>


OUR PANELISTS INCLUDE:

<DL>
        <DT>David Goldfarb (Moderator),<I> Goldfarb & Abrandt, NY </I>
        <DT>Cynthia L. Barrett, <I>Attorney at Law, OR</I>
        <DT>Baird B. Brown, <I>Attorney at Law,  CO</I>
        <DT>Carl H. Coleman, <I>New York State Task Force on Life and the Law, NY </I>
        <DT>Robert B. Fleming, <I>Fleming & Curti, AZ</I>
        <DT>Michael Gilfix, <I>Gilfix Associates, CA</I>
        <DT>Bernard A. Krooks, <I>Littman Krooks & Roth, NY </I>
        <DT>Patty Lipshutz,<I> St. Luke's-Roosevelt Hospital Center, NY  </I>
        <DT>Harry S. Margolis, <I>ElderLaw Services, MA </I>
        <DT>Gary Mazart,<I> Hannoch Weisman, NJ</I>
        <DT>Rebecca C. Morgan, <I>Stetson University College of Law, FL  </I>
        <DT>Steven C. Perlis,<I> Family Center for Elder Law, IL </I>
        <DT>Steven J. Silverberg,<I> Attorney at Law, NY </I>
        <DT>Emily S. Starr, <I>Ciota, Starr & Vander Linden, MA </I>
        <DT>Timothy L. Takacs,<I> Family Law Practice, TN </I>
        <DT>Stuart D. Zimring, <I>Attorney at Law, CA</I> </DL>


<P>Join these panelists beginning on October 16 on Counsel Connect under Counsel Connect Seminars, in DISCUSS. For more information, email
Pamela Brownstein or call (201) 642-0258.   To join Counsel Connect,
click on the "Join CC"  button on the navigational bar at bottom of this
page or call 800-569-4086. </P>


