<H2>Intranets:  Behind Closed Web Doors<BR> A Week On The Web Workshop<BR>
October 7 - 11</H2>


<P>You've heard the latest buzz, but do you know what intranets are and how
your firm or company can use them?  Please join us for a special Week on
the Web as we take a look "Behind Close Web Doors" in a week-long program on intranets.  </P>

You'll learn:

<OL TYPE=1 START="1">
        <LI>What an intranet is, exactly

        <LI>How law departments are using intranets for compliance work and
        other corporate databases  

        <LI>How law firms are using intranets to communicate with clients and
store firm materials  

        <LI>The basics you'll need to build an intranet   </OL>

OUR PANELISTS:

<DL>
        <DT>Barry Bayer,  <I>Law Office Tech Review</I>

        <DT>Ted Banks, <I>Kraft Foods, Inc. </I>

        <DT>Guiliano Chicco, <I>General Electric</I>

        <DT>Alan Cohen,  <I>American Lawyer Media</I>

        <DT>Ron Friedmann, <I>Wilmer Cutler</I>    

        <DT>David Johnson, <I>Counsel Connect</I>

        <DT>Marc Lauritsen, <I>Harvard Law School</I>

        <DT>Barry Levinsky, <I>Inland Steel</I>

        <DT>Jesse Londin, <I>Counsel Connect</I>

        <DT>Charles Merrill, <I>McCarter &  English</I>

        <DT>Alan Rothman, <I>Computer Trend Forum Moderator</I>  

        <DT>Jake Vogelaar, <I>Counsel Connect</I>

        <DT>Jeff Weitzman, <I>Counsel Connect</I>


</DL>

<P>Please join us starting October 7 on Counsel Connect under Counsel
Connect Seminars in DISCUSS..  Bring your questions and comments! 
  To
join Counsel Connect, click on the "Join CC"  button on the navigational
bar at bottom of this page or call 800-569-4086. </P>

