<h3 align=center><font color=42426F>Virtual Book Tour:<BR> Reel Justice</font></h3> 

<H4 align=center>September 9 - 22</H4>

<blockquote>


<P>Who can forget Jack Nicholson's explosive testimony in "A Few Good Men"?
Or Marisa Tomei's hilarious discourse on Positraction tire marks in "My
Cousin Vinny?" Hollywood knows that for lawyers and nonlawyers alike, the
stuff of the legal profession makes for good entertainment. </P>

<P>But how accurately do Hollywood producers portray the machinations of the
legal profession on the silver screen? When do they ignore the rules of
evidence to create a better drama? Join Michael Asimow and Paul Bergman
online to discuss their book, "Reel Justice: The Courtroom Goes to the
Movies." "Reel Justice" is a tour of over 50 courtroom movies in which the
authors rate each on the bases of quality, dramatic power and authenticity
of trial scenes.</P>

<P>So, get ready to review the movies that help shape public perceptions
about the legal profession. Join Michael Asimow and Paul Bergman online
starting September 9. You can find them in DISCUSS; Counsel Connect
Seminars; Virtual Book Tours.</P>

