<h3 align=center><font color=42426F>The Law of the Electronic Road:<BR>
Commerce, Property, Freedom and Privacy on the Information Highway</font></h3> <blockquote>

<H4>August 15 - September 15</H4>





<P>For the fourth time, Counsel Connect will host the leading online seminar on the developing law of the information highway.</P>

<P>As commercial and social interaction flourishes over computer networks, lawyers and their clients face new and sophisticated legal questions about copyright, payments, privacy, cryptography, jurisdiction, liberty and electronic contract issues.  Join our experts to learn about, discuss and debate the fields of law that hold the greatest promise for practice development in the information age.</P>

<P>Our distinguished faculty for this month-long online conference includes:</P>
<UL>
<P><LI>Benjamin Wright (seminar co-chairman), attorney and author of "The Law of Electronic Commerce: EDI, E-Mail and the Internet" (Little, Brown)</P>

<P><LI>David R. Johnson (seminar co-chairman), chairman, Counsel Connect, DC</P>

<P><LI>Philip N.  Argy, Mallesons Stephen Jaques,  Australia</P>

<P><LI>John H.  Awerdick, Stryker, Tams & Dill, NJ </P>

<P><LI>Stewart A. Baker, Steptoe & Johnson, DC </P>

<P><LI>Michael S. Baum, Verisign, MA</P>

<P><LI>Amelia H. Boss, Temple University School of Law, PA</P>

<P><LI>J. Beckwith Burr, Federal Trade Commission, DC</P>

<P><LI>Kenneth W. Dam, University of Chicago Law School, IL</P>

<P><LI>Larry Downes, CSC Index, CA</P>

<P><LI>A. Michael Froomkin, University of Miami School of Law, FL</P>

<P><LI>Patricia Fry, University of North Dakota Law School, ND</P>

<P><LI>Peter F. Harter, Netscape Communications Corporation, CA</P>

<P><LI>M. Ethan Katsh, University of Massachusetts, MA</P>

<P><LI>Kenneth M. Kaufman, Roberts & Eckard, DC</P>

<P><LI>Alistair Kelman, LSE Computer Security Research Centre, England</P>

<P><LI>Terrence P. Maher, Cooley Godward Castro Huddleson & Tatum, CO</P>

<P><LI>Charles Merrill, McCarter & English, NJ</P>

<P><LI>Henry H. Perritt,  Villanova University School of Law, PA</P>

<P><LI>David Post, Georgetown University Law Center, DC</P>

<P><LI>E. Michael Power, Department of Justice, Canada</P>

<P><LI>Mark Pruner, Web Counsel LLC, CT  </P>

<P><LI>Mark F. Radcliffe, Gray Cary Ware & Freidenrich, CA</P>

<P><LI>Joel R. Reidenberg, Fordham University, NY</P>

<P><LI>Lance J. Rose, Lewis and Roca, AZ</P>

<P><LI>Pamela Samuelson, University of California at Berkley, CA</P>

<P><LI>A. Jared Silverman, Hannoch Weisman, NJ</P>

<P><LI>Donald Skupsky, Information Requirements Clearinghouse, CO</P>
</UL>

<P>Join this distinguished panel in the Seminars area of Discuss, beginning August 15.</P>



