<h3 align=center><font color=42426F>Virtual Book Tour<BR>Final Jeopardy</font></h3> <blockquote>

<H4>Begining August 19</H4>

<P></P>



<P>Beginning August 19, join Linda Fairstein, head of the Sex Crimes
Unit in the Manhattan District Attorney's office, in a discussion about
her new novel, "Final Jeopardy." Final Jeopardy, which centers around
the investigation of a celebrity murder, is a fast read with great
descriptions of the daily goings-on in the D.A.'s office. Fairstein is
at her best when describing the strange characters who she meets on
their journeys through the halls of justice. As one of the characters in
the book says "You just couldn't make this stuff up."</P>

<P>Join Linda Fairstein and other readers in DISCUSS, under Virtual Book
Tours.</P>





