<HtMl><title>CC Web Editor's Picks Archive page 2</title><body bgcolor=ffffff text=5c4033 link=00009c   vlink=ff0000> <p align=center> <img width=442 height=57 border=0 src="/images/header.gif" alt="COUNSEL CONNECT"><BR><img width=325 height=30 border=0  src="/images/eparchive.gif" alt="EDITOR'S  PICK'S ARCHIVE"></P><BLOCKQUOTE><B><FONT color="000000">Here's even more of our editor's picks from weeks gone by. Our editors continually check the Net, tracking interesting legal and government sites so you don't have to.</FONT></B></BLOCKQUOTE></P><UL><P><FONT SIZE="+2" color="000000"><LI><TT><B>Week of April 22:</B></TT></font> </P><P><B><a href="/spotlight/dole.html">Exclusive! Dole Attacks A.B.A.</a></B><ul>"The ABA even opposes closing legal loopholes that would make it easier to convict vicious sex offenders," claims the nominee.</ul></P><P><b><a href="http://www.epo.co.at/epo/">European Patent Office</a></b><ul>Over 80% of the world's patents are granted by the EPO, the Japanese Patent Office and the U.S. Patent & Trademark Office. Visit the EPO (headquartered nonvirtually in Munich) for info on filing in one of three official languages (English, French or German) to get patent protection in all 18 member countries of the European Patent Organization.  With links to other patent offices and databases.</ul></P><P> <b><a href="http://procure.msfc.nasa.gov/fedproc/home.html">Federal  Acquisition Jumpstation</a></b><ul>Now that the government has collected everyone's 1995 tax, you or your favorite client may want to cash in on the spoils by garnering a lucrative government contract.  Who wouldn't?  This collection of pointers takes you to the agencies and department open for business.  With links to miltary and executive offices and lots of resources for contracting info and opportunities.</ul></P><P> <B><a href="http://www.adr.org/intarb.html">International Arbitration Rules</a></B><ul>A sole arbitor, or a tribunal of three or more?  Arbitration in English, or another language?  What about administrative fees? Here are recommended rules  for parties involved ininternational business who elect to resolve disputes witharbitration.  From the American Arbitration Association, the not-for-profit organization calling itself "the largest single repository of information on alternative dispute resoplution law and practice."</ul></p><P><B> <a href="http://www.courttv.com/casefiles/okc/">Oklahoma City Bombing: A Year After</a></B> <ul>On April 19, 1995  explosives decimated a federal officebuilding in Oklahoma killing 168 people and injuring hundreds more. On this sad anniversary, take a look at the Court TV Law Center's Oklahoma casefile featuring American Lawyer Media articles,  trial documents and court briefs. Follow the timeline outlining the upcoming federal trial of Timothy McVeigh.</ul></p><P> <B><a href="http://www.nashville.Net/~gsiskind/bulletin.html">Siskind'sImmigration Bulletin</a></B><br><ul>In the wake of Senator Bob Dole's decision to pull the immigration bill from the floor of the Senate, travel over to Siskind and Susser's website to review the latest Immigration Bulletin. This month's issue features a new legislative update and "Visa Spotlight," along with reports on aliens and social security numbers, the INS Service Center, and more. </UL></P><P><FONT SIZE="+2" color="000000"><LI><TT><B>Week of April 15:</B></TT></font> </P><P><b><a href="http://www.fbi.gov/">Federal Bureau of Investigation</a></b><UL>Now that Ted Kaczynski is in custody, visit the homepage of the  hardworking FBI for a mix of unclassified goodies on Bureau programs  and high-profile investigations including Unabomber, Oklahoma, "Ten Most  Wanted Fugitives," Ruby Ridge, economic espionage, international  crime, computer crime, and cool spy stuff.  Review  1995 crime stats; find out about fingerprint identification. And remember, "national security begins with you."</ul></P><P> <b><a href="http://thomas.loc.gov/home/hot-subj.html">Major  Legislation</a></b><UL> What's on Congress' plate?  Every day the media reports on the work of our federal lawmakers.   Now, put on your asbestos e-boots and walk through a selection of hot bills and amendments--proposed laws that have received floor action or debate during the 104th Congress.  Browse through the alphabetical list of approximately 60 topics of legislation, from abortion to welfare.  On Thomas.</ul></P><P> <B><a href="http://rampages.onramp.net/~tradelaw/">International and Customs Law Links</a></b><UL>International and customs law firm Braumiller & Rodriguez, Dallas, presents a varied compilation of pointers to international trade law, treaties, foreign law, and general legal sites. Including a special menu of NAFTA links.  Don't  miss the excellent listing of upcoming international law events.</ul></P><P> <B> <a href="http://www.pulitzer.org/winners/1996/">Pulitzer Prize Home Page</a></b><UL>And the cyberwinner is . . . Last week the discerning  Pulitzer Prize Board announced the 1996 recipients of the coveted Pulitzer. Prizes recognize excellence in journalism, poetry, fiction, photography, drama, history, music and more.  Here are works and profiles of this year's eloquent, artistic and literary winners.</ul></P><P> <B> <a href="http://www.upside.com/resource/print/9601/ecash.html"><I>Showdown Over E-Cash</I></a></b><UL>E-cash is a new kind of money, born in the digital age. According to Howard Andersen of the Yankee Group, electronic money will "fractionate the balance of power in banking, retailing, software and the stock market . . . [and] hobble governments as it undercuts their ability to control the flow of money with monetary policy."  Read this striking report, taken from a recent conference and published byUpscale Online.  With links to e-cash and cyberfinance companies.</ul></P><P> <P><FONT SIZE="+2" color="000000"><LI><TT><B>Week of April 8:</B></TT></font> </P><P><b><a href="http://www.doc.gov/">Department of Commerce</a></b><UL>This week the nation mourns the untimely death of Secretary of Commerce Ronald H. Brown.  Visit his Department's website to read a bio of the late cabinet chief, lawyer, former chaiman of the Democratic National Committee, and first African-American CommerceSecretary. Follow links to Commerce agencies and the offices where the spirit of Ron Brown lives.</ul></P><P> <b><ahref="http://www.usc.edu/dept/law-lib/librarys/locators.html">Indexof Law School Web and Gopher Servers</a></b><UL>Nostalgic about school?  You can always go back. Courtesy of the University of Southern California Law Center, take a tour of a few hundred law schools on the Net, from American University to Yale, including schools in Canada, Europe, even China.  Visit your old stomping ground and recall what you loved about law school.  And what you didn't.</ul></P><P> <B><a href="http://palissy.humana.univ-nantes.fr/homepage">Maritimeand Oceanic Law</a></B><UL>As the weather warms now's a good time to look ahead tosummer--beaches, oceans and the open sea.  From the University of Nantes, France, sail over to a clear blue compilation of U.S. and European maritime, oceanic, coastal, port, admiralty and shipping sites.  Read the U.N. Law of the Sea treaty, visit Sea.Net, CargoWeb, Merchant Mariner's Homeport, Seaports Infopages, the Council on OceanLaw and other deep sites.</UL></p><P><B> <a href="http://law.uark.edu/arklaw/aglaw/">National Center for Agricultural Law Research</a></B> <UL>While English farmers figure out a way to destroy millions of stricken cows, Congress is busy seeding the fields with a big new farm bill.   Plow over to the NCALRI's site for full text of  the bill, a report on farm bill alternatives (from American Farmland Trust), a message from Agriculture Secretary Dan Glickman, links to the USDA, the American Agricultural Law Association, the NationalAgriculture Library, and other agricultuire resources.</ul> </p><P> <B> <a href="/spotlight/scien2.html">Scientology: <I>Making Law, Making Enemies</I></a></B><UL>Reprinted from <I> The American Lawyer</I>, this article examines The Church of Scientology's  numerous clashes with the online community. The church maintains it is trying to protect its <I>copyrighted</I>religious dogma, but netizens everywhere insist it is out to silence its critics -- under the guise of copyright protection.</ul> </P><P><FONT SIZE="+2" color="000000"><LI><TT><B>Week of April 1:</B></TT></font> </P><P><b><a href="/goto?http://www.courttv.com/casefiles/serb/">Court TV Law Center Exclusive: War Crimes Tribunal</a></b><UL>Will Bosnia see justice?  As the International War Crimes Tribunal for the formerYugoslavia gears up for its first case, the trial of Bosnian Serb Dusko Tadic,read excerpts from Court TV anchor Terry Moran's recent interview with ChiefProsecutor Richard Goldstone.  Also, dip into the collection of indictments andother documents from the Tribunal.  And don't miss a riveting look back atNuremberg.</UL></P><P> <b><a href="http://www.abaa-booknet.com/usa/lbe/">LawbookExchange</a></b><UL>Looking for classic legal books and landmark treatises from the fifteenth centuryto the present?  For reprints and original texts in all fields of law and legalhistory, browse the virtual catalogues and search the digital shelves at theLawbook Exchange. Items for sale include scholarly and out-of-print works of thetwentieth century, reference books, and law dictionaries.</UL></P><P> <B><a href="http://www.McCutchen.com/env">McCutchen Environmental Group</a></B><UL>Here's the latest online offering from McCutchen, Doyle, Brown & Enersen, LLP. The firm's environmental group has staked out its own piece of evergreencyberspace with timely summaries of environmental and natural resources lawsummaries, featuring California law. The site also presents select environmentallaw links.</UL></p><P> <B> <a href="http://www.nara.gov/">National Records and ArchivesAdministration</a> </B><UL>What do Nixon's letter of resignation, the verdict against Alphonse Capone andthe Louisiana Purchase have in common? They're all archived and maintained byNARA, the independent federal agency responsible for managing the records of theU.S. government. NARA's online exhibits are based on nonvirtual displays in theNational Archives Building in Washington, D.C. Check out the Constitution, theBill of Rights and a cybertrove  of gifts from foreign countries to U.S.presidents.</UL> </p><P> <B> <a href="http://www.ai.mit.edu/stocks">StockMaster at MIT</a></B> <UL>The award-winning and   StockMaster is presented by the wizards at theMassachusettes Institute of Technology Artificial Intelligence Laboratory.  Gethot stock market data including yesterday's closing prices, graphs of historicprices, stock and mutual fund charts, historic datafiles, "top stocks" graphs,and other juicy financial info and links. </UL></P> <P><TT><B><FONT SIZE="+2" color="000000"><LI>Week of March 25</FONT></B></TT></P><P> <B> <a href="http://nii.nist.gov">National Information   Infrastructure Virtual Library</a></B><uL>   The information superhighway has come a long way since the days of smoke signals andPony Express.  Visit the NII Virtual Library for NII resources, an inventory ongovernment activities and projects, info on standards, and some background on who's whoin the technology industries.  (This online collection is sponsored by the President'sInformation Infrastructure Task Force and the Council on Competitiveness.)</uL> <p> <B> <a href="http://www.execpc.com/~mhallign/">Trade Secrets Home Page</a> </B><UL>Chicago trade secret lawyer and lecturer R. Mark Halligan shares his insights on tradesecret law, from audits to investigations, including summaries of recent cases, newdevelopments and a discussion of the Uniform Trade Secrets Act.</UL> <P> <B> <a href="http://www.un.org/News">United Nations News</a> </B> <UL> From United Nations headquarters in New York City, here are up-to-the-cyberminute UNdaily journals, agendas, press releases (in French and English), and newsletters from theDepartment of Public Affairs.  And hit the link to zip right over to the UN homepage.</UL> <P> <B> <a href="http://www.usc.edu/dept/law-lib/legal/journals.html">Index ofLaw-Related E-Journals and Periodicals</a></B><UL>  Browse this thorough collection of law journals on the Web, along with a separatesection on general interest and computing periodicals, and an archive of e-texts. Presented by the University of Southern California Law Library.</UL> </P><p> <B> <a href="http://www.spp.umich.edu/telecom-info.html">Telecom InformationResources</a> </B> <UL> From the University at Michigan's School of Public Policy, here are over 900 linksto telecommunications sites and sources, from broadcasters, standards bodies,government agencies, and professional associations to information about networksecurity, telecom projects and events.</UL>  <P><P><TT><B><FONT SIZE="+2" color="000000"><LI>Week of March 18</FONT></B></TT></P><P> <a href="http://www.courttv.com/download/legalt.html"><B><I>Legal Times</I> Exclusive: The Tobacco Case ABC NeverMade</a></b><UL> Philip Morris Companies Inc. settled its libel suit against ABClastsummer after the network apologized for parts of its 1994 broadcast that allegedthatnicotine is added to tobacco products. A copy of a <b><ahref="http://www.courttv.com/download/library/tobacco/brief.html">keybrief prepared by ABC's lawyers</a></B> -- made available to <I> Legal Times   </I> by aconfidential source -- reveals for the first time the detailed evidence the networkwasprepared to present in support of its charges that Philip Morris was addingaddictivenicotine to its cigarettes.  Read it for  yourself on Court TV's Law Center. </UL> </P><P><B><a href="http://www.abiworld.org">ABI World</a></B><UL>Here's the newly-launched site of the American Bankruptcy Institute, theorganization for bankruptcy lawyers and other insolvency professionals. Under heavyconstruction, ABI World promises a library, calendar of events, legislative news,chat, more. Don't miss the regularly updated section, Today's Bankruptcy Headlines .    </UL> <p> <B> <a href="http://sray.wcl.american.edu/pub/journals/hmnrghts.htm">HumanRights Brief</a></B><UL>  An e-journal from the Center for Human Rights and Humanitarian Law and The AmericanUniversity Washington College of Law.  Read articles on international refugees,immigration and Proposition 187, internally displaced persons, political asylum,women's rights issues and more. </UL> <p> <B> <a href="http://oyez.at.nwu.edu/oyez.html">Oral Arguments Site</a> </B><UL>Listen to RealAudio tapes of oral arguments before the U.S. Supreme Court inselected landmark cases of the past 40 years. <I>Roe v. Wade, U.S. v. Nixon,Griswold v. Connecticut</I>.  The biggies. Check back as Professor Jerry Goldman andhis team at Northwestern University deliver to the Web hundreds of historicarguments. </UL> </P><P><a href=http://www.realchange.org/><B>Skeleton Closet</b></a><UL> No presidential candidate escapes cyberscrutiny at this political landmine as thenon-partisan group Real People For Real Change  shine a laser into the dark cornersof each candidates character.  Have a riveting peek at the digital dirt, and don'tcast your vote until you peek in the closet. </UL> </P><P><TT><B><FONT SIZE="+2" color="000000"><LI>Week of March 11</FONT></B></TT></P><P><b><a href="http://www.govt-waste.org">Citizens Against Government Waste</a></b><UL>Nobody loves government waste.  And nobody loves it less than than that private,non-partisan, non-profit, perpetually pissed-off taxpayer group, Citizens AgainstGovernment Waste. Here they are, along with publications like Reality Checks, PigBook and Wastewatcher, to confirm that government is a wasteland, our evil taxmasters must be destroyed, and by the way,your share ofthe national debt is $18,686.</UL> </P><P> <B><a href="http://www.enn.com">Environmental News Network</a></B><UL> Stay on top of environmental news and save a nonvirtual tree.  ENN features freeweekly stories,daily headlines, events calendar and marketplace. In addition, paying members getunlimitedaccess to the entire website, including full news stories, archive andlibrary.</UL> </p><P> <B> <a href="http://www.link.org">International Centre for Commercial Law</a> </B> <UL>Need a banking lawyer in Switzerland?  Interested in the effects of Austriancartel law on foreign mergers?  Check here for European law firms listed byspecialty, as well as summaries ofcommercial law issues across Europe, organized by country.</UL>    </p><P>  <B> <ahref="http://sunsite.unc.edu:80/patents/ipnsinfo.html">Internet Patent NewsService</a> </B> <UL>  Sign up for your free, weekly e-mailannouncement of all patents issued by the U.S. Patent and Trademark office duringthe past week.  There's background on the service and subscription information.  Stop by the <a href=http://sunsite.unc.edu:80/patents/document.html>IPNSarchive</a>  for past mailings.</UL>  </P><P> <B><ahref="http://lawlib.wuacc.edu/forint/constitu.html">World Constitutions</a><UL></B> Compare and contrast the lofty documents that underpingovernments of the world, from the U.S. to Japan to the People's Republic ofChina.  How about Russia, Greece, Germany, Sweeden, Saudi Arabia and more? Spanish translation available.</UL>  </P><P><TT><B><FONT SIZE="+2" color="000000"><LI>Week of March 4</FONT></B></TT></P><P><b><a href="http://www.fec.gov/">Federal Election Commission</a></b><UL>Here's where the feds report on who's running for president and Congress, howmuch they're spending, who's taking what PAC money, and other golden nuggets ofcampaign finance.  The site also offers data and charts from past electioncycles.  The FEC promises to update financial information as the '96 electioncontinues. </UL> </P><P> <B><a href="http://www.shadow.net/~nfstc/links.html">Forensic Science and LawEnforcement Links</a></B><UL>  Visit a police lab, learn about bloodstain pattern analysis, investigate a crimescene.   From the American Academy of Forensic Science to Zeno Rebozo's ShoeprintIdentification, sneak intothe fascinating world of forensics, courtesy of the National Forensic ScienceTechnology Center. </UL> </p><P> <B> <a href="http://www.inter-law.com/ref.html">Lawcopedia</a> </B> <UL>From the folks at 'lectric law Library, here's the Web's answer to a plain 'olnonvirtual law dictionary.  It's a hypertext index of law terms and phrases,organized by topic -- from ADR to taxation. You can also use the alphabet bar toclick on the first letter of the word you want to look up.  Res ipsa loquitur.</UL>    </p><P>  <B> <a href="http://sunsite.unc.edu/gaylaw/">National Journal of SexualOrientation Law</a></B> <UL>  Billing itself as "the first on-linejournal in the country and the second devoted exclusively to issues affectinglesbians, gay men and bisexuals," this publication explores topics such asrecognition of domestic partnership and gay marriage, sexual orientationdiscrimination, state anti-gay legislation.  Browse a recent symposium on sexualminorities in legal education. </UL>  </P><P> <B><ahref="http://www.netplanning.com">National Network of Estate Planning Attorneys</a><UL></B>  Looking for the "keys to wealth enhancement and preservation?" Search the National Network databases for tips onestate, investment, charitable and retirement planning, and business continuity. Use the directories to locate estate planning attorneys and financial planners.</UL>  </P><P><TT><B><FONT SIZE="+2" color="000000"><LI>Week of February 26</FONT></B></TT></P><P><b><a href="/goto?http://www.courttv.com/casefiles/oj/ddocs/">Court TV Law Center Exclusive!</a></b><UL>Read all five volumes of O.J. Simpson's deposition in the civil lawsuit.</UL> </P><P> <P><b><a href="http://www.aipla.org">American Intellectual Property Law Association</a></b><UL>Meet the AIPLA. Founded in 1897, this organization of 9,000 intellectual property lawyers in all states and 34 foreign countries features committee reports, agendas,  application for membership,  ADR and CLE information, and more on its web site.</UL> </P><P> <B><a href="http://pathfinder.com/money/flattax">Money Online's Flat Tax E-Valuator</a></B><UL> It's one of the hottest and most controversial issues of the presidential campaign.  Is flat tax good forAmerica?  Is it good for you?  Consider the various proposals of flat tax proponents Steve Forbes, PatrickBuchanan and Rep. Dick Armey.  Use the interactive flat tax e-valuator to calculate your hypothetical flattax under the various schemes.  On Pathfinder. </UL> </p><P> <B> <a href="http://www.fas.org/pub/gen/fas/sgp">Project on Government Secrecy</a> </B> <UL>If the cold war is over, why is the U.S. spending an estimated $16 billion annually on its secrecy system? Does the government abuse its national security classification authority?  The Federation of AmericanScientists (FAS) is on a mission to "illuminate the extent of government secrecy."  Check out securityreports, policy documents, FAS bulletins and links to related sites.</UL>    </p><P>  <B> <a href="http://www3.law.cornell.edu/Harvest/brokers/circuit-x/fancy.query.html">Search U.S. Court of Appeals Opinions</a></B> <UL>   The Web is home to recent opinions of all Circuit Courts of Appeals.  Now, thanks to a customized search tool created by Cornell LawSchool's Legal Information Institute, it's easy to simultaneously search these databases of opinions.  Plug inkeywords, party names, and cites to  search quickly across the circuits.</UL>  </P><P><TT><B><FONT SIZE="+2" color="000000"><LI>Week of February  19</FONT></B></TT></P><P> <B><ahref="http://www.nps.gov/">U.S. National Parks Service</a><UL></B> From Fire Island National Seashore one hour east of New York City, to Yosemite National Park in California, the National Park Service oversees treasured national parks, while maintaining a valuable campsite on theWeb.  Hike over to the NPS homepage and use clickable maps to search for choice destinations nationally.</UL>  </P><P><b><a href="/goto?http://www.courttv.com/casefiles/okc/">Exclusive! Oklahoma City Bombing Case</a></b><UL>Visit our affiliate Court TV Law Center to follow theevents unfolding in the case against Timothy McVeigh andTerry Lynn Nichols. Read the detailed indictment, preliminarytranscript and other hot docs from the explosion that rockedthe nation.</UL> </P><P>  <B> <a href="http://www.NASA.gov">National Aeronautics and SpaceAdministration</a> </B><UL>Ten years ago on January 28, the space shuttle Challenger exploded 74 seconds afterlift-off killing all seven crew members including public school teacher ChristaMcAuliffe, and grounding the U.S. space program for three years.  Today America isback in space, and on the Web, too.</UL> </P><P><b><a href=" http://www.laig.com/law/intnet">International Entertainment & Multimedia Law & Business Network </a></b><UL>From Harris Tulchin & Associates, Los Angeles, tune into aneclectic grouping of articles and outlines addressingentertainment law issues such as international film licensing,distribution and sales, and unfair competition for multimediaresources.  With links to intellectual property sites and multimedia publications. Don't miss the film festivals calendar.</UL> </P><P> <B><a href="http://www.maol.com/maol/">M & A Online</a></B><UL> Looking to acquire a marina complex for less than a millionbucks? How about a reasonably priced commercial printing service,or an apparel manufacturer, or even a wholesale aircraft partsdeveloper?   Here's a searchable database of companies for sale,along with listings of equity and debt providers, valuation stats,funding requests, and merger and acquisition announcements.Go for it.</UL> </p><P><TT><B><FONT SIZE="+2" color="000000"><LI>Week of February 12</FONT></B></TT></P><P> <B> <a href="http://www.ojp.usdoj.gov/bjs/">Bureau of Justice Statistics</a> </B> <UL>Does crime pay?  Don't ask the Menendez brothers.  Head over to acollection of crime data from the Department of Justice.  Readabout crime in America, including a report on guns used bycriminals, with data on how criminal courts deal with weaponsoffenses.  Download the "World Criminal Justice Factbook" fordescriptions of criminal justice systems in countries around theworld.</UL>    </p>  <P> <B> <a href=http://www.pbs.org/>PBS Online</a></B> <UL>  From Mystery! to Masterpiece Theatre and Nova to Washington Week, tune in to PBS's site to preview your favorite science, news, cultural and educational public broadcast programming.         </UL>  </P><P> <B> <a href=" http://www.gama.com/">Global Arbitration and Mediation Center</a></B> <UL>  Everyone's entitled to his or her day in court.  But beforeyou file a lawsuit, stop by GAMA for information on "disputeresolution at the speed of light"--that's right, ADR over theInternet.  GAMA also offers sample mandatory arbitrationand mediation agreements and clauses, a collection of legalforms, and a directory of ADR organizations and professionals.And if you're an expert, GAMA invites you to join its panel ofmediators and arbitrators.</UL>  </P><P> <B> <a href="http://www.navisoft.com/munibond/index.htm">Municipal Bond  Scandals</a></B> <UL>If you delight in scandal, and didn't get enough when Orange County, California went belly-up, feast on the latest in the wild world of muni bond bombshells and disasters.</UL>  </P><P> <B> <a href="/spotlight/telecom/telecom.htm">Seminar! Telecommunications Reform- A New Playing Field</a></B> <UL> On February 8, President Clinton signed the sweeping Telecommunications Act of 1996. Join a panel from Counsel Connect and the Internet and discuss the new law and its effects on business and the online world. </UL></P><P><P><TT><B><FONT SIZE="+2" color="000000"><LI>Week of February 5</FONT></B></TT></P><P> <B> <a href="http://AllPolitics.com/>All Politics</a></B> <UL> From CNN and Time magazine comes this newly launched site covering "politics in the digital age". Its slogan, "Candidates. Computers. Campaigns". Check out E-mailf+om the Trail, poll and election results, and follow links to all the candidtates' webpa+es.</UL></P><P></B> <B> <a href=http://www.scj.albany.edu:90/jcjpc/>Journal of Criminal Justice and Popular Culture</a></B> <UL>A bi-monthly journal devoted to the "review of all types of popular culture artifacts and original essays pertaining to the intersection of popular culture and criminal justice". From SUNY Albany's School of Criminal Justice.</UL></P><P> <B> <a href=http://www.usda.gov>U.S. Department of Agriculture</a></B> <UL>As Congress puts together a major agricultural law overhaul, visit the homepage of the USDA for news, fact sheets, information about farm and agricultural programs, and a message or two from Secretary Dan Glickman.  </UL>  </P>    <P> <B> <a href="http://www.pli.edu/">Practising Law Institute</a></B> <UL>Here's where lawyers go to keep in practice. Find out about the latest offerings from the biggest and oldest continuing legal education organization.</UL>  </P><P> <B> <a href=http://www.courts.com/>Your Nation's Courts 1996</a></B> <UL>Which states make up the Fifth Circuit? Who's the Clerk of the U.S. Tax Court? For information about federal and state judges and courts, check these listings, reproduced for the Web from the  print directories of Want Publishing Co.         </UL>            </P><P> <B> <a href=http://barratry.law.cornell.edu:5123/notify/buzz.html>BigEar</a></B> <UL>Another innovation from Tom Bruce and Cornell's inimitable Legal Information Institute, BigEar monitors discussions on top legal listservs and complies a weekly listing of new sites, all of interest to lawyers. </UL> </p><P><TT><B><FONT SIZE="+2" color="000000"><LI>Week of January 29</FONT></B></TT></P><P> <B> <a href=http://orbus.pls.com:8001/his/cfr.html>Code of Federal Regulations</a></B> <UL>Search the experimental CFR server, courtesy of House Information Systems at the U.S. House of Representatives Internet Law Library.</UL></P><P> <B> <a href=http://www.nttls.co.jp/infomofa/ju/c_agenda/mes/main.html>U.S.-Japan Common Agenda for Cooperation in Global Perspective</a></B> <UL> In 1993 the U.S. and Japan launched the "Common Agenda", a wide-reaching bilateral partnership for public and private cooperation. Now, courtesy of Japan's Ministry of Foreign Affairs, the successful and ongoing agreement now lives on the Web.</UL></p><P> <B> <a href=http://www.kuesterlaw.com/mpep/>U.S. Patent & Trademark Office, Manual of Patent Examination Procedure</a></B> <UL> Read the MPEP, and other new patent law documents which incorporate GATT changes, on the website of intellectual property cyberlawyer Jeffrey Kuester.</UL>            </P><P> <B> <a href=http://www.fga.com/aaaa/>AffAct Web</a></B> <UL>Is affirmative action dead? Visit the homepage of the American Association for Affirmative Action for recent cases, legislation and publications addressing one of the most debated issues of the year. </UL>        </P><P> <B> <a href=http://www.radix.net/~ggmark/welcome.html>GGMARK</a></B> <UL>The "All About Trademarks" page includes information about marks for specialists and beginners, and a good collection of trademark and other law-related links, from the law firm of Guillot & Gazala.</UL>   </p><P><TT><B><FONT SIZE="+2" color="000000"><LI>Week of January 22</FONT></B></TT></P><P> <B> <a href=http://falcon.cc.ukans.edu/~ptull/constitutions.html>World Constitutions</a></B> <UL> Compare and contrast constitutions of the world, from the U.S. to Japan, to the People's Republic of China. Also includes Russia, Greece, Germany, Sweeden, Saudi Arabia and more. The site offers Spanish translations of these lofty documents.</UL></P><P> <B> <a href=http://www.jpl.nasa.gov/galileo/countdown/>Galileo Countdown to Jupiter</a></B> <UL>In 1610 Galileo took the first look through a telescope at Jupiter. In 1989, NASA sent a spacecraft named for the astronomer on a six year, two and a half billion mile journey to touch the face of the Jovian planet. Galileo has arrived. CNN can't be there, but on the Web, you  can.</UL>  </P><P> <B> <a href=http://www.dtic.dla.mil/bosnia/index.html>BosniaLINK</a></B> <UL> Last week the leaders of Bosnia, Serbia and Croatia entered a pact to bring peace to the war-tom region formerly known as Yugoslavia. As 60,000 NATO troops march into Bosnia in an effort to enforce the Paris treaty, visit the Pentagon's newly-launched site to monitor developments. Review maps, speeches, press documents, testimony and other background materials.</UL></P><P> <B> <a href=http://www.radix.net/~stmon/USDC/ddc.html>Unofficial Home Page of the USDC for the District of Columbia Court</a></B> <UL>Cyberclerk Steve Mon of the U.S. District Court for the District of Columbia posts this "unofficial" site featuring information about the court, the District's judges, judicial units, clerks, dockets. And while you're there, calculate the interest on your judgments using T-Bill rates graciously included.  </UL></P><P> <B> <a href=http://www.fordhamiplj.com/>Intellectual Property, Media and Entertainment Law Journal</a></B> <UL>Intellectual  Property, Media and Entertainment Law Journal: The latest law e-joumal to go live on the Web, from Fordham Law School.</UL></p><P><TT><B><FONT SIZE="+2" color="000000"><LI>Week of January 15</FONT></B></TT></P><P> <B> <a href=http://www.customs.com/>International Trade Homepage</a></B> <UL> New York's Wasserman, Schneider & Babb offer a memo on the constitutionality of harbor maintenance fees on exports, and a good collection of links to custom and trade law sites.</UL></P><P> <B> <a href=http://www.verbatimreporters.com/>Verbatim Reporters Center</a></B> <UL> From the National Court Reporters Association, locate experienced court reporters, translators, proofreaders, transcribers and more, to suit all your litigation needs.</UL></P><P> <B> <a href=http://www.llr.com/opinion/PLS.HTM>Lawyers Legal Research Network (LLR)</a></B> <UL> Register at this super resource for free federal circuit court opinions, as well as opinions from many state appellate courts.</UL>         </P><P><P><B><a href="http://www.courttv.com/seminars/handbook/index.html">The UltimateEmployee Handbook - A Workshop</a></B><UL>What makes an employee handbook an asset or a liability? A panel from Counsel Connect and theInternet discuss company policy, handbook language, computer networkpolicies - even office romance. In this "golden age" of corporate compliance, stophere to read up on handbook do's and dont's.</UL> </P><P><P> <B> <a href=http://www.moments.com/html/dream.htm>I Have a Dream</a></B> <UL> This week marks the tenth anniversary of the national holiday honoring the slain civil rights leader. Here's Dr. Martin Luther King's famous opus, delivered on the steps of the Lincoln Memorial in Washington, D.C., August 28, 1963. Let freedom ring.</UL>  </P><P><TT><B><FONT SIZE="+2" color="000000"><LI>Week of January 8</FONT></B></TT></P><P> <B> <a href=http://asa.ugl.lib.umich.edu/chdocs/womenpolicy/womenlawpolicy.html>Internet Resources for Women's Legal and Public Policy Information</a></B> <UL>A guide to resources related to law and policy issues concerning women, including work, healthcare, family, and the military. The guide offers pointers to gay, feminist and international organizations and materials.</UL>           </P><P> <B> <a href=http://www.ionet.net/~mdyer/netwatch.shtml>Netwatchers Magazine</a></B> <UL> A monthly e-zine addressing legal topics and developments in cyberspace and online communities. Includes links and "Netwatchers Legal Bookmarks".         </UL> </P><P> <B> <a href=http://www.business.gov/>U.S. Business Advisor</a></B> <UL> While the federal government haggles over the budget, visit the site billed as the "one-stop for all the services and information that the government offers business." The Business Advisor features a comprehensive  Regulatory Assistance Center where businesses can decipher rules and regs on labor, taxes, the environment, immigration, safety, more.</UL> </P><P> <B> <a href=http://www.ustr.gov/>United States Trade Representative</a></B> <UL> Ambassador Mickey Kantor's office, responsible for international trade and investment policy, and negotiating with international business partners, offers issued reports, recent speeches, congressional testimony on trade issues, and agreements negotiated by USTR.</UL>    </P><P> <B> <a href=http://www.senate.gov/>United States Senate</a></B> <UL> Thanks to Newt Gingrich and the Contract With America, media attention and public scrutiny primarily focused this session on the House of Representatives. But after a conspicuous absence, the Senate too, has arrived on the Web. Get to know the Senate, it's history, leadership, committees and more. And the site stays in session when the busy, brawling 104th Congress finally adjourns.</UL>      </P>      </UL>  <P align=center><a href="http://www.counsel.com/cgi-bin/htimage/images/toolbar.map"><img ISMAP width=503 height=40 border=0  src="/images/toolbar.gif"</a><br clear=all><font size=-2><TT><a href="/">Home</a>  <B>&#183;</B>  <a href="/comment.html">Comments</a>  <B>&#183;</B>  <a href="/inside/join.html">Join Counsel Connect</a> <B>&#183;</B>  <a href="http://www.courttv.com">Court TV Law Center</a> </font></TT></P></body></HtMl>
