<HEAD>
   <TITLE>Opinions Unlimited: VersusLaw</TITLE>
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0Gold (Win95; I) [Netscape]">
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<CENTER><P><IMG SRC="opunl.gif" HEIGHT=80 WIDTH=400><BR>
<IMG SRC="versuscc.gif" > </P></CENTER>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><FONT SIZE=+1>V. makes legal research fast and easy with a state-of-the-art
search engine and your choice of natural language or Boolean search operators.
V. is the only service on the Web that provides you unlimited access to
archival appellate court opinions from all 50 states, in many cases back
to 1950, all Federal Circuit Courts back to 1950, and the U.S. Supreme
Court back to 1930. Most of our cases come with the official court citation,
in addition to our own electronic citation which has been approved in the
16th Edition of the Harvard Bluebook. And with V., you are guaranteed to
have the most up-to-date case results. V. updates its opinions library
several times a day, and in most cases you will have access to appellate
cases within twenty-four hours or release by the court. There are no extra
charges for downloads or printing out results. Your daily, monthly or annual
subscription charge covers everything. </FONT></P>

<P><FONT SIZE=+1>Click here to discover <A HREF="vcrtinf.html">the extent
of V.'s opinion library coverage</A>. </FONT></P>

<P><FONT SIZE=+1>Under Counsel Connect's special arrangement with VersusLaw,
Counsel Connect members will receive a 20% discount off the regular rate
for all subscription plans: daily, monthly or annual. And Counsel Connect
members who have Zurich as their malpractice insurance provider receive
access to V. absolutely free. Counsel Connect members must register through
Opinions Unlimited in order to receive the 20% discount on whatever V.
subscription plan they choose.</FONT></P>

<P><FONT SIZE=+1>V. offers you a full TWO-WEEK free trial period, with
unlimited access to the entire V. opinions library for all fifty states
and all Federal Circuits. </FONT></P>

<P><FONT SIZE=+1>V.'s subscription plans are as follows: </FONT></P>

<P><IMG SRC="orangeba.gif"  ALIGN=LEFT><B>Daily Plan</B>: $12 for Counsel
Connect members (regular rate $14.95). This plan allows unlimited access
to the V. opinions library for 24 hours from the time your subscription
begins. (A good plan for those who only need to do legal research on an
infrequent basis). There is no limit on the number of times you can do
a daily subscription within a year. Payment is via major credit card, <B>online
only</B>. </P>

<P><IMG SRC="orangeba.gif"  ALIGN=LEFT><B>Monthly Plan</B>: $60 for Counsel
Connect members (regular rate: $75). This plan provides unlimited access
on an ongoing monthly basis. Your subscription continues automatically
on a month-to-month basis with your subscription automatically charged
to your credit card. Cancel at any time. Payment is via major credit card,
<B>online only</B>.</P>

<P><IMG SRC="orangeba.gif"  ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=+1> </FONT>Annual
Plan</B>: $476 for Counsel Connect members (regular rate: $595). This plan
works out to an average cost of less than $40 a month - our very best plan.
Payment is via major credit card, <B>online only</B>.</P>

<P>Above rates are for single users only. For special multi-user discount
packages, contact the Subscription Department at VersusLaw tollfree at
1-888-VERSUSLAW (1-888-377-8752) and dial extension 3027. Be sure to identify
yourself as a Counsel Connect member and provide your Counsel Connect member
ID to qualify for the special Counsel Connect multi-user discounts.</P>

<CENTER><P><FONT SIZE=+1><A HREF="http://www.counsel.com/opinions/signup.html">Register
or Renew your subscription</A></FONT><BR>
<A HREF="http://www.counsel.com/opinions/signup.html"><IMG SRC="register.gif" ALT="Sign Up" BORDER=0 HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=100 ALIGN=CENTER></A><BR>
</P></CENTER>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
