<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Counsel Quote -  Counsel Canvass</TITLE>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#FF0000" BACKGROUND="paper.gif">
<p align=center><img src="/counselquote/canvasheader.gif" width=600 height=100 alt="COUNSEL CANVAS"></P>
<HR>
<center><A HREF="/images/cquotenavbar.map"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/counselquote/cquotenavbar.gif" ISMAP></A></center>
<HR>

<BLOCKQUOTE><H2 align=center><font color=ff0000>Grappling With the Right to Die</font></H2>

<P>On March 6th, the 9th U.S. Circuit Court of Appeals ruled that terminally
ill patients have a constitutional right to die with the assistance of a
physician. </P>

<P>From March 15 to May 2nd, Counsel Connect asked members if they thought
that terminally ill patients have a right to physician-assisted suicide,
and whether the U.S. Supreme Court will affirm the 9th Circuit's opinion,
if it grants cert in that case. </P>

<P>We received 205 responses, and found that while a large majority (81
percent) supported the right to die, only about two-thirds (64 percent)
believed that the Supreme Court would support the right to die.</P>

<H4>Survey Questions and Results:</H4>

<P>1) Do you think that terminally ill patients should have the right to end
their lives with the assistance of a physician? </P>

<P>Yes: 167 responses (81 percent)</P>

<P>No: 38 responses (19 percent)</P>

<P>2) If this case goes to the Supreme Court, do you think it will support the
right to die?</P>

<P>Yes: 132 responses (64 percent)</P>

<P>No: 73 responses (36 percent)</P>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>WT07-B36-100</DOCNO>
<DOCOLDNO>IA022-000238-B024-50</DOCOLDNO>
