<P><BR>

<P>
<P><B>C</B>ovington  & Burling,  founded 75 years ago,  is one of the largest law firms in Washington,  D.C.,  and also has more than 20 lawyers in Europe. The firm's practice includes advice and representation in regulatory and legislative matters,  litigation,  and transactional work throughout the United States and abroad.
<P>
<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>The Antitrust Practice Group</H3></CENTER>

<P>Covington  & Burling has long played a leading role in the field of antitrust law. The firm is engaged in all aspects of antitrust litigation,  counseling,  and government proceedings,  both civil and criminal. The firm also deals regularly with state antitrust and franchise laws and business torts involving competition issues. The firm has extensive experience in every aspect of antitrust practice and with industries of all types. Two partners were formerly assistant attorneys general in charge of the Justice Department's Antitrust Division,  and many firm lawyers have other relevant government experience. The firm's European offices have an active antitrust practice before the European Commission and in the member states of the EU.<BR><P>Representative clients include Exxon,  Procter  & Gamble,  the National Football League,  Warner-Lambert Co.,  AlliedSignal,  Trane,  Canon,  Union Pacific,  Florida Power  & Light,  and Textron. The firm's antitrust clients also include many trade associations,  joint ventures,  and smaller companies. Among partners active in the antitrust field are:<BR>
