Chaoyang District,  Beijing 100020,  China<BR>
Tel 8610-501-3388,  ext 33078  <B>*</B>  Fax 8610-501-5186<BR>
<BR>
107 lawyers  <B>*</B>  9 lawyers in the Antitrust Practice Group<BR>
</CENTER>
<P>
<P>
<P>
<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Antitrust Practice</H3></CENTER>

<P><B>T</B>he Sherman Antitrust Law of 1890 was enacted long after the founding fathers of Gray Plant Mooty opened the doors of their law practice; but they studied hard and soon began counseling their clients regarding this `emerging' area of the law. Over a century later,  the antitrust laws continue to `emerge' and Gray Plant Mooty continues to provide counseling and tribunal/trial representation in all areas that antitrust (and unfair competition) laws intersect with your business (or that of your client),  including the following:<BR>
<UL><BR><BR><LI> Distribution and pricing practices (including price and non-price vertical restraints)<LI> Licensing of intellectual property rights<LI> Monopolies and regulated industries<LI> State and federal investigative demands<LI> Mergers and acquisitions (including premerger filings)<LI> Immunities and exemptions<LI> Trade associations and joint ventures<LI> Refusals to deal<BR>
<BR>
</UL><BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Antitrust Experience</H3></CENTER>

<P><BR><BR>
Gray Plant Mooty is active in both antitrust counseling and litigation. Our antitrust litigation group represents both plaintiffs and defendants. In recent years,  Gray Plant Mooty has defended companies charged with price-fixing,  tying,  dealer-terminations,  conspiracy,  boycotts,  exclusive dealing,  and monopolization,  among other claims. Gray Plant Mooty has recently litigated private treble-damage actions on behalf of plaintiffs involving claims of monopolization,  monopoly leveraging,  sales below cost,  refusals to deal,  boycotts,  regulated industries,  and bid-rigging. Gray Plant Mooty will,  in the right circumstances,  take plaintiffs' antitrust cases on a contingency basis.<BR><BR><P>We have litigated on behalf of and/or counseled clients regarding antitrust issues arising in the following industries:<BR>
<BR><UL><LI> health care<LI> telecommunications<LI> franchise<LI> insurance<LI> utilities<LI> biotechnology<LI> specialty retail<LI> automobile<LI> consumer electronics<LI> pharmaceuticals<LI> computers<LI> manufacturing<LI> agricultural products<LI> trucking/common carriers</UL><BR>
<BR>
<P>Please direct all inquiries to Gray Plant Mooty's Antitrust Practice Group chair: Richard G. Braman at Gray,  Plant,  Mooty,  Mooty  & Bennett,  P.A.,  3400 City Center,  33 South Sixth Street,  Minneapolis,  Minnesota 55402. E-mail: <A HREF="mailto:BramanRG%GPM@mcimail.com">BramanRG%GPM@mcimail.com</A><BR>
<BR>
<B>Richard G. Braman</B> is a partner in Gray Plant Mooty,  and he is also the current co-chair of the Minnesota State Bar Association's Antitrust Section. Richard has practiced in the area of antitrust and complex business litigation for 17 years,  representing both plaintiffs and defendants. He also counsels clients on antitrust and trade regulation issues. Richard started his career in 1978 at the San Francisco law firm of Brobeck,  Phleger  & Harrison and then spent five years at the Minneapolis law firm of Schatz,  Paquin,  Lockridge,  Grindal  & Holstein where he focused on plaintiffs' class action antitrust litigation. Richard is a <I>summa cum laude</I> graduate of the University of Minnesota and a <I>magna cum laude</I> graduate of the University of Minnesota Law School.<BR>


</UL></BODY>
