<P><BR>

<P>
<P><B>K</B>ilpatrick  & Cody (K &C) offers a full range of legal services to business clients around the world from offices in Atlanta and Augusta,  Georgia; Washington,  D.C.; London; and Brussels. Among its 218 attorneys are five former chairmen of the State Bar of Georgia's Antitrust Section. K &C attorneys have extensive experience in all aspects of antitrust and trade-regulation practice,  including civil and criminal litigation; regulatory proceedings; federal and state civil antitrust investigations and grand jury proceedings; Hart-Scott-Rodino premerger filing and enforcement proceedings; transaction analysis; and day-to-day business counseling to avoid antitrust and trade-regulation problems.
<P><BR><P><I>Antitrust and Trade Regulation Practice </I>K &C attorneys have represented both plaintiffs and defendants in a broad range of antitrust and related litigation,  including class action and multidistrict proceedings; civil actions for damages and injunctive relief; grand jury proceedings and criminal enforcement actions; merger investigations and enforcement proceedings; Federal Trade Commission enforcement actions; Department of Justice enforcement actions; investigations and enforcement proceedings instituted by state attorneys general; antitrust claims and counterclaims in intellectual property litigation; and other complex economic litigation involving issues of competition law. Our business counseling practice includes day-to-day analysis and advice regarding joint ventures,  mergers,  distribution arrangements,  pricing practices,  and industry and trade associations. We regularly assist our clients in evaluating potential antitrust problems with proposed business arrangements to structure risk-avoiding solutions. The firm has particular expertise in health care collaborative ventures. K &C attorneys frequently conduct antitrust audits,  prepare tailored antitrust guidelines,  and present antitrust compliance programs.<BR><P><I>Representative Clients.</I> Aaron Rents Inc.; BellSouth Corporation; BellSouth Enterprises,  Inc.; Blue Cross/Blue Shield Association; Delta Airlines,  Inc.; Equifax Inc.; Flowers Industries,  Inc.; Interface Inc.; Intermet Corporation; Lockheed Aeronautical Systems Co.; National Cardiovascular Network,  Inc.; PepsiCo,  Inc.; Progressive Health Care Providers,  Inc.; Raytheon Company; Schlumberger Inc.; Spalding  & Evenflo Companies; University Hospital (Augusta,  Georgia); The Weather Channel.<BR>
<BR><P>Partners with extensive antitrust experience include:<BR>
<BR>
<UL><BR>
