<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>Antitrust</H2>
<H3>Vorys,  Sater, Seymour and Pease
</H3>

</CENTER>
<B><CENTER>Columbus:</B> 52 East Gay Street,  Columbus,  OH 44126<BR>
Tel 614-464-6400  <B>*</B>  Fax 614-464-6350<BR>
<B>Cincinnati:</B> Suite 2100,  Atrium Two,  221 East Fourth Street,  Cincinnati,  OH 45201<BR>
Tel 513-723-4000  <B>*</B>  Fax 513-723-4056<BR>
<B>Cleveland:</B> 2100 One Cleveland Center,  1375 East Ninth Street,  Cleveland,  OH 44114<BR>
Tel 216-479-6100  <B>*</B>  Fax 216-479-6060<BR>
<B>Washington:</B> Suite 1111,  1828 L Street N.W.,  Washington,  DC 20036<BR>
Tel 202-467-8800  <B>*</B>  Fax 202-467-8900<BR>
<BR>
285 lawyers  <B>*</B>  11 lawyers in Antitrust Practice Group<BR>
</CENTER>
<P>See this firm's profiles in the following other directories:<BR>
<UL><BR>
   <LI><A HREF="../95CLFolder/vorys.html"> Commercial Litigation</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95CSFFolder/vorys.html"> Corporate Securities</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95ENVFolder/vorys.html"> Environmental</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95IPFolder/vorys.html"> Intellectual Property</A>
   <LI><A HREF="..//vorys.html"> International</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95LABFolder/vorys.html"> Labor</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95PLFolder/vorys.html"> Product Liability</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95WCCFolder/vorys.html"> White Collar Crime</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95WOFolder/vorys.html"> Workout</A>
</UL>

<P>
<P>
<P><B>V</B>orys,  Sater,  Seymour and Pease offers national and international representation in all areas of law including antitrust,  bankruptcy,  commercial,  corporate,  energy,  government contracting,  health care,  insurance,  intellectual property,  international,  labor,  legislation,  litigation,  public utilities,  real estate,  and white collar defense.<BR><P>Experience in antitrust litigation includes: defending Occidental Petroleum Corporation against a lawsuit challenging its attempt to acquire Mead Corp.; defending AT &T in litigation challenging its acquisition of NCR Corp.; representing Mobil Oil in its attempted acquisition of Marathon Oil; representing a major health insurance company challenging territorial restrictions imposed by a national trade association; defending a major insurance company in precedent-setting litigation regarding physician control of health insurance companies; prosecuting on behalf of supermarkets a lawsuit against several supermarket chains and their union charging a conspiracy to restrict competition; defending a university in an investigation of an alleged conspiracy among private universities in setting tuition fees and professors' salaries; defending an international concrete pipe company in a coordinated FTC and grand jury investigation resulting in indictments of companies and individuals other than our client; notification filings for the FTC and Department of Justice; counseling on the dangers of market definitions unique to the high tech industry,  software and maintenance 'tying' problems; and the intersections between the antitrust laws and the protections provided by intellectual property status.<BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>James P. Kennedy</B> (<I>Columbus; 614-464-6245</I>) A partner with substantial trial experience in complex commercial and criminal antitrust litigation. Mr. Kennedy represented a defendant in <I>U.S. </I>v.<I> N.L. Industries,  et al.</I>,  where the jury returned a not-guilty verdict. Supervised a project which provides `Sample Jury Instructions in Criminal Antitrust Cases' for members of the bench and the bar (ABA Press,  1984). He participated in the revision of the ABA's <I>Criminal Antitrust Litigation Manual</I>. Fellow of the American College of Trial Lawyers. University of Michigan,  J.D.,  1959. Admitted in Ohio.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Michael J. Canter</B> (<I>Columbus; 614-464-6327</I>) Practice includes specialization in antitrust law,  including defense and prosecution of civil actions and defense of criminal investigations and indictments. Mr. Canter works closely with Community Mutual Insurance Company,  one of the nation's largest Blue Cross and Blue Shield plans. He also provides general litigation representation to The Limited,  Inc. Other recent responsibilities include representation of an automobile manufacturer in a Federal Trade Commission investigation and defense of a major pharmaceutical manufacturer in nationwide federal multidistrict and state litigations concerning alleged violations of the Sherman Act,  the Robinson-Patman Act,  and similar state laws. Mr. Canter is vice-chair of the Civil Litigation Committee of the Antitrust Section of the American Bar Association and a member of the Board of Governors of the Antitrust Section of the Ohio State Bar Association.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Ivery D. Foreman</B> (<I>Columbus; 614-464-6322</I>) Practices in corporate and securities,  and antitrust regulatory law. Extensive experience regarding compliance with,  and pre-merger notification filings under,  the Hart-Scott-Rodino Antitrust Improvements Act. Northwestern University,  J.D.,  1978. Admitted in Ohio.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Laura G. Kuykendall</B> (<I>Columbus; 614-464-6445</I>) Extensive experience in state and federal antitrust investigations,  counseling,  and civil litigation. Significant experience in complex corporate takeover litigation,  including AT &T/NCR,  Mead/Occidental,  and Mobil/Marathon. Member,  ABA Antitrust and Litigation Sections,  Ohio State Bar Association Antitrust Section. Contributing author,  <I>Antitrust Counseling and Litigation Techniques</I> (Van Kalinowski,  general editor). University of Virginia,  J.D.,  1978. Admitted in Ohio.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Ellen A. Efros</B> (<I>Washington; 202-467-8803</I>) Extensive experience in all areas of antitrust law and intellectual property law. Hofstra University,  J.D.,  1978. Admitted in the District of Columbia,  New York,  and Maryland.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>James A. Wilson</B> (<I>Columbus; 614-464-5606</I>) Substantial experience in civil and criminal antitrust litigation and representation of clients in grand jury and FTC investigations. Assistant editor,  ABA <I>Antitrust Law Journal</I> (1992- ); Board of Governors,  Ohio State Bar Association Antitrust Section. Columbia University,  J.D.,  1985. Admitted in Ohio.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>

</UL>


</UL></BODY>
