<CENTER>
<H2>Commercial Litigation</H2>
<H3>Babst,  Calland,  Clements and Zomnir
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>Pittsburgh:</B> Two Gateway Center,  Pittsburgh,  PA 15222<BR>
Tel 412-394-5400  <B>*</B>  Fax 412-394-6576<BR>
<B>Philadelphia:</B> The Curtis Center,  Suite 1100,  Sixth  & Walnut Streets, <BR>
Philadelphia,  PA 19106<BR>
Tel 215-627-3056  <B>*</B>  Fax 215-627-3042<BR>
<BR>
50 lawyers  <B>*</B>  24 lawyers in construction,  environmental and corporate/commercial litigation<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>
<P>
<P>
<P><B>N</B>amed as one of the country's top law firms for litigation and environmental law in <I>The American Lawyer</I>'s recent 'Clients' Choice' survey of law firms for service,  quality and value,  Babst,  Calland,  Clements and Zomnir,  A Professional Corporation (`BCC &Z') provides focused legal assistance in the areas of construction,  environmental,  and corporate/commercial litigation. Founded in 1986,  BCC &Z has grown to 50 lawyers and 16 paralegals,  with a majority dedicated to addressing the litigation needs of its clients.
<P>
<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Construction Litigation</H3></CENTER>

<P>BCC &Z has represented clients from all facets of the construction industry in a wide range of complex construction disputes. Matters in both government and private contracting have been handled by BCC &Z throughout the country,  ranging from residential to commercial/industrial disputes. In addition,  coupled with its environmental practice group,  BCC &Z has addressed cases involving environmental remediation contracting,  and with its energy practice group,  the Firm has litigated matters regarding power plant facilities.<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Environmental Litigation</H3></CENTER>

<P>A significant amount of the Firm's focus lies in the field of environmental litigation. BCC &Z has resolved many complex environmental cases for some of the country's largest steel,  chemical,  petroleum,  and transportation companies. The Firm combines experienced environmental litigators with its staff of 15 environmental regulatory lawyers in representing clients in federal and state administrative and judicial actions all across the country. These cases include private cost-recovery matters,  remedial construction disputes,  and multimedia enforcement cases.<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Corporate/Commercial Litigation</H3></CENTER>

<P>BCC &Z has litigated a vast variety of complex corporate/commercial cases. The Firm has represented clients in disputes including products liability,  commercial contracts,  Uniform Commercial Code,  shareholder rights,  securities,  unfair competition,  antitrust,  RICO,  and media-related matters.<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Representative Clients</H3></CENTER>

<P>Beazer East,  Inc.,  Columbia Gas of Pennsylvania,  Inc.,  Dravo Corporation,  General Chemical Corp.,  Inland Steel Corp.,  Mannesmann Demeg Corp.,  National Steel Corporation,  North American Chemical Company,  Nova Corporation,  PNC Bank Corp.,  Quaker State Corporation,  Rexroth Corp.,  USAir,  Inc.,  Weirton Steel Corporation,  and Westinghouse Electric Corp.<BR><P>A partial listing of BCC &Z lawyers follows:<BR>
<BR>
<UL><BR>
