<P>
<P><B>B</B>ondurant,  Mixson  & Elmore (BME) practices complex civil and white collar criminal litigation.
<P>
<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Commercial Litigation Experience and Clients</H3></CENTER>

<P>BME represents plaintiffs and defendants before state and federal trial and appellate courts,  administrative agencies,  and grand juries throughout the United States and in alternative forms of dispute resolution such as mediation,  arbitration,  and proceedings before special masters. BME regularly handles litigation involving antitrust,  bankruptcy,  business torts,  corporate governance,  employment,  environmental,  insurance,  intellectual property,  personal injury,  product liability,  professional liability,  RICO,  securities,  and white collar criminal litigation.<BR><P>The firm's representative clients include Aetna,  Delta Air Lines,  The Trammell Crow Companies,  and Wyle Laboratories.<BR>
<BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>Emmet J. Bondurant II </B>has extensive experience in the fields of antitrust and unfair competition,  securities,  lawyer liability,  and white collar criminal defense litigation. He is a member of the American Law Institute,  the American College of Trial Lawyers,  and a fellow of the American Bar Association. Law clerk to Judge Clement F. Haynsworth,  Jr.,  U.S. Court of Appeals for the Fourth Circuit. University of Georgia,  A.B.,  <I>cum laude</I>,  1958,  LL.B.,  <I>magna cum laude</I>,  1960; Harvard University,  LL.M.,  1962.<BR>
<BR>
