<BR>
<LI><B>M. Jerome Elmore</B> has a broad range of experience in business litigation,  with particular emphasis on environmental and real estate litigation. His practice also includes personal injury and product liability litigation. University of Virginia,  B.A.,  high honors,  1970; Emory University,  J.D.,  1976; member,  editorial board,  <I>Emory Law Journal</I>. Admitted in Georgia and Florida.<BR>
