<BR>
240 lawyers  <B>*</B>  50 lawyers in complex business litigation<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>
<P><BR>

<P>
<P><B>B</B>uchanan Ingersoll provides clients with cost-effective access to 50 commercial litigators in eight offices through an integrated network approach. This regional structure broadens the availability of our services by having more lawyers accessible in more areas.
<P><BR><P>We litigate and provide litigation counseling on behalf of a broad and diverse cross-section of regional,  national,  and international businesses. Our clients expect excellence in advocacy,  work product,  service,  and cost-effective representation. They expect to be part of the litigation decision-making process. They expect successful results at the negotiation table,  through arbitration or other alternative dispute resolution mechanisms,  or at trial.<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Clients and Experience</H3></CENTER>

<P>Among Buchanan Ingersoll's clients in the area of litigation are Alexander  & Alexander Inc.,  Armstrong World Industries,  Inc.,  CNG Transmission Corp.,  Edward J. DeBartolo Corporation,  Integra Financial Corporation,  National Mine Service Company,  Pennzoil Company,  and PNC Bank,  N.A.<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Practice Areas</H3></CENTER>

<P><BR><BR>
Buchanan Ingersoll has litigated and tried cases in the following practice areas:<BR><BR><UL><LI>Admiralty<LI>Antitrust<LI>Bankruptcy<LI>Cable television<LI>Class actions<LI>Coal<LI>Construction<LI>Contracts<LI>Copyrights/trademarks<LI>Covenants not to compete<LI>Employment agreements<LI>Employment & labor<LI>Environmental<LI>ERISA<LI>Family law<LI>First amendment<LI>Insurance<LI>Intellectual property<LI>Lender liability<LI>Letters of credit<LI>Liquor law & licensing<LI>Mergers & acquisitions<LI>Oil & gas<LI>Patent<LI>Personal injury<LI>Product liability<LI>PUC & energy<LI>Real estate<LI>Shareholder suits<LI>Securities <LI>Taxation<LI>Toxic substance<LI>Trade secrets<LI>White collar criminal defense<LI>Workman's compensation<LI>Zoning<BR>
<BR></UL>
<LI><B>Samuel W. Braver</B> (<I>412-562-8939</I>) is chairman of the firm's Commercial Litigation Section. He has 20 years of experience and has served as lead trial counsel in many commercial cases tried to final verdict,  both jury and nonjury,  and has been involved in a significant amount of appellate work. His cases involve banking,  environmental,  oil and gas law,  insurance defense,  and contract litigation. He is a 1974 graduate of the Duquesne University School of Law.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Leonard J. Marsico</B> (<I>412-562-8940</I>) works exclusively in commercial litigation matters,  many of which are national in scope. His cases primarily involve banking,  transactional,  environmental,  securities,  and general corporate litigation. He is a 1980 graduate of the University of Pittsburgh School of Law.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Pamela A. McCallum</B> (<I>412-562-1412</I>) tries cases involving trade secrets,  covenants not to compete,  employees' fiduciary duties to employers,  and unfair competition. She is a 1982 graduate of the Georgetown University School of Law.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Arthur J. Schwab</B> (<I>412-562-1438</I>) is Chair of Litigation. With more than two decades of litigation experience,  he has a national litigation practice and has tried cases in state and federal courts in over 22 different states. He is a 1972 graduate of the University of Virginia School of Law.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Thomas L. VanKirk</B> (<I>412-562-8875</I>) has an active commercial litigation and trade regulation practice. His trade regulation work includes litigation and corporate advising on antitrust matters,  both domestic and foreign,  including international licensing and joint technology agreements. He is a 1970 graduate of the Dickinson College School of Law.<BR>

</UL></BODY>
