<CENTER>
<H2>Commercial Litigation</H2>
<H3>Calhoun & Stacy, P.C.</H3>
</CENTER><CENTER><B>Dallas:</B> 5700 NationsBank Plaza, 901 Main Street, Dallas, TX 75202-3747<BR>Tel 214-748-5000 <B>*</B> Fax 214-748-1421<BR><BR>18 lawyers <B>*</B> 14 lawyers in commercial litigation<BR></CENTER>

<P><P><BR><P><B>F</B>or more than twenty years, litigation has been the mainstay of Calhoun & Stacy, P.C. The Dallas-based firm is a strong mid-sized firm which is committed to the zealous delivery of quality legal service bounded by the highest standards of ethics. Our client list includes international, national, and local businesses, including service businesses, telecommunications companies, transportation companies, insurance companies, manufacturers, real estate companies, financial institutions, and proprietorships, as well as individuals and families.<BR><BR><P>Calhoun & Stacy assists clients in sophisticated problem solving by pursuing the right combination of litigation, arbitration, or mediation . Our experience includes the following areas:<BR><BR><UL><LI>Antitrust<LI>Aviation<LI>Banking & Financial Institutions<LI>Bankruptcy & Creditors' Rights<LI>Condemnation<LI>Construction<LI>Contracts<LI>Corporate<LI>Defamation<LI>Employment<LI>Environmental<LI>Franchising<LI>General Casualty<LI>Insurance Defense<LI>Lender Liability<LI>Personal Injury<LI>Products Liability<LI>Professional Liability & Malpractice<LI>Railroads<LI>Real Estate<LI>Telecommunications<LI>Transportation<LI>Travel<LI>Trucking<LI>Workers' Compensation<LI>Wrongful Termination<BR><BR></UL><CENTER><B>Representative Clients</B></CENTER><BR>Allstate Insurance; American General Hospitality, Inc.; APAC Texas, Inc.; Ashland Oil, Inc.; Avis Rent-A-Car; Carolina Casualty Insurance; Dallas Area Rapid Transit (DART); Dresser Industries; Dynamo Corporation; Fireman's Fund Insurance; Hayes Leasng Company; Inwood National Bank; Jackson-Shaw Company; Kitty Hawk Group, Inc.; Marriott Corporation; MCI Telecommunications; Metropolitan Insurance Company; Mirage Resorts, Inc.; Norfolk Southern Railway; North American Specialty Insurance; North American Van Lines, Inc.; Omega Travel; Quest Communications; Southern Pacific Transportation Company; Terminix Company; Thor Energy; Transport Insurance Company; and Zupata Partnerships.<BR><BR><P>The litigation practice group includes the following shareholders:<BR><BR><LI><B>Mark Alan Calhoun</B>  Mr. Calhoun is a founder, chairman, and CEO of Calhoun & Stacy. His primary emphasis is in the area of general civil litigation, where he has represented primarily national clients in major transportation, telecommunications, banking, construction, condemnation and general business litigation matters. University of Texas, B.B.A., 1969, J.D., 1972.<BR><BR><LI><B>Dennis D. Conder</B>  Mr. Conder concentrates most of his practice in the insurance defense area. He has represented clients in the areas of general negligence, aviation negligence, and product liability claims; premises liability; medical malpractice; workers' compensation; and claims asserting "bad faith" and Texas Deceptive Trade Practices Act violations. Southwestern University, B.B.A., 1983; Baylor University Law School, J.D., 1986; Phi Delta Phi.<BR><BR><LI><B>David W. Elrod</B>  Mr. Elrod has experience in all major areas of the commercial litigation practice, including general contract, antitrust, commodities, securities, employment, fraudulent sales law, banking, creditors' rights and bankruptcy litigation. He also has experience in telecommunications, lender liability, officer and director liability, construction, and real estate litigation. Oklahoma State University, B.S., 1974; University of Oklahoma, J.D., 1978; Order of the Coif; Phi Kappa Phi; editor, <I>Oklahoma Law Review</I><BR><BR><LI><B>Steven D. Goldston</B>  Mr. Goldston had litigation experience in oil and gas, banking, real estate, consumer protection, condemnation, probate, and land title matters. He also serves as counsel to several banks. Mr. Goldston is certified in Civil Trial Law by the Texas Board of Legal Specialization, and he is also a certified public  accountant. University of Texas, B.B.A., highest honors, 1978, J.D., honors, 1982; Order of the Coif.<BR> <BR><LI><B>V. Paige Pace</B>  Ms. Pace is certified in Personal Injury Trial Law by the Texas Board of Legal Specialization. She has represented clients in the areas of products liability, premises liability, business tort, employment, automobile collision, employment, workers' compensation, and sexual assault. She has also represented physicians and hospitals in medical negligence cases. Texas Christian University, B.S., 1980; South Texas College of Law, J.D., <I>cum laude</I>, 1984; Order of Lytae; National Orders of Barristers.<BR><BR><LI><B>Roy L. Stacy</B>  Mr. Stacy focues his practice in the areas of commercial and tort litigation. He directs Calhoun & Stacy's tort litigation practice and has represented insurance companies and self-insured companies in the defense of suits alleging medical malpractice, products liability, bad faith, and general casualty loss. He also has experience in cases dealing with employment law, securities violations, patent infringements, noncompetition agreements, real estate disputes, and partnership dissolutions. Angelo State University, B.A., 1972; Baylor University School of Law, J.D., <I>cum laude</I>, 1974; associate editor, <I>Baylor Law Review</I>
