<HEAD>
<TITLE>Collier,  Shannon,  Rill  & Scott
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>Commercial Litigation</H2>
<H3>Collier,  Shannon,  Rill  & Scott
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>Washington:</B> 3050 K Street,  N.W.,  Suite 400,  Washington,  DC 20007<BR>
Tel 202-342-8400  <B>*</B>  Fax 202-338-5534  <B>*</B>  E-mail: <A HREF="mailto:Col1DC01.MHS@Compuserve.Com">Col1DC01.MHS@Compuserve.Com</A><BR>
<BR>
85 lawyers  <B>*</B>  22 lawyers in the litigation group<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>See this firm's profiles in the following other directories:<BR>
<UL><BR>
   <LI><A HREF="../95ATFolder/collier.html"> Antitrust</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95IPFolder/collier.html"> Intellectual Property</A>
</UL>

<P>
<P>
<P><B>C</B>ollier,  Shannon,  Rill  & Scott,  founded in 1963 in Washington,  D.C.,  today has approximately 85 lawyers. Litigation is one of its primary areas of practice. The Firm's client base includes domestic and international corporations and numerous Fortune 500 corporations,  as well as smaller businesses engaged in manufacturing,  communications,  pharmaceuticals,  finance,  agriculture,  health care,  energy,  and services,  and more than 100 trade associations.
<P>
<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>The Litigation Practice</H3></CENTER>

<P><BR>
<BR><P><I><LI> Antitrust:</I> The firm represents large corporations with significant antitrust matters,  including issues of false advertising and consumer protection.<BR><BR><P><I><LI> Government Contracts,  Contracts and Commercial Law:</I> The group handles government,  construction,  and other private contract disputes,  lending relationship disputes,  real estate litigation,  condemnation matters,  intra-corporate and intra-partnership disputes,  and the full range of general commercial and corporate defense litigation,  as well as ADR.<BR>
<BR><P><I><LI> Environmental:</I> We represent clients in enforcement proceedings,  contamination cases under CERCLA,  and lawsuits seeking indemnification for environmental expenses.<BR>
<BR><P><I><LI> Intellectual Property:</I> We represent clients in patent,  trademark,  copyright,  trade secrets,  licensing,  and false advertising litigation.<BR>
<BR><P><I><LI> Product Liability:</I> Representation of manufacturing and pharmaceutical companies in the defense of product liability actions,  and recalls by the administrative agencies.<BR>
<BR><P><I><LI> Labor:</I> Representation and counseling employers and fiduciaries about federal,  state,  and local labor laws,  ERISA,  and employment discrimination matters.<BR>
<BR><P><I><LI> Administrative: </I>Representation and counseling of companies before numerous federal agencies,  including the Department of Justice,  FTC,  CPSC,  Department of Labor,  EEOC,  Pension Benefit Guarantee Corporation,  NLRB,  Occupational Safety and Health Review Commission,  U.S. Patent and Trademark Office,  Department of Energy,  and Department of Transportation.<BR>
<BR><P><I><LI> Bankruptcy:</I> Representation of creditors,  partners,  and shareholders of many bankrupt and near-bankrupt entities and related negotiations in bankruptcy courts and courts of general jurisdiction around the country.<BR>
<BR>
<BR><BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Representative Clients and Experience</H3></CENTER>

<P>Allegheny Ludlum,  American Stores,  Briggs  & Stratton,  CSX,  Danaher,  Frito-Lay,  General Motors,  Glaxo,  International Paper,  Holiday Inns,  Lykes Bros. Steamship,  Mobil Chemical,  Mobil Oil,  Marion Merrell Dow,  Inc.,  Murray Ohio,  Merit System,  National Labor Union Health and Welfare Fund,  PepsiCo,  Petrolon,  RJR,  Scottish Lion Insurance,  Triangle Wire and Cable,  and Weyerhauser.<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Firm Attorneys</H3></CENTER>

<UL><BR><LI><B>Mark Austrian</B> (<I>202-342-8495</I>) concentrates in complex litigation and has handled jury trials in large pharmaceutical cases. His practice also includes litigation in environmental,  product liability,  administrative agency,  and intellectual property matters. University of Pennsylvania Law School,  1970.<BR><BR><LI><B>Patrick Coyne</B> (<I>202-342-8606</I>) concentrates in intellectual property matters where he both advises clients and litigates cases. He is a registered patent attorney and has also litigated other cases involving pharmaceutical,  chemical,  and mechanical products and processes and antitrust issues. University of Virginia Law School,  1982.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Karen Lockwood</B> (<I>202-342-8870</I>) concentrates in complex commercial litigation and government contracts,  including construction and service contracts. She advises clients in pre-litigation strategy and is experienced in ADR. American University,  Washington College of Law,  1978.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Michael O'Connell</B> (<I>202-342-8600</I>) concentrates in transportation litigation and tax-related transportation matters. Catholic University of America,  Columbus School of Law,  1984.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Brad Reynolds</B> (<I>202-342-8634</I>) is a former assistant attorney general in the Civil Rights Division of the U.S. Department of Justice,  assistant to the Solicitor General,  and counselor to the Attorney General of the United States. He has tried a broad range of civil and criminal matters at the trial,  appellate,  and Supreme Court levels. Vanderbilt University School of Law,  1967.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>William Rodgers</B> (<I>202-342-8470</I>) is a former executive assistant to the Secretary of Labor and concentrates in labor law. He has represented major corporations and multiemployee bargaining groups in labor relations,  ERISA,  employment discrimination,  labor disputes,  and sexual harassment cases. Fordham University Law School,  1968.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Dan Sullivan</B> (<I>202-342-8558</I>) has been lead trial counsel on matters ranging from a hostile corporate takeover attempt,  to an inverse condemnation case against the United States,  to representation of the secured creditors in a $1.4 billion real estate bankruptcy. American University,  Washington College of Law,  1977.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>John Williams</B> (<I>202-342-8435</I>) has focused his litigation practice on matters involving antitrust and intellectual property. He has represented both plaintiffs and defendants and won several substantial judgments in jury cases. Catholic University,  Columbus School of Law,  1978.<BR>
<BR>

</UL>
