<HEAD>
<TITLE>Gardner,  Carton  & Douglas
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>Commercial Litigation</H2>
<H3>Gardner,  Carton  & Douglas
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>Chicago:</B> 321 North Clark Street,  Chicago,  IL 60610<BR>
Tel 312-644-3000  <B>*</B>  Fax 312-644-3381<BR>
<B>Washington:</B> 1301 K Street,  N.W.,  Washington,  DC 20005<BR>
Tel 202-408-7100  <B>*</B>  Fax 202-289-1504<BR>
<BR>
206 lawyers  <B>*</B>  67 lawyers in the litigation practice<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>
<P><BR>

<P>
<P><B>F</B>ounded in 1910,  Gardner,  Carton  & Douglas is a Chicago-based,  full-service corporate law firm with one-third of its lawyers in the litigation area.<BR><BR>
<P><I>Business Litigation and Regulatory</I> Gardner,  Carton  & Douglas attorneys have litigated business disputes of virtually every type,  including cases arising from business transactions between small private companies and disputes involving multinational conglomerates. We have represented clients in actions involving banks,  brokerage houses,  natural resources developers,  manufacturers,  utilities,  and service providers. These cases have included complex contract claims,  the Uniform Commercial Code,  business torts,  breaches of fiduciary duty,  fraud and thefts of trade secrets,  product liability,  breaches of warranty,  antitrust,  RICO,  securities,  dealer termination claims,  and claims under state fair trade laws. We also have extensive experience at all levels of regulatory enforcement and in multijurisdictional enforcement actions.<BR><BR><P><I>Antitrust Litigation</I> The firm's experience includes every area of antitrust litigation. Our antitrust trial lawyers defend government criminal antitrust cases and conduct civil treble-damage litigation for plaintiffs and defendants. Clients call on us to respond to Justice Department,  Federal Trade Commission,  and other government investigations into industry behavior; we defend individuals and corporations facing grand jury antitrust investigations. We also advise clients on antitrust considerations in all types of business relations,  including mergers,  acquisitions,  tender offers,  and joint ventures,  and we defend corporations in government merger challenges. We have represented both sides in antitrust class actions,  and have tried antitrust injunction cases to courts and damages cases to juries throughout the country. Leaders in the health care antitrust bar,  our attorneys have tried three of the six hospital merger challenges brought to trial by the Department of Justice and the FTC. We brought the first and only successful plaintiff's antitrust case to block a merger of competing hospitals.<BR>
<BR><P><I>Health Care Litigation</I> We handle virtually every sort of adversarial proceeding for hospitals,  HMOs,  physicians,  treatment centers,  health care providers,  and support services across the country. We have successfully defended merging hospitals and HMOs,  and have defended hospitals against claims brought by medical staff.<BR>
<BR><P><I>Securities and Financial Products and Services Litigation</I> The firm has litigated securities issues under all major federal securities laws. We have represented acquiring and target corporations in proxy contests and takeovers. We have represented purchasers and sellers in post-acquisition litigation over failures to disclose under the securities laws and other matters related to securities fraud. We represent brokers and investment bankers and have been active in securities-related corporate investigations. The firm also represents clients in the evolving financial services industry. We have successfully represented clients before regulatory agencies,  state and federal courts,  securities and futures exchanges,  and in options arbitration. Our practice includes securities,  commodity futures and options,  oil and gas ventures,  limited partnerships,  and other investments.<BR>
<BR><P><I>Environmental Litigation</I> We conduct environmental litigation of all types at both the state and federal levels,  and in enforcement actions and Superfund proceedings.<BR>
<BR><P><I>Employment Litigation</I> The firm represents clients in employment litigation ranging from major class actions before the U.S. Supreme Court to suits involving individual employees and claims of discrimination,  libel,  defamation,  breach of contract,  torts,  and breach of noncompetition and confidentiality agreements.<BR>
<BR><P><I>Arbitration and Alternative Dispute Resolution</I> We have extensive experience in domestic and international arbitration forums,  including the International Chamber of Commerce,  arbitration forums for all financial markets,  AAA arbitration,  mediated disputes,  and alternative forums. We participate in the Center for Public Resources,  a leading New York alternative dispute resolution organization.<BR>
<BR><P><I>Intellectual Property Litigation</I> Our litigators represent clients in patent,  trademark,  copyright,  and trade secret actions in state and federal courts and before the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office.<BR>
<BR><P><I>White Collar Criminal Defense</I> We regularly represent corporations and individuals in state and federal white collar criminal investigations and trials. We have tried criminal cases and represented parties in grand jury investigations throughout the United States. <BR>
<BR><P><I>Product Liability</I> The firm has handled the full spectrum of product liability litigation,  including trials,  case management,  and counseling.<BR>
<BR><P><I>Bankruptcy Litigation</I> We regularly represent parties in bankruptcy litigation. Our lawyers won the leading lender liability decision in the U.S. courts on behalf of one of our lender clients.<BR>
<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Representative Clients</H3></CENTER>

<P>Adventist Health System; Allied Products Corporation; AM International,  Inc.; Ameritech Corporation; Archer Daniels Midland; Cherry Communications,  Inc.; First Options of Chicago; Kerr-McGee Chemical Corporation; Pacific Dunlop Limited; and Sears Roebuck  & Co.,  Inc.<BR>
<UL><BR>
