<P>
<P>
<P><B>H</B>onigman Miller Schwartz and Cohn is a full-service business law firm. Our litigation practice is enhanced by our broad practice in the areas of corporate,  securities,  workout and restructuring,  real estate,  finance,  employee benefits,  tax,  environmental,  health care and hospitals,  labor,  antitrust,  and trade regulation law.<BR>
<P>
<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Litigation Practice</H3></CENTER>

<P>Our litigators have experience in cases of all sizes,  from nationwide class action lawsuits,  to trials and appeals,  to administrative hearings and commercial arbitrations. Defending some of the largest claims ever filed in Michigan,  including securities and derivative actions seeking up to $4 billion,  we have obtained results ranging from outright dismissals to highly favorable settlements. On behalf of business plaintiffs,  we have obtained multimillion-dollar jury verdicts in contract,  commercial,  and insurance cases.<BR><P>Our litigators,  resident in our offices in Michigan,  Florida,  and California,  practice in such diverse areas as corporate and securities litigation,  class actions,  commercial and contract litigation,  product liability,  real estate and construction litigation,  banking and lender liability,  zoning and land use,  environmental and toxic tort litigation,  insurance litigation,  media law,  libel law,  intellectual property,  divorce,  white collar crime,  and immigration.<BR>
<BR><P>We have handled lawsuits throughout the continental United States,  as well as in Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands. We have also served the legal community through scholarship,  teaching,  and service to the bar,  including Jason Honigman's treatises on the Michigan Court Rules and James K. Robinson's leading role in drafting the Michigan Rules of Evidence.<BR>
<BR><P>Litigation clients include national and multinational corporations,  small and medium-sized entities,  and individuals. They have included Burroughs Corp.,  Consumers Power Co.,  Detroit Free Press,  Ford Motor Land Development Corp.,  General Electric Capital Auto Lease Inc.,  General Motors Acceptance Corp.,  NBD Bank,  N.A.,  PHM Corp.,  Renaissance Center Partnership,  Roney  & Co.,  Sandy Corp.,  Speed Queen Co.,  Unisys,  Walbridge Aldinger Co.,  Whirlpool Financial Corp.,  and Dean Witter.<BR>
