<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Howrey  & Simon</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL><CENTER><H2>Commercial Litigation</H2><H3>Howrey  & Simon</H3><B>Washington:</B> 1299 Pennsylvania Avenue,  N.W.,  Washington,  DC 20004<BR>Tel 202-783-0800  <B>*</B>  Fax 202-383-6610<BR><B>Los Angeles: </B>550 South Hope Street,  Suite 1400,  Los Angeles,  CA 90071<BR>Tel 213-892-1800  <B>*</B>  Fax 213-892-2300<BR><BR>300 lawyers  <B>*</B>  140 lawyers in complex business litigation<BR></CENTER><P>See this firm's profiles in the following other directories:<BR><UL><BR>   <LI><A HREF="../95ATFolder/howrey.html"> Antitrust</A>   <LI><A HREF="../95ENVFolder/howrey.html"> Environmental</A>   <LI><A HREF="../95IPFolder/howrey.html"> Intellectual Property</A>   <LI><A HREF="../95PLFolder/howrey.html"> Product Liability</A>   <LI><A HREF="..//howrey.html"> White Collar Crim</A></UL><P><BR><BR><P><BR><P><B>F</B>ounded in 1956,  Howrey  & Simon is the fourth largest firm in Washington,  D.C.,  with a national and international practice. The firm is primarily engaged in matters involving litigation and government regulation. Our work is supported by Capital Economics,  Capital Accounting,  and Capital Environmental,  affiliates with more than 30 economists,  financial analysts,  and environmental specialists.<BR><P><BR><CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Complex Business Litigation</H3></CENTER><P>Howrey  & Simon built its reputation around its capabilities of taking the largest of cases to trial and winning. We represent scores of companies in business litigation of virtually every kind and character. In the process,  we have developed what we believe to be one of the largest groups of experienced counsel in the United States dedicated to litigation. We have handled numerous cases involving antitrust,  product liability,  business torts,  complex contracts,  fraud,  government contracts,  RICO,  securities,  patents/trademarks/copyrights,  insurance coverage,  and environmental matters. Our litigation experience is widely dispersed throughout the federal and state court systems of the United States. The firm also has a group of highly experienced appellate lawyers who handle complex appeals,  mainly in the federal circuit courts,  the U.S. Supreme Court,  and various state appellate courts. We are also experienced in utilizing alternative dispute resolution to achieve the most efficient,  economical,  and effective results.<BR><BR><P>While the firm is best known for its defense work,  it has represented plaintiffs and in the process has achieved some of the largest jury awards in the United States affirmed on appeal,  including a jury verdict of more than $275 million against a telephone company and a jury verdict of more than $600 million against a railroad.<BR><BR><CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Representative Clients</H3></CENTER><P>AB SKF Group Companies; Anheuser-Busch Companies,  Inc.; Apple Computers,  Inc.; Ashland Oil,  Inc.; Carolina Power  & Light Company; Caterpillar Inc.; COMSAT Corporation; Dana Corporation; Duke Power Company; Encyclopaedia Britannica,  Inc.; Exxon Corporation; H.J. Heinz Company; Hershey Foods Corporation; Johnson  & Johnson; Litton Industries,  Inc.; The LTV Corporation; The Mead Corporation; Mobil Corporation; Nestl &#232; Companies; PepsiCo,  Inc.; The Pillsbury Company; The Prudential Insurance Co. of America; The Quaker Oats Company; Rockwell International Corporation; Schering-Plough Corporation; Shell Oil Company; Siemens AG (Germany); South Carolina Electric  & Gas Company; Timex Corporation; Uniroyal Chemical Co.; and Witco Corporation.<BR><BR><P>A partial listing of Howrey  & Simon lawyers,  each with 15-30 years of experience in handling complex business litigation,  follows:<BR><BR><UL><LI><B>Robert G. Abrams</B> Represents oil companies in complex litigation,  including class actions and multidistrict federal court cases.<BR><BR><LI><B>Ray S. Bolze</B> Represents several power companies and others in cases arising under business torts,  contracts,  RICO,  and antitrust.<BR><BR><LI><B>John DeQ. Briggs</B> Represents manufacturing concerns and insurance and reinsurance companies in business torts/contracts,  RICO matters,  asbestos property damage cases,  numerous veil piercing cases,  and antitrust matters. Chair,  Section of Antitrust Law,  ABA,  1995-1996.<BR><BR><LI><B>Richard T. Colman</B> Considerable experience in private treble-damage antitrust litigation,  including representation (with Robert Ruyak) of steel companies in successful litigation resulting in jury verdicts in excess of $600 million.<BR><BR><LI><B>Peter E. Moll</B> Represents a major brewer,  multinational food companies,  and others in business tort,  antitrust,  distributor termination,  and other commercial litigation.<BR><BR><LI><B>Keith E. Pugh,  Jr.</B> Represents manufacturers of food products,  oil companies,  and others in connection with business tort,  contract,  antitrust,  and advertising litigation throughout the United States.<BR><BR><LI><B>Robert F. Ruyak</B> Represents manufacturers of computers and components,  semiconductor devices,  major steel companies and others in business,  employment,  contract,  tort,  patent,  dealer/distribution,  and antitrust litigation.<BR><BR><LI><B>Ralph J. Savarese</B> Managing partner. Represents liquor and cereal companies,  and furniture and watch producers in cases involving contract disputes,  torts,  unfair trade practices,  antitrust,  and related issues.<BR><BR><LI><B>Terrence C. Sheehy</B> Represents multinational food manufacturers and a domestic brewer in connection with business litigation,  antitrust,  and regulatory matters involving competitors,  distributors,  and suppliers.<BR><BR><LI><B>Mark D. Wegener</B> Represents a telecommunications company,  a book publisher,  oil companies,  and a major manufacturer of air conditioners in business tort,  contract,  and antitrust litigation.<BR><BR><LI><B>Alan M. Wiseman</B> Represents a major forest products company and others in business tort,  contract,  antitrust,  and unfair competition litigation.<BR><BR><BR><BR><BR></UL></UL></BODY></HTML>
