<HEAD>
<TITLE>Hoyle,  Morris  & Kerr
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>Commercial Litigation</H2>
<H3>Hoyle,  Morris  & Kerr
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>Philadelphia:</B> One Liberty Place,  Suite 4900,  1650 Market Street, <BR>
Philadelphia,  PA 19103-7397<BR>
Tel 215-981-5700  <B>*</B>  Fax 215-851-0436<BR>
<BR>
45 lawyers  <B>*</B>  All lawyers practicing in commercial litigation<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>See this firm's profiles in the following other directories:<BR>
<UL><BR>
   <LI><A HREF="../95ATFolder/hoyle.html"> Antitrust</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95ENVFolder/hoyle.html"> Environmental</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95PLFolder/hoyle.html"> Product Liability</A>
</UL>

<P><BR>

<P>
<P><B>H</B>oyle,  Morris  & Kerr has both a local and national litigation practice that includes the broad spectrum of commercial litigation. Our clients range from small and mid-size businesses to Fortune 500 and multinational corporations in a wide variety of industries. Our litigation experience includes traditional commercial subjects such as securities,  antitrust,  breach of contract,  unfair competition,  and employment discrimination,  as well as the increasingly pervasive issues of toxic torts,  products liability,  environmental issues,  ERISA,  RICO,  and insurance coverage.<BR>
<P>We are especially well versed in complex litigation,  including class actions,  matters before the Judicial Panel on Multi-District Litigation,  and management of nationwide products liability litigation. Our practice in both simple and complex litigation includes experience at both trial and appellate levels,  including practice before the United States Supreme Court.<BR><P>Recognizing that most companies prefer to avoid litigation,  we provide our clients with counsel and advice concerning resolution of problems outside the judicial system. When major litigation is necessary,  however,  our firm has an excellent track record. The firm has obtained numerous favorable jury verdicts in cases tried in state or federal courts not only in Pennsylvania,  where the firm is located,  but also in numerous other courts. By way of example,  we have obtained a jury verdict covering $101 million of insurance following trial in the Southern District of New York; a defense verdict in a securities class action litigated in the Eastern District of Pennsylvania; and a defense verdict in a contract interpretation dispute. We also obtained defense verdicts in the first two asbestos property damage cases ever tried to juries and continued to earn a successful win-loss record in that litigation.<BR>
<BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>Lawrence T. Hoyle,  Jr.</B> Mr. Hoyle concentrates his practice in toxic tort,  environmental,  products liability,  antitrust,  insurance coverage,  securities and general commercial litigation. Deputy attorney general,  civil litigation division chief,  Department of Justice,  Commonwealth of Pennsylvania,  1971-1972; executive director,  Pennsylvania Crime Commission,  1972-1974. Fellow,  American Bar Foundation. Duke University,  B.A,  1960; University of Chicago,  J.D.,  1965. Admitted in Pennsylvania,  1976.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Alexander Kerr</B> Mr. Kerr's practice includes insurance coverage,  securities and RICO,  antitrust,  toxic torts,  environmental,  and general commercial litigation. Law clerk to Justice Samuel J. Roberts,  Pennsylvania Supreme Court,  1970-1971; deputy attorney general,  Pennsylvania Department of Justice,  1972-1974. Yale University,  B.A.,  1967; University of Pennsylvania,  J.D.,  1970; editor,  U<I>niversity of Pennsylvania Law Review</I>,  1968-1970. Admitted in Pennsylvania,  1971.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Bernard J. Smolens</B> Mr. Smolens's practice includes products liability and construction litigation. University of Pennsylvania,  B.A.,  1938; University of Pennsylvania,  L.L.B.,  1941; fellow,  American College of Trial Lawyers. Admitted in Pennsylvania,  1946.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Susan K. Herschel</B> Ms. Herschel's principal practice areas are products liability,  toxic tort,  and medical malpractice. Law clerk,  Judge Daniel H. Huyett III,  U.S. District Court for the Eastern District of Pennsylvania,  1974-1976. Syracuse University,  B.A.,  <I>summa cum laude</I>,  1964; Rutgers University-Camden School of Law,  J.D.,  <I>summa cum laude</I>,  1974. Admitted in Pennsylvania,  1974.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Arlene Fickler</B> Ms. Fickler's practice focuses on complex commercial litigation,  including products liability,  toxic tort,  and securities class actions. Member,  American Law Institute. University of Pennsylvania,  B.A.,  <I>cum laude</I>,  1971,  J.D.,  <I>cum laude</I>,  1974. Admitted in Pennsylvania,  1974,  and the District of Columbia,  1980.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Stephen J. Mathes</B> Mr. Mathes's practice is in general commercial litigation. Law clerk,  Honorable Arlin M. Adams,  U.S. Court of Appeals for the Third Circuit,  1970-1971. University of Pennsylvania,  B.A.,  1967,  J.D.,  1970. Admitted in New York,  1971,  and Pennsylvania,  1972.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Jill A. Douthett</B> Ms. Douthett represents corporate policyholders in insurance coverage litigation over underlying products liability,  toxic tort,  and environmental claims. Divisional deputy city solicitor,  commercial litigation,  City of Philadelphia,  1982-1984. London School of Economics; Tulane University,  B.A.,  1973; University of Virginia,  J.D.,  1976; Phi Beta Kappa. Admitted in Pennsylvania,  1976.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
