<B>Other offices:</B> Berlin,  Brussels,  London,  Tokyo<BR>
<B>Correspondent offices:</B> Mexico City (J &#242;uregui,  Navarrete,  Nader y Rojas,  S.C.)<BR>
<BR>
644 lawyers  <B>*</B>  180 lawyers in commercial litigation<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>See this firm's profiles in the following other directories:<BR>
<UL><BR>
   <LI><A HREF="../95ENVFolder/mayer.html"> Environmental</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95LABFolder/mayer.html"> Labor</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95PLFolder/mayer.html"> Product Liability</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95WCCFolder/mayer.html"> White Collar Crime</A>
</UL>

<P><BR>

<P>
<P><B>M</B>ayer,  Brown  & Platt,  founded in Chicago in 1881,  is one of the largest and most diverse firms in America,  with more than a third of the lawyers specializing in trial and appellate litigation.<BR><P>The lawyers at Mayer,  Brown  & Platt have extensive experience and expertise in all areas of litigation including class actions; commercial contract disputes; antitrust matters (both civil and criminal); securities litigation (civil,  criminal,  regulatory,  and arbitral); RICO litigation; hostile takeover litigation; contested tender offers and other challenges to corporate control; shareholder derivative suits; accountants' liability cases; bankruptcies,  workouts,  and corporate restructurings; white-collar criminal matters; lender liability; patent,  trademark,  and copyright infringement cases and other intellectual property matters; environmental; construction; insurance and reinsurance; entertainment; <I>qui tam</I> litigation; libel and defamation; energy; franchising and dealer relations; and business tort matters.<BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>Tyrone C. Fahner</B> (<I>Chicago; 312-701-7062; mbpdb!tcf@attmail.com</I>) is a former Attorney General of the State of Illinois and an assistant U.S. attorney,  with over 20 years of jury trial and appellate practice in state and federal courts. Ty specializes in business litigation including civil and criminal antitrust,  trade regulation,  product liability,  commodities,  securities,  white collar crime,  civil and criminal fraud,  and multidistrict litigation matters.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Richard J. Favretto</B> (<I>Washington; 202-778-0615; mbpdb!rjf@attmail.com</I>) is a veteran of 15 years' service in the Antitrust Division of the U.S. Department of Justice,  culminating in service as Deputy Assistant Attorney General and Acting Assistant Attorney General,  and more than a decade of private practice.<BR><BR>
<LI><B>Kenneth J. Jurek</B> (<I>Chicago; 312-701-7156; mbpdb!kjj@attmail.com</I>) joined Mayer,  Brown  & Platt after clerking for Judge Prentice H. Marshall in the Northern District of Illinois. Ken,  coauthor of the <I>Federal Litigation Guide</I>,  specializes in intellectual property and antitrust litigation and counseling.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>William H. Knull III</B> (<I>Houston; 713-221-1651; mbpdb!whk@attmail.com</I>) heads the litigation group in the Firm's Houston office. Bill has extensive experience in complex commercial and financial litigation in New York and Houston involving oil and gas,  banking,  franchising,  securities,  and corporate governance.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Hugh R. McCombs</B> (<I>Chicago; 312-701-7357; mbpdb!hrm@attmail.com</I>) has extensive experience in the trial and arbitration of construction claims involving developers,  design/builders,  architects,  civil engineers,  and construction managers. Rick has served as an arbitrator of contested construction and reinsurance claims and as a mediator of complex construction cases.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Alan N. Salpeter</B> (<I>Chicago; 312-701-7051; mbpdb!ans@attmail.com</I>) has tried more than 60 cases involving all types of commercial litigation. Many cases include securities fraud,  takeovers,  contract disputes,  and complex financings.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Neil M. Soltman</B> (<I>Los Angeles; 213-229-9516; mbpdb!nms@attmail.com</I>) has 20 years of experience litigating disputes in both federal and state courts throughout California. Neil has substantial experience in intellectual property and unfair competition; antitrust,  trade,  and franchise disputes; insurance and reinsurance claims; and environmental matters.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Steven Wolowitz</B> (<I>New York; 212-506-2535; mbpdb!svw@attmail.com</I>) is head of the litigation group in the Firm's New York office and is co-chair of the Firm's securities litigation group. Steve specializes in business litigation including securities,  banking,  insurance,  employment and intellectual property cases.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Herbert L. Zarov</B> (<I>Chicago; 312-701-7317; mbpdb!hlz@attmail.com</I>) specializes in securities,  accountants' liability,  and mass tort litigation. Herb has most recently served as national counsel for The Dow Chemical Company in the federal multidistrict breast implant product liability litigation.<BR>
<BR>
