<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>Commercial Litigation</H2>
<H3>Robins,  Kaplan,  Miller & Ciresi
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>Minneapolis:</B> 2800 LaSalle Plaza,  800 LaSalle Avenue,  Minneapolis,  MN 55402<BR>
Tel 612-349-8500  <B>*</B>  Fax 612-339-4181<BR>
<B>Other offices: </B>Atlanta,  Boston,  Chicago,  Costa Mesa (California), <BR>
Los Angeles,  San Francisco,  St. Paul,  Washington,  D.C.<BR>
<BR>
230 lawyers in the firm  <B>*</B>  92 lawyers practicing in business litigation<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>See this firm's profile in the following other directory:<BR>
<UL><BR>
   <LI><A HREF="../95IPFolder/robins.html"> Intellectual Property</A>
</UL>

<P>
<P>
<P><B>R</B>obins,  Kaplan,  Miller  & Ciresi is a national litigation and business practice firm with offices in nine major metropolitan areas throughout the country.
<P>
<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>The Business Litigation Group</H3></CENTER>

<BR><BR>
<P>The business litigation group prosecutes and defends matters on all aspects of business law including: <BR>
<BR><UL><LI>antitrust<LI>cable communications<LI>construction<LI>contracts<LI>dealer terminations<LI>employment<LI>franchising<LI>intellectual property<LI>lender liability<LI>real estate<LI>RICO<LI>securities<LI>trade secrets<LI>unfair competition<BR></UL>
<BR><P>This litigation is on behalf of a diverse group of clients including Fortune 100 companies,  lending institutions,  property insurers,  the Big Six accounting firms,  and foreign,  state,  and municipal governments.<BR>
<BR><P>Our attorneys take a client-centered approach to litigation matters,  working closely with the client to determine the most productive and cost-effective strategies.<BR>
<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Experience and Clients</H3></CENTER>

<BR><BR>
<P>The firm's clients include 3M,  Alliant Techsystems Inc.,  American Business Information,  Babcock  & WiLCox,  Best Buy Co.,  Inc.,  Burlington Northern Railroad,  Continental Cablevision,  Cox Communications,  The Crosby Group,  Ecolab,  General Mills,  Graco,  Harris Waste Management Group,  Honeywell Inc.,  Hormel,  ITT Consumer Financial Corp.,  KBLCOM Inc.,  KPMG Peat Marwick,  Kaiser Aluminum  & Chemical Corporation,  NordicTrack,  Norwest Bank Minnesota,  NuSkin International,  Pitney-Bowes,  Phillips Beverage Company,  Polaris Industries,  The Providence Journal Company,  Toro Company,  TCF Bank,  TCI,  Time Warner,  Universal Cooperatives,  UNOCAL,  Waldorf Corporation,  and W.R. Grace  & Company.<BR><P>Cases handled for these clients include such diverse claims as:<BR>
<BR<UL><LI> Patent,  trademark,  and copyright infringement;
<LI> Antitrust,  dealer terminations,  and RICO;
<LI> Breach of contract and fraud arising out of M &A transactions;
<LI> Securities fraud; and
<LI> Class action employment litigation.
</UL><BR>
<BR><P>Our litigation group includes the following attorneys:<BR>
<BR><UL>
<LI><B>Michael V. Ciresi</B> (<I>Minneapolis; 612-349-8500</I>) Mr. Ciresi is chairman of the firm's executive board. His practice is focused on trial work and consulting in the areas of business litigation,  product liability,  intellectual property,  and commercial litigation in national and international arenas. He has twice been identified by the <I>National Law Journal</I> as one of the top ten trial lawyers in the United States,  and has been recognized in <I>The Best Lawyers in America</I> since 1989.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Thomas J. Gallo</B> (<I>Atlanta; 404-233-1114</I>) Mr. Gallo's practice focuses on business litigation,  including breach of contract,  securities fraud,  shareholders' rights,  and employment-related claims. He has served as counsel in a number of class actions representing both plaintiffs and defendants. <BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Elliot S. Kaplan</B> (<I>Minneapolis; 612-349-8500</I>) Mr. Kaplan is a member of the firm's executive board. His practice is focused on trial work and consulting in the areas of antitrust,  trade regulation,  intellectual property,  and securities matters. He has tried copyright,  antitrust,  trademark,  securities,  and unfair trade practice cases in several federal and state courts. He is a frequent lecturer on antitrust matters. He has been recognized in <I>The Best Lawyers in America</I> since 1989.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>William H. Manning</B> (<I>Minneapolis; 612-349-8500</I>) Mr. Manning has tried to conclusion or settled more than 300 lawsuits over the past 15 years. He has been lead counsel in numerous complex product liability cases and commercial cases that have been tried in various state and federal jurisdictions. He is a frequent lecturer on all aspects of the trial process.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>J. Jonathan Schraub</B> (<I>Washington; 202-775-0725</I>) Mr. Schraub's practice has included the defense of directors,  officers,  and outside counsel of failed thrifts in litigation brought by the FDIC and RTC. In addition to trial and appellate work,  he handles a wide spectrum of employment law issues.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Ernest I. Reveal</B> (<I>Costa Mesa; 714-434-3400</I>) Mr. Reveal has represented plaintiffs and defendants in complex litigation involving antitrust,  employment,  securities,  and intellectual property law. He has represented cable operators and broadcasters in litigation in federal and state courts involving issues of antitrust,  franchises,  civil rights,  and property taxation.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
</UL><BR>


