<P>
<P>
<P><B>T</B>he lawyers in the litigation practice at Seyfarth,  Shaw,  Fairweather  & Geraldson represent clients in state and federal courts in the United States,  including appellate matters before the U.S. Supreme Court,  in certain foreign forums,  and in domestic and international arbitration proceedings.
<P><BR><P>Our litigation experience includes trial and appellate representation in virtually every area of commercial and civil litigation,  including business contract disputes,  securities and commodities law,  corporations and partnerships,  insurance and reinsurance coverage and claims disputes,  white collar crime,  intellectual property,  bankruptcy and creditors' rights,  environmental,  safety and health law,  product liability,  general torts and workers' compensation,  real estate,  construction law,  government contracts,  antitrust law and unfair competition,  professional malpractice,  trust and probate,  administrative law,  tax,  admiralty and maritime law,  and appellate practice.<BR><P>The success of our representation is dependent both on the results we achieve and the overall satisfaction of our clients. To ensure that both of these goals are accomplished,  our approach to dispute resolution includes thoroughly preparing cases for trial; promptly reporting all litigation developments; adopting competitive rates; monitoring expenses carefully throughout the litigation process; tailoring case preparation to match case value; trying cases aggressively; formulating fresh approaches to persistent problems; and utilizing the national resources of the Firm to achieve economic and successful results.<BR>
<BR><P>Though the Firm believes in vigorous advocacy on behalf of our clients,  we have found in recent years that mediation,  arbitration,  and other forms of alternative dispute resolution have proved to be effective and economical in resolving certain disputes for our clients. Our attorneys have been extensively involved in mediations,  arbitrations,  summary trials,  and minitrials encompassing most substantive areas of civil litigation. Our lawyers have also acted as mediators and arbitrators.<BR>
<BR><P>Seyfarth Shaw is also a subscriber to the policies of the Center for Public Resources,  a not-for-profit organization that fosters alternative dispute resolution. A subscribing firm agrees to give serious consideration to alternative dispute resolution; to assure clients that its attorneys are knowledgeable about ADR; and,  where appropriate,  to discuss ADR with clients.<BR>
<BR><P>Our litigation partners include:<BR>
<BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>Alan L. Unikel</B> (<I>Chicago</I>) is the head of the Litigation group. He practices intellectual property law and product liability litigation.<BR>
<BR>
