<BR>
<LI><B>Raymond J. Kelly</B> (<I>Chicago</I>) has a broad range of litigation experience,  including construction and general commercial litigation,  product liability,  tort and personal injury,  employment,  and health care litigation.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Thomas E. Wilson</B> (<I>Washington</I>) practices in the areas of white collar criminal litigation and complex civil and criminal matters. He successfully represented a CIA station chief in the Iran-Contra affair.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Nathaniel H. Akerman</B> (<I>New York</I>) practices in complex civil business litigation RICO,  antitrust,  fraud,  and libel and white collar criminal litigation. He also conducts internal investigations for corporate clients.<BR>
<BR>
