<P>
<P>
<P><B>S</B>mith Helms Mulliss  & Moore,  L.L.P. was created in 1986 by the merger of two leading North Carolina law firms with roots going back to 1919. With offices in North Carolina's three major metropolitan areas,  the firm maintains a statewide presence and also provides its clients with regional and national representation. The firm's practice groups provide a full range of legal services in litigation and nonlitigation specialties.
<P>
<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Commercial Litigation Practice</H3></CENTER>

<P>Our firm and its predecessors have for many years represented and counseled clients in a wide variety of complex commercial litigation cases,  which is our single largest practice area. We handle all types of commercial disputes,  including antitrust and unfair trade practices,  banking and financial services,  bankruptcy,  construction,  distributor and franchise terminations,  environmental,  intellectual property,  labor and employment relations (management),  media law,  products liability and toxic torts,  securities and corporate matters,  transactional and investment disputes,  white collar crime,  and zoning and condemnation matters. The firm's attorneys also have substantial experience in alternative dispute resolution methods and procedures.<BR><P>Smith Helms Mulliss  & Moore maintains an active quality management program,  and the firm is dedicated to providing the highest value legal services to meet our clients' litigation and business objectives. We work actively with our clients to articulate goals,  plan litigation tactics,  and develop cost and budgetary outlines.<BR>
<BR><P>The firm's statewide presence allows great flexibility in handling litigation in North Carolina for clients who may be headquartered across the country. Also,  we provide national and regional litigation coordination for clients in a number of fields. A representative sample of our commercial clients includes: American  & Efird,  Inc.; Becton Dickinson and Co.; Cone Mills Corp.; General Motors,  Inc.; Jefferson-Pilot Corp.; Kayser Roth Hosiery,  Inc.; Landmark Communications,  Inc.; Miller Brewing Co.; NationsBank Corp.; Roche Biomedical Laboratories,  Inc.; Royal Insurance Co.,  Inc.; and Security Pacific Housing Services,  Inc.<BR>
<BR><P>Some of the firm's litigation partners who have a broad expertise in commercial litigation matters,  and who may be contacted with any representational inquiry,  are listed below.<BR>
<BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>E. Osborne Ayscue,  Jr.</B> (<I>Charlotte; 704-343-2058</I>) Mr. Ayscue has acted as lead counsel in a wide variety of commercial litigation cases,  including antitrust,  media law,  banking,  securities,  trade regulation,  and intellectual property. University of North Carolina,  J.D.,  1960.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Peter J. Covington</B> (<I>Charlotte; 704-343-2058</I>) Mr. Covington has litigated numerous corporate and securities-related claims,  including shareholder derivative actions,  business break-ups and departing employee disputes,  and stock valuation and brokerage disputes. Tulane University,  J.D.,  1980.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>J. Donald Cowan,  Jr.</B> (<I>Greensboro; 910-378-5329</I>) Mr. Cowan has broad commercial litigation experience,  including securities claims,  intellectual property disputes,  insurance coverage and defense,  unfair trade,  products liability,  and banking and transactional disputes. Wake Forest University,  J.D.,  1968.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Benjamin F. Davis,  Jr.</B> (<I>Greensboro; 910-378-5352</I>) Mr. Davis concentrates in litigation involving financial institutions and bankruptcy matters,  including lender liability,  foreclosure,  project workouts,  and contract disputes. Harvard University,  J.D.,  1971.<BR>
