<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>Commercial Litigation</H2>
<H3>Steel Hector  & Davis
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>Miami:</B> 200 South Biscayne Boulevard,  Miami,  FL 33131-2398<BR>
Tel 305-577-7000  <B>*</B>  Fax 305-577-7001<BR>
<B>Other offices:</B> Key West,  London,  Tallahassee,  West Palm Beach<BR>
<BR>
172 lawyers  <B>*</B>  90 lawyers in commercial litigation<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>
<P><BR>

<P>
<P><B>W</B>e founded our practice in 1925 to help Henry Flagler pioneer his railroad to the alligator-infested swamp that was Miami. True to that tradition,  Steel Hector  & Davis today is an innovative firm for major industries that see Florida as their destination,  home,  or gateway.<BR><P>Because our primary practice area always has been complex commercial litigation,  Steel Hector  & Davis is one of the few Florida firms with the size and the experience to handle major matters. One of our largest clients is Florida Power  & Light Co.,  the successor to Flagler's original Miami utility company.<BR><P>Our recent litigation has included such diverse matters as the prosecution of massive uranium fuel claims,  the defense of multistate employee-benefit disputes with the federal government involving billions of dollars,  representation of a foreign automobile importer in a contest arising from its acquisition of a national car rental agency,  and the defense of a television station in one of the most aggressively prosecuted libel cases in Florida history.<BR>
<BR><P>Our areas of litigation practice include antitrust,  securities,  banking,  mergers and acquisitions,  employment relations and employment discrimination,  ERISA,  communications,  trademark and unfair competition,  Racketeer Influenced and Corrupt Organizations Act (RICO),  contracts,  lender liability,  environmental,  state and local taxation,  construction,  eminent domain,  defamation,  and real estate.<BR>
<BR><P>Our litigators also have been trained to explore all alternatives to litigation. A number have received special training sessions through the Harvard Negotiation Workshop and other leading mediation and arbitration programs.<BR>
<BR><P>Representative clients: FPL Group; Florida Power  & Light Co.; American Express Company; American Media; The Bank of New York; CBS Inc.; Capital Cities/ABC,  Inc.,  Central Romana Development Corp.,  Inc.; Citibank of Florida; Collier Enterprises; OrNda Healthcorp; Disney Development Company; FAIC Securities,  Inc.; Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation; Federal Reserve Bank of Atlanta; First Union Bank of Florida; Flo-Sun Incorporated; General Electric Real Estate Equities,  Inc.,  Hyundai Heavy Industries; John Hancock Mutual Life Insurance Co.; Lucille P. Markey Charitable Trust; Merrill Lynch Hubbard,  Inc.; Middle South Utilities,  Inc.; Mitsubishi Motor Sales of America,  Inc.; Morgan Guaranty Trust Co.; NCNB National Bank of Florida; Palm Beach Newspapers,  Inc.; Premier Resorts and Hotels; Provident Life and Accident Insurance Co.; State Street Bank  & Trust Co.; SunHealth Enterprises; Trafalgar Developers of Florida,  Inc.; Turner Broadcasting System; University of Miami; United Teachers of Dade; United Technologies Corp.<BR>
<BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>Joseph P. Klock,  Jr.</B> is chairman and managing partner of our firm and chairman of our international group. His practice includes both corporate and litigation matters. He has worked closely with foreign investors in the Dominican Republic and has served as chairman of the American Bar Association's Caribbean Law Committee.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Alvin B. Davis</B> is chairman of our Litigation Department. He has served as lead trial counsel for major financial institutions and utilities in complex state and federal litigation throughout the country.<BR>
