<P><BR>

<P>
<P><B>V</B>inson  & Elkins L.L.P. is one of the world's largest international law firms,  representing clients in almost all areas of law. Since 1917,  the firm has worked with clients to solve all types of commercial disputes. We have represented clients before state and federal trial and appellate courts as well as in a variety of adversary proceedings before such fora as the SEC,  FTC,  FERC,  Provider Reimbursement Review Board,  state administrative boards,  arbitration panels,  and grand juries. We also conduct various types of investigations of incidents that ultimately may involve litigation. Over 160 Firm attorneys have litigation practices in such areas as admiralty/special risk insurance,  antitrust,  appeals,  aviation,  banking,  bankruptcy,  condemnation,  construction,  contract,  Texas Deceptive Trade Practices Act (DTPA),  environmental,  fiduciary duty,  fraud,  governmental powers/public law,  health law,  insurance coverage,  lender liability,  natural resources,  officer and director liability,  oil and gas,  personal injury,  premises liability,  products liability,  professional malpractice (accounting,  legal,  architechtural,  and engineering,  etc.),  corporate and securities,  tax,  title- and land-related disputes,  and warranty claims.<BR><P>Our experience includes resolving client disputes through negotiation,  mediation,  arbitration,  trial,  appeal,  and settlement in state and federal courts nationwide. Our trial attorneys are experienced in representing clients in international proceedings,  including arbitration and mediation. In a 1993 survey of law firms,  Vinson  & Elkins was ranked fourth nationally in arbitration and litigation. We have acted as lead counsel in mass tort and class-action litigation relating to property damage and personal injury claims. We have experience with litigation growing out of bank closings and federal banking regulation. We have handled a wide array of improper business practice claims,  including suits brought under state consumer protection,  DTPA,  and the federal RICO statutes. We are experienced in dealing with multiple plaintiff and multiple defendant cases. We have the resources and experience to handle cases that involve hundreds of thousands of claimants and are litigated in fora nationwide.<BR><BR><UL><LI><B>Scott J. Atlas</B> (<I>Houston; 713-758-2024</I>) practices primarily in business litigation and appeals in federal and state court,  including antitrust,  securities,  corporate law,  contracts,  business torts,  DTPA,  lender liability,  fraud,  RICO,  and general matters.<BR>
