<P>
<P><B>V</B>orys,  Sater,  Seymour and Pease offers national and international representation in all areas of law including antitrust,  bankruptcy,  commercial,  corporate,  energy,  government contracting,  health care,  insurance,  intellectual property,  international,  labor,  legislation,  litigation,  public utilities,  real estate,  and white collar defense.
<P>
<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Business and Commercial Litigation</H3></CENTER>

<P>Vorys,  Sater handles all types of litigation rising out of complex business and commercial disputes. We have an extensive trial and appellate practice in the federal and state court systems. Eight of our litigators are fellows of the American College of Trial Lawyers and several are listed in <I>The Best Lawyers in America</I>. Our litigation practice includes securities litigation,  professional malpractice,  intellectual property litigation,  lender liability,  environmental litigation,  product liability,  white collar,  complex medical matters,  toxic tort actions,  antitrust,  and other matters.<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Experience and Clients</H3></CENTER>

<P>Experience includes: representing companies involved in complex acquisitions,  divestitures,  and mergers; representing national accounting firms and other professional service firms in malpractice litigation; representing clients in complex securities litigation; serving as local counsel for Citibank in the Campeau Corporation bankruptcy; successfully representing gas producers in a $56 million class action; representing A. Bartlett Giamatti in Pete Rose's suit against the former commissioner of baseball; successfully representing a financial institution in precedent-setting U.S. Supreme Court litigation regarding fiduciary liability; serving as counsel for Honda of America Manufacturing,  Inc. on a wide variety of litigation matters; and handling complex litigation matters for numerous financial institutions,  including Bank One,  N.A.<BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>John C. Elam</B> (<I>Columbus; 614-464-6271</I>) Over 40 years' experience in federal,  state,  and appellate court complex litigation,  takeovers,  antitrust,  and class action cases. Fellow of the American College of Trial Lawyers. Permanent delegate to the Sixth Circuit Judicial Conference. University of Michigan,  J.D.,  with distinction,  1949. Admitted in all Ohio state and federal courts,  U.S. Court of Appeals for the District of Columbia,  and the U.S. Supreme Court.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Duke W. Thomas</B> (<I>Columbus; 614-464-6263</I>) Extensive experience with over 30 years in civil litigation including class actions,  professional malpractice,  securities,  construction disputes,  and product liability in state and federal courts. Fellow of the American College of Trial Lawyers. The Ohio State University,  J.D.,  1964. Admitted in Ohio.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Thomas M. Taggart</B> (<I>Columbus; 614-464-6252</I>) More than 25 years' experience in complex medical litigation,  professional malpractice litigation,  construction litigation,  and corporate mergers and acquisitions. Harvard University,  LL.B.,  1965. Admitted in Ohio.<BR>
