<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Washington</H3></CENTER>

<BR><BR><UL><LI><B>Roger E. Zuckerman</B> has litigated contractual disputes,  major forfeitures,  and cases involving securities fraud claims,  banking and commercial lending. He is a former assistant U.S. attorney and a fellow of the American College of Trial Lawyers.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Mark W. Foster</B> has litigated disputes involving real estate financing,  environmental hazards,  lender liability,  corporate ownership and control,  and government contracts. He is experienced in alternative dispute resolution,  as an advocate and as a mediator/arbitrator.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Roger C. Spaeder</B> is a former assistant U.S. attorney who has conducted antitrust,  business tort,  fraud,  securities,  trademark,  and fiduciary breach litigation.<BR><BR>
<LI><B>William W. Taylor III</B> represents clients in a wide range of business controversies and government investigations,  involving securities,  fraud and RICO,  contract disputes,  antitrust,  unfair trade practices,  and partnership dissolutions. Mr. Taylor is a fellow in the American College of Trial Lawyers.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Peter R. Kolker</B> represents business clients in trials,  arbitrations,  and mediations,  with an emphasis on real estate and commercial leasing controversies,  banking and lender liability litigation,  and commercial contractual disputes.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Stephen H. Glickman</B> is ZSGT &K's managing partner. He represents business executives and other professionals in fiduciary breach and fraud litigation.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Nelson C. Cohen</B> represents lenders,  lessors,  secured parties and borrowers in contract disputes and other commercial litigation,  and has extensive experience in all phases of bankruptcy litigation.<BR>
