<TITLE>Hogan  & Hartson L.L.P.
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>Corporate Securities</H2>
<H3>Hogan  & Hartson L.L.P.
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>Washington:</B> 555 Thirteenth Street,  N.W.,  Washington,  DC 20004<BR>
Tel 202-637-5600  <B>*</B>  Fax 202-637-5910<BR>
<B>Other offices:</B> Brussels,  London,  Moscow,  Paris (affiliated office),  Prague,  Warsaw,  Baltimore,  Bethesda (Maryland),  Colorado Springs,  Denver,  McLean (Virginia)<BR>
<BR>
400 lawyers  <B>*</B>  160 lawyers practicing in the corporate finance and securities areas<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>See this firm's profile in the following other directory:<BR>
<UL><BR>
   <LI><A HREF="../95ENVFolder/hogan.html"> Environmental</A>
</UL>

<P><BR>

<P>
<P><B>H</B>ogan  & Hartson advises clients with respect to single-country and international mergers,  acquisitions,  and joint ventures; public and private offerings of equity and debt securities; public finance; recapitalizations; REITs; leveraged management buyouts; `going private' transactions; general issues of securities law compliance; financings; privatizations; project financings; investments; franchising; licensing; takeovers and takeover defenses; and proxy contests.
<P><BR><P>Hogan  & Hartson has been among the most active firms in the United States in representing issuers and underwriters in public offerings of equity securities. The firm also has been involved in a number of complex public and private offerings of debt securities,  including investment grade,  high-yield,  and asset-backed debt securities. Much of this financing work has been in the real estate,  communications,  healthcare/medical technology,  and information technology areas.<BR><P>Hogan  & Hartson's lawyers are experienced in virtually every form of single-country and international credit transaction,  having structured and implemented numerous large-scale financings,  including financings underwritten on the basis of,  and secured by,  the cash flows from the transaction or project,  and transactions involving numerous layers of debt and equity. The firm's public/project finance practice has focused in particular on large,  complex public and private financings of major infrastructure projects. Our lawyers have been centrally involved in financing airports,  toll roads,  convention center and stadium developments,  telecommunications systems,  public and private power projects,  highway programs,  prison construction,  and water and wastewater projects.<BR>
<BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>Helen Atkeson</B> handles asset-backed taxable debt and other structured financings,  significant restructurings,  and revenue-based obligations.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Raymond J. Batla,  Jr. </B>advises clients,  particularly in the energy industry,  on a wide range of business transactions,  including mergers and acquisitions,  corporate finance,  and international joint ventures.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>David Bonser</B> represents issuers and underwriters in connection with public and private offerings of both debt and equity securities.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Rebecca Bronson</B> serves as counsel to government issuers of debt to finance large capital projects,  and as counsel to investment and commercial banks participating in public/project financings.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Michael Cheroutes</B> specializes in public/project finance law,  with particular focus on major infrastructure construction and privatization projects.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Claudette Christian</B> handles primarily international transactions,  including stock acquisitions and divestitures,  asset acquisitions,  project finance,  mergers,  leveraged buyouts,  banking transactions,  corporate restructurings,  and joint ventures.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Alan Dye</B> represents issuers and underwriters in connection with public and private offerings of both debt and equity securities.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Bruce GiLChrist</B> advises underwriters and issuers on public and private equity and debt financings,  and handles mergers and acquisitions,  restructurings,  and recapitalizations.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Warren Gorrell</B> advises underwriters and issuers on public and private equity and debt financings,  including REITs,  and handles mergers and acquisitions,  restructurings,  and recapitalizations.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Anthony Harrington</B> handles venture capital and other financings,  acquisitions,  mergers,  and joint ventures.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Robert Jeffers</B> handles public and private offerings,  foreign and domestic mergers,  acquisitions,  and joint ventures; recapitalizations; tender offers; proxy contests; and investment company and investment adviser matters.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Duncan Klinedinst</B> practices in the corporate area with particular emphasis in international aircraft financing transactions.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Mark Mazo</B> handles U.S. and international business transactions,  including acquisitions,  equity and debt financings,  joint ventures,  and technology commercialization.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Peter Romeo</B> counsels clients on securities law matters and is an authority on the insider trading laws.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>James Rosenhauer</B> advises clients concerning mergers,  stock and asset acquisitions (including leveraged buyouts),  securities issuances,  international joint ventures and licensing,  international finance,  and project finance.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Michael Silver</B> represents underwriters and issuers on public and private securities offerings,  and handles mergers and acquisitions,  corporate organization and governance issues,  and structured finance transactions.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Robert Waldman</B> handles mergers,  acquisitions,  public and nonpublic offerings,  financings,  stock accumulations,  proxy contests,  and change-in-control matters.<BR>
