<P>
<P>
<P><B>L</B>owenstein Sandler is among the largest general corporate practice firms in New Jersey. In our corporate practice,  we provide advice to a variety of clients,  ranging from privately owned family businesses to multinational public corporations. Our areas of expertise include the organization of new businesses,  business planning,  mergers and acquisitions,  securities,  corporate reorganizations,  licensing,  secured and unsecured lending,  leveraged buyouts,  franchising,  employment law,  environmental law,  real estate,  health care,  bankruptcy,  and general corporate matters. Furthermore,  we work closely with our Tax Department to assure tax-efficient solutions to corporate issues.
<P><BR><P>Naturally,  our corporate practice varies from client to client. In many cases,  we serve as general counsel or as outside general counsel for our corporate clients. However,  we also frequently serve as special New Jersey counsel with respect to mergers and acquisitions and other corporate reorganizations centered outside of New Jersey but with a nexus to our state. Overall,  we strive to provide high-quality,  practical legal advice and business counseling on a cost-efficient and timely basis.<BR>
<UL><BR>
