<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>Corporate Securities</H2>
<H3>Winston  & Strawn
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>Chicago:</B> 35 West Wacker Drive,  Chicago,  IL 60601<BR>
Tel 312-558-5600  <B>*</B>  Fax 312-558-5700  <B>*</B>  E-mail: <A HREF="mailto:info@winston.com">info@winston.com</A><BR>
<B>Other offices:</B> New York,  Washington,  D.C.,  Geneva,  Paris,  Riyadh<BR>
<BR>
465 lawyers  <B>*</B>  110 lawyers in corporate securities and finance<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>See this firm's profiles in the following other directories:<BR>
<UL><BR>
   <LI><A HREF="../95CLFolder/winston.html"> Commercial Litigation</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95LABFolder/winston.html"> Labor</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95PLFolder/winston.html"> Product Liability</A>
</UL>

<P><BR>

<P>
<P><B>W</B>inston  & Strawn provides assistance in virtually every major legal discipline to a wide range of clients throughout the United States and abroad.
<P><UL><BR<
<BR><P><I><LI> Mergers and Acquisitions.</I> The firm represents companies and banks in public and private acquisitions,  leveraged buyouts,  divestitures,  joint ventures,  and proxy contests. We recently have been involved in several significant acquisitions,  including Luxottica Group S.p.A.'s acquisition of The United States Shoe Corporation,  Lear Seating Corporation's acquisition of Automotive Industries,  and National Westminster Bancorp's acquisition of Citizens First Bancorp,  Inc. <BR><BR><P><I><LI> Securities.</I> Our securities attorneys handle initial public offerings and other underwritings of equity and debt,  and represent institutional investors in the purchase of securities and equity hybrids. We assist domestic and foreign issuers,  placement agents,  and underwriters.<BR>
<BR><P><I><LI> Commercial Lending.</I> Our commercial lending attorneys serve as counsel to lenders providing senior secured and unsecured loans,  and draft and negotiate a complete range of collateral and security documents. <BR>
<BR><P><I><LI> Leveraged Leasing. </I>The firm provides assistance with a wide variety of tax-beneficial lease transactions involving equipment and facilities,  as well as large integrated facilities,  including nuclear generating facilities. <BR>
<BR><P><I><LI> Project Finance. </I>Winston  & Strawn's project finance experience includes pure project (non-recourse) financing,  projects which convert to non-recourse financing,  and leveraged leases. Our experience spans large-scale projects for energy production,  solid waste disposal,  resource recovery,  oil and gas pipelines,  and natural resource development and the privatization of government-owned facilities.<BR>
<BR><P><I><LI> Other Services.</I> In addition to the areas outlined above,  the firm has substantial experience in bank regulatory matters,  asset securitization,  financial restructuring,  and general corporate matters. <BR>
<BR></UL>
<LI><B>Paul B. Abramson</B> is an attorney and a registered professional engineer whose practice is extremely broad,  representing developers,  lenders,  investors,  and others in structuring project finance deals.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Daniel C. Bird,  Jr.</B> focuses on asset securitizations,  has developed unique financing structures,  and also has extensive experience in SEC-registered offerings of securities,  development and offering of corporate and municipal securities,  and the securitization of equipment leases. <BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>David G. Crumbaugh</B>'s practice is focused on commercial lending and leveraged acquisitions. He has structured and negotiated leveraged buyout transactions or refinancings as lenders' counsel or borrowers' counsel,  involving secured loans in asset-based or cash flow transactions.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Robert W. Ericson</B>,  the New York office managing partner,  is experienced in securities,  mergers,  and acquisitions. His practice has been focused on representing issuers and underwriters,  and financial institutions in mergers and acquisitions.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Jonathan Goldstein</B> has represented lenders,  including NatWest,  Barclays Bank,  and FINOVA Capital Corporation,  in financing more than 50 media acquisitions. He also represents Italy's Luxottica Group S.p.A.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Gary A. Goodman</B> represents clients in a variety of industries,  concentrating on lender representation in matters ranging from leveraged buyouts to insolvency. <BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Arnie Gough</B> represents borrowers and lenders in connection with multi-bank secured financing. He also has counseled First Chicago Leasing,  National Westminster Bank USA,  and Westinghouse Credit Corporation.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Gregory S. Murray</B> represents domestic and non-U.S. banks and diversified financial service companies in commercial lending and regulatory matters,  including representing lenders in various senior and subordinated debt facilities.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Bruce A. Toth</B> is the Corporate Department head,  focusing his practice in bank financing and securities. He participated in a number of significant corporate restructurings,  including West Point-Pepperell,  New World Television,  and GHI.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Joseph A. Walsh,  Jr.</B> concentrates his practice in mergers and acquisitions,  and the formation of joint ventures,  partnerships,  and other business entities.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Robert A. Wall</B> has participated in more than 60 publicly disclosed mergers and acquisitions and has done extensive work in the corporate and securities area.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Kenneth Willig</B> handles secured lending transactions and leveraged leases,  and represents financial institutions in the acquisition of equity interests and the placement of debt in connection with the project financing of alternative energy projects.<BR>
