<TITLE>Bondurant,  Mixson & Elmore
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>Environmental</H2>
<H3>Bondurant,  Mixson & Elmore
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>Atlanta:</B> 1201 West Peachtree Street,  N.W.,  3900 One Atlantic Center,  Atlanta,  GA 30309<BR>
Tel 404-881-4100  <B>*</B>  Fax 404-881-4111<BR>
<BR>
18 lawyers  <B>*</B>  4 lawyers practicing in environmental litigation<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>See this firm's profiles in the following other directories:<BR>
<UL><BR>
   <LI><A HREF="../95ATFolder/bondurant.html"> Antitrust</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95CLFolder/bondurant.html"> Commercial Litigation</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95WCCFolder/bondurant.html"> White Collar Crime</A>
</UL>

<P>
<P>
<P><B>B</B>ondurant,  Mixson  & Elmore (BME) practices complex civil and white collar criminal litigation.
<P>
<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Environmental Experience and Clients</H3></CENTER>

<P>BME represents plaintiffs and defendants before state and federal trial and appellate courts,  administrative agencies and grand juries throughout the United States,  and in alternative forms of dispute resolution such as mediation,  arbitration,  and proceedings before special masters.<BR><P>BME attorneys are experienced in a broad range of litigation involving environmental law. BME has represented insurance companies in environmental coverage disputes,  chemical manufacturers in toxic tort actions,  plaintiffs and defendants in underground storage tank litigation,  waste disposal companies in suits involving proper disposal of waste,  environmental remediation companies in suits against disposal companies,  government contractors in suits against the United States,  and landowners in suits for migration of contaminants,  evaluation of contaminated realty and lending practices involving contaminated realty.<BR>
<BR><P>BME has experience with litigation involving novel legal issues,  complex or highly technical fact issues,  multiple parties,  class actions,  multidistrict litigation,  and interrelated matters pending before different tribunals. The firm is also experienced in handling emergency proceedings that present significant time constraints,  including injunctions and receiverships.<BR>
<BR><P>The firm's attorneys combine excellent academic credentials with practical experience. For example,  every BME attorney has served as a law review editor or federal law clerk,  or both. Every BME attorney has practiced as a litigator from the inception of his or her career and understands the need to achieve the client's specific litigation objectives in the most efficient manner possible. This experience and flexibility has enabled BME to successfully represent a broad range of clients,  from multinational corporations and partnerships to individuals and small corporations.<BR>
<BR><P>The firm's representative environmental litigation clients include Fina Oil  & Chemical Co.,  Conoco,  Inc.,  The Travelers Indemnity Co.,  Sanifill,  Inc.,  and Velsicol Chemical Corporation.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>M. Jerome Elmore</B> has a broad range of experience in business litigation,  with particular emphasis on environmental litigation. University of Virginia,  B.A.,  high honors,  1970; Emory University,  J.D.,  1976; member,  editorial board,  <I>Emory Law Journal</I>. Admitted in Georgia and Florida.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>John E. Floyd</B> has experience in a broad range of complex litigation,  including bankruptcy,  lender liability,  and business torts,  with particular emphasis on RICO litigation. Law clerk to Judge William C. O'Kelley,  U.S. District Court for the Northern District of Georgia. Brown University,  B.A.,  with honors,  1980; Emory University,  J.D.,  1983; notes and comments editor,  <I>Emory Law Journal</I>.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Michael B. Terry</B> has experience in a broad range of litigation involving environmental issues,  including insurance coverage,  RCRA and CERCLA,  RICO,  toxic torts,  and underground storage tanks. Member,  editorial board,  <I>Georgia Journal of International and Comparative Law</I>. University of Georgia,  B.A.,  <I>magna cum laude</I>,  1982,  J.D.,  <I>magna cum laude</I>,  1987; Order of the Coif,  Order of Barristers.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
