<BR>
148 lawyers  <B>*</B>  9 lawyers in environmental law and litigation<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>
<P><BR>

<P>
<P><B>C</B>alfee,  Halter  & Griswold's environmental attorneys represent a range of publicly- and privately-held corporations,  municipalities,  other governmental entities and trade associations. Our clients are engaged in a variety of businesses and activities that regularly confront environmental regulation,  including chemical recycling,  transportation,  real estate lending and development,  chemicals and metals processing and manufacturing,  paints and coatings,  minerals and mining,  plastics,  and waste handling.
<P><UL><BR>
<BR><P>Some specific examples of our recent experience include:<BR><P><LI> development of a compliance policy and audit program for a publicly-held paints and coatings manufacturer;<BR>
<BR><P><LI> identification of potential environmental liabilities related to acquisition,  divestiture,  and lending transactions for public and closely-held businesses and a major regional bank;<BR>
<BR><P><LI> defense against alleged SARA reporting violations on behalf of privately-held companies who received a blanket mailing from a citizen's group;<BR>
<BR><P><LI> representation of RCRA TSDF permittees before the Ohio and U.S. EPAs and the Ohio Hazardous Waste Facility Board;<BR>
<BR><P><LI> representation of a developer in an environmental citizen's group challenge to an Ohio EPA action before the Ohio Environmental Board of Review;<BR>
<BR><P><LI> representation of a privately-held public drinking water source in adjudication proceedings before the Ohio EPA;<BR>
<BR><P><LI> representation of private parties and government entities before the State Fire Marshal with regard to underground storage tank regulation;<BR>
<BR><P><LI> obtaining U.S. EPA approval for group stormwater permits;<BR>
<BR><P><LI> representation of a closely-held manufacturer in permit negotiations with the Ohio EPA and in an administrative appeal before Ohio's Environmental Board of Review involving alleged violation of Ohio's Air Toxics Program;<BR>
<BR><P><LI> defense against alleged Clean Water Act violations at a municipal POTW;<BR>
<BR><P><LI> wetlands and submerged land lease negotiations and permitting for development of a 500-slip marina on urban lakefront property;<BR>
<BR><P><LI> defense of a Fortune 500 chemicals manufacturer in litigation and administrative proceedings relating to a multiparty Superfund site where on-site incineration was a component of the remedy;<BR>
<BR><P><LI> representation of a subsidiary of a Fortune 500 industrial gases manufacturer in administrative proceedings and litigation brought by the State of Ohio relating to a RCRA closure and groundwater remediation;<BR>
<BR><P><LI> representation of a closely-held paint manufacturer in state-led litigation to cap a municipal landfill and to contain and treat leachate;<BR>
<BR><P><LI> defense of environmental engineers against claims arising out of design and construction of a regulated landfill and air pollution control equipment;<BR>
<BR><P><LI> representation of a solid waste management district with respect to organization and financing of its solid waste facilities; and<BR>
<BR><P><LI> representation of a Fortune 500 chemicals manufacturer in proceedings (including ADR) at a multiparty Superfund site involving claims of stream sediment and flood plains contamination.<BR></UL>
<BR><P>Calfee,  Halter  & Griswold is the Ohio member of Lex Mundi,  an international organization of independent law firms,  which allows our lawyers to access the expertise,  environmental and otherwise,  of lawyers in other U.S. and foreign jurisdictions.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>William E. Coughlin</B> (<I>Cleveland; 216-622-8334</I>) Contact for litigation andenforcement. Experienced in litigation and administrative proceedings under CERCLA,  RCRA,  Clean Water Act,  Clean Air Act and corresponding state laws and regulations. Member,  Environmental Committee,  Ohio State Bar Association,  and Environmental Section,  Cleveland Bar Association. Georgetown University,  J.D.,  1983.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Kevin P. Hallquist</B> (<I>Cleveland; 216-622-8505</I>) Contact for regulatory compliance and transactions. Experienced in counseling with respect to environmental compliance,  audits and transactions; and permitting under the Clean Air Act,  Ohio Air Toxics Program,  RCRA,  Clean Water Act,  Safe Drinking Water Act and TSCA. Member,  Section of Natural Resources,  Energy and Environmental Law,  American Bar Association; Environmental Law Institute. Chemical researcher,  Diamond Shamrock Company,  1982-1986. Case Western Reserve,  B.A.,  chemistry,  1981. Cleveland State University,  J.D.,  1986. Admitted before the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office.<BR><BR>


</UL></BODY>
