<TITLE>Fried,  Frank,  Harris,  Shriver  & Jacobson
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>Environmental</H2>
<H3>Fried,  Frank,  Harris,  Shriver  & Jacobson
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>New York:</B> One New York Plaza,  New York,  NY 10004<BR>
Tel 212-859-8000  <B>*</B>  Fax 212-859-4000<BR>
<B>Washington:</B> 1001 Pennsylvania Avenue,  N.W.,  Washington,  DC 20004-2505<BR>
Tel 202-639-7000  <B>*</B>  Fax 202-639-7003<BR>
<B>Other offices:</B> Los Angeles,  London,  Paris<BR>
<BR>
357 lawyers  <B>*</B>  20 lawyers in Environmental Practice Group<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>See this firm's profiles in the following other directories:<BR>
<UL><BR>
   <LI><A HREF="../95ATFolder/fried.html"> Antitrust</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95IPFolder/fried.html"> Intellectual Property</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95WCCFolder/fried.html"> White Collar Crime</A>
</UL>

<P>
<P>
<P><B>F</B>ried Frank is a national law firm with a practice that is international in scope. The Firm's 357 attorneys represent businesses and individuals in complex matters,  many of them in the forefront of financial and legal developments.
<P>
<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>The Environmental Practice Group</H3></CENTER>

<P>Fried Frank's Environmental Practice Group is engaged in an active litigation and regulatory practice,  representing clients in Superfund and other enforcement matters,  public safety and product recall matters,  and in contractual,  statutory cost recovery,  contribution,  and indemnification actions. The Firm also represents clients in toxic tort litigation and criminal prosecutions,  and counsels clients on lender,  successor,  and parent company liability,  corporate compliance programs,  environmental audits,  and voluntary site remediation. In addition,  a significant component of the Group's practice involves complicated transactional due diligence,  disclosure issues in public securities filings,  and mortgage securitizations. The firm represents clients before federal and state environmental and public safety agencies involving complex regulatory compliance issues.<BR><P>By way of example,  the Firm represents Fortune 500 industrial manufacturers in allocation proceedings involving Superfund sites; a major Midwestern utility on Clean Air Act regulatory issues,  including allowance trading; one of the nation's largest pharmaceutical and consumer products companies in connection with compliance matters; and a large mining company on enforcement issues. We work closely with in-house counsel and environmental consultants on remediation projects at sites throughout the United States and in foreign countries. Fried Frank attorneys also have extensive experience in the defense and management of complex toxic tort actions addressing the limits of causation analysis and permissible expert testimony,  including breast implant litigation. We handled the successful appeal of <I>Sterling </I>v.<I> Velsicol Chemical Corp.</I>,  a landmark Sixth Circuit toxic tort case,  and have served as trial counsel in major consolidated asbestos litigation. Representative clients include Asarco,  Bristol-Myers Squibb,  CH2M Hill,  Forstmann Little,  the Commonwealth of Puerto Rico,  GKN,  Ivaco,  Lear Siegler,  Ohio Edison,  Paramount Communications,  Procter  & Gamble,  Pullman,  SAIC,  Sequa,  Teachers Insurance and Annuity Association,  3M,  and TRC Companies.<BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>Allen Kezsbom</B> (<I>New York; 212-859-8148</I>) Allen Kezsbom,  the senior litigation partner who leads Fried Frank's Environmental Practice Group,  has a practice encompassing environmental and toxic tort litigation,  as well as sophisticated transactional matters. He has written and spoken extensively on environmental law and the trial of complex litigation. Brooklyn College,  B.A.,  1962; Harvard University,  LL.B.,  <I>magna cum laude</I>,  1965; <I>Harvard Law Review</I>,  1963-1965.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>E. Donald Elliott </B>(<I>Washington; 202-639-7170</I>) Don Elliott,  formerly General Counsel of the U.S. EPA,  1989-1991,  is the partner in charge of the Group's practice in the Washington,  D.C.,  office. His practice encompasses a full range of regulatory counseling and toxic tort issues,  including Clean Air Act,  RCRA,  and CERCLA. He has taught environmental law at Yale Law School since 1981. Yale University,  B.A.,  <I>summa cum laude</I>,  1970,  J.D.,  1974; Phi Beta Kappa.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Richard M. Schwartz</B> (<I>New York; 212-859-8263</I>) Richard Schwartz represents clients in environmental enforcement proceedings and transactions throughout the United States. From 1984 to 1991,  he served in the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York,  where he held several supervisory positions,  including Chief of the Environmental Protection Unit. Yale College,  B.A.,  <I>magna cum laude</I>,  1972; Clare College,  University of Cambridge,  B.A.,  1974,  M.A.,  1978; University of Chicago,  J.D.,  1977.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Anthony E. Satula,  Jr.</B> (<I>New York; 212-859-8117</I>) Anthony Satula represents clients in a wide range of environmental matters including Superfund liability,  private site cleanups,  cost recovery litigation and toxic tort litigation. Calvin College,  A.B.,  1969; Duke University,  J.D.,  1972; Editorial Board,  <I>Duke Law Journal</I>,  1971-1972.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Jay R. Kraemer</B> (<I>Washington; 202-639-7060</I>) Jay Kraemer represents clients in Clean Water Act and Atomic Energy Act regulatory matters,  and engages in legislative advocacy on environmental issues. The George Washington University,  B.A.,  with distinction,  1970; National Law Center at George Washington University,  J.D.,  with highest honors,  1973.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Gerald H. Yamada</B> (<I>Washington; 202-639-7050</I>) Gerald Yamada represents clients on regulatory and administrative law matters. He served as Principal Deputy General Counsel and Acting General Counsel of the U.S. EPA. University of California,  B.A.,  1966; San Francisco State University,  M.A.,  1968; George Washington University,  J.D.,  1974.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
