<BR>
<LI><B>Patrick Raher</B> represents clients in various EPA investigations and suits involving Superfund,  RCRA,  FIFRA,  and TSCA; and has testified before federal and state agencies concerning environmental rulemaking and enforcement matters.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Leslie Sue Ritts</B> is involved in environmental rulemakings,  including permitting approvals and control requirements for new and industrial sources and expansions of existing plants; and has represented clients in landmark Superfund cases.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Paul Rogers</B> is the former chairman of the House Subcommittee on Health and the Environment (1971-1979),  and authored major environmental statutes,  including the Clean Air Act and the Safe Drinking Water Act.<BR>
