<HEAD>
<TITLE>Hoyle,  Morris  & Kerr
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>Environmental</H2>
<H3>Hoyle,  Morris  & Kerr
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>Philadelphia:</B> One Liberty Place,  1650 Market Street,  Philadelphia,  PA 19103-7397<BR>
Tel 215-981-5700  <B>*</B>  Fax 215-851-0436<BR>
<BR>
45 lawyers  <B>*</B>  20 lawyers concentrating in environmental litigation and insurance coverage<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>See this firm's profiles in the following other directories:<BR>
<UL><BR>
   <LI><A HREF="../95ATFolder/hoyle.html"> Antitrust</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95CLFolder/hoyle.html"> Commercial Litigation</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95PLFolder/hoyle.html"> Product Liability</A>
</UL>

<P><BR>

<P>
<P><B>H</B>oyle,  Morris  & Kerr has a national litigation practice that includes the broad spectrum of commercial litigation. Firm attorneys are particularly experienced in complex litigation,  especially environmental claims,  insurance coverage disputes,  and products liability and toxic tort cases.
<P>
<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Environmental Litigation and Regulation</H3></CENTER>

<P>Hoyle,  Morris  & Kerr lawyers defend toxic tort and Superfund litigation,  oversee cooperative responses to EPA and state agency cleanup mandates,  participate in rulemaking and other regulatory activities with the EPA,  and represent corporate policyholders in insurance coverage disputes concerning environmental claims.<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Experience and Clients</H3></CENTER>

<P>Hoyle,  Morris  & Kerr is regularly engaged to represent companies in defense of lawsuits alleging personal injury or property damage from air pollution,  groundwater pollution,  or other contamination by hazardous substances,  in addition to counseling clients on environmental issues that may arise from real estate transactions,  construction projects,  and transportation or disposal of materials. The firm has provided clients with environmental audits in connection with possible corporate acquisitions. It also has advised clients concerning the development of procedures to be followed in the event of a toxic release or spill. In particular,  the firm works with chemical companies in connection with releases or other disposals of chemicals into the environment. It works with these clients to assist in their internal investigation of the causes of the releases and to develop comprehensive responses to complaints by residents of adjacent communities. When resulting litigation is initiated,  the firm works side by side with experts to marshal the complex medical-scientific evidence on which modern environmental claims are based. The firm also concentrates in the representation of corporate policyholders in disputes with their insurance carriers over coverage for environmental and toxic tort claims.<BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>Lawrence T. Hoyle,  Jr.</B> Mr. Hoyle has defended chemical and building products manufacturers in personal injury and property damage litigation complaining of alleged emissions into the air. Deputy attorney general,  Civil Litigation Division chief,  Department of Justice,  Commonwealth of Pennsylvania,  1971-1972; executive director,  Pennsylvania Crime Commission,  1972-1974. Fellow,  American Bar Foundation. Duke University,  A.B.,  1960; University of Chicago,  J.D.,  1965. Admitted in Pennsylvania,  1965.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Arlene Fickler</B> Ms. Fickler's practice includes defense of toxic tort class actions and participation in related regulatory proceedings. Member,  American Law Institute. University of Pennsylvania,  B.A.,  <I>cum laude</I>,  1971,  J.D.,  <I>cum laude</I>,  1974; comment editor,  <I>University of Pennsylvania Law Review</I>,  1973-1974. Admitted in Pennsylvania,  1974,  and the District of Columbia,  1980.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Ralph A. Jacobs</B> Mr. Jacobs' environmental practice includes litigation of claims involving hazardous waste disposal,  air and groundwater pollution,  and allegations of permit violations. Assistant U.S. attorney,  District of New Jersey,  1977-1985. Chief,  Appeals Division,  1984-1985. University of Pennsylvania,  A.B.,  1972,  J.D.,  <I>cum laude</I>,  1975; Order of the Coif. Admitted in Pennsylvania,  1975; Maryland,  1976; and New Jersey,  1984.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Jill A. Douthett</B> Ms. Douthett represents corporate policyholders in insurance coverage litigation over environmental claims. Divisional deputy city solicitor,  commercial litigation,  City of Philadelphia,  1982-1984. London School of Economics; Tulane University,  B.A.,  1973; University of Virginia,  J.D.,  1976. Phi Beta Kappa. Admitted in Pennsylvania,  1976.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Eric B. Henson</B> Mr. Henson's practice focuses on medical and technical issues inherent in toxic tort and environmental litigation. University of Kentucky,  B.A.,  1964; Harvard University,  M.A.,  1967; University of Pennsylvania,  J.D.,  1970. Phi Beta Kappa. Woodrow Wilson Fellow. Admitted in Pennsylvania,  1970.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Bebe H. Kivitz</B> Ms. Kivitz has represented chemical companies,  building products manufacturers,  and manufacturers of in-ground storage tanks in toxic tort and environmental litigation. Assistant district attorney,  Philadelphia District Attorney's Office,  1979-1985. University of Pennsylvania,  B.A.,  <I>cum laude</I>,  1976; Temple University School of Law,  J.D.,  1979. Admitted in Pennsylvania,  1979.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Sean P. Wajert</B> Mr. Wajert has represented chemical companies,  building products manufacturers,  and property owners in toxic tort and environmental litigation. Lecturer in Law,  Products Liability,  1990-1994,  Toxic Torts,  1995,  University of Pennsylvania Law School. Law clerk,  Judge Arlin M. Adams,  U.S. Court of Appeals for the Third Circuit,  1984-1985. Harvard University,  A.B.,  <I>magna cum laude</I>,  1981; University of Pennsylvania Law School,  J.D.,  <I>cum laude</I>,  1984; Order of the Coif; editor-in-chief,  <I>University of Pennsylvania Law Review</I>,  1983-1984. Admitted in Pennsylvania,  1984.<BR>
<BR>

</UL>


</UL></BODY>
