Tel 322-647-6025  <B>*</B>  Fax 322-640-7071<BR>
<BR>
334 lawyers  <B>*</B>  17 lawyers concentrating in environmental,  safety,  and health law<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>See this firm's profiles in the following other directories:<BR>
<UL><BR>
   <LI><A HREF="../95CLFolder/seyfarth.html"> Commercial Litigation</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95CSFFolder/seyfarth.html"> Corporate Securities</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95ERIFolder/seyfarth.html"> ERISA</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95IPFolder/seyfarth.html"> Intellectual Property</A>
   <LI><A HREF="..//seyfarth.html"> International Finance</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95LABFolder/seyfarth.html"> Labor</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95WCCFolder/seyfarth.html"> White Collar Crime</A>
</UL>

<P>
<P>
<P><B>S</B>eyfarth,  Shaw,  Fairweather  & Geraldson has a national environmental,  safety,  and health law practice,  comprised of 17 attorneys,  assisting clients in environmental compliance counseling,  litigation,  transactional and business planning,  and government regulation. In the area of compliance counseling,  we assist clients with the application and enforceability of federal,  state,  and local environmental and safety statutes and regulations,  advise them of precautionary measures,  alert them to changes in government policies and regulatory proposals,  and help with permitting. We advise clients on compliance with the Resource Conservation and Recovery Act and the Clean Air Act,  as well as other major environmental laws. We assist clients with contract negotiations for divestitures and acquisitions of businesses,  plants,  and operations; the transfer of various permits from buyers to sellers; environmental remediation contracts; environmental expenses related to loan origination; funding and workouts; and disclosure obligations. We have represented clients before administrative agencies and in civil and criminal enforcement actions in courts nationwide. Our clients have included major and <I>de minimis</I> generators at more than 100 Superfund sites,  including generators,  transporters,  site owners,  and engineering and consulting firms. Our attorneys are experienced in negotiating consent decrees and the scope of investigatory or remedial work,  participation agreements,  steering committee arrangements,  and related Superfund matters. We have handled claims involving asbestos,  radiation,  welding fumes,  and other hazardous materials,  and have successfully defended cases brought by OSHA under its penalty policies for egregious violations.
<P><BR><P>Seyfarth Shaw also offers comprehensive government relations services including the representation of clients before numerous federal and state regulatory agencies. In addition,  we assist in drafting proposed legislation and regulations,  advocating favorable changes in existing and proposed state environmental,  safety,  and health laws and regulations,  and in facilitating solutions between clients and the state administration,  the legislature,  and regulatory agencies. <BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>Brent I. Clark</B> (<I>Chicago</I>) has extensive experience in environmental,  OSHA,  MSHA,  and toxic tort and commercial litigation. He also counsels clients on environmental and OSHA compliance,  investigations,  audits,  and criminal enforcement matters.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Michael Hickok</B> (<I>Los Angeles</I>) has extensive experience in litigation,  administrative proceedings,  and compliance counseling,  specifically with environmental auditing,  real property transactions involving contaminated properties,  representation in federal Superfund cases,  private cleanup cost-recovery actions,  and toxic torts.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Dixie Lee Laswell</B> (<I>Chicago</I>) has 20 years of experience handling a wide variety of environmental law issues on the local,  state,  and federal levels. Her experience ranges from representing clients on local air and waste permitting issues and property transfers to challenging EPA policies and rules on a federal level.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Jeryl L. Olson</B> (<I>Chicago</I>) is experienced in environmental enforcement and compliance and enforcement matters associated with real estate and corporate transactions,  and business operations.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Keith A. Onsdorff</B> (<I>Washington</I>) focuses on both civil and criminal defense litigation,  defending clients in CERCLA,  RCRA,  CAA,  and CWA civil enforcement,  and both federal and state criminal investigations and cases.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Andrew H. Perellis</B> (<I>Chicago</I>) counsels clients on the interpretation and application of state and federal environmental statutes and regulations; environmental litigation; administration of complex CERCLA sites; participation in state and federal rulemaking and permitting proceedings; and counseling regarding environmental aspects of business transactions.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Lawrence P. Postol</B> (<I>Washington</I>) has experience in medical,  epidemiological,  and toxicological issues,  including defense of radiation,  lead,  and welding fumes claims. He has experience in Superfund,  toxic tort claims,  environmental insurance coverage claims,  and OSHA litigation.<BR>
