<BR>
360 lawyers  <B>*</B>  37 lawyers in environmental counseling and litigation<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>
<P><BR>

<P>
<P><B>S</B>quire,  Sanders  & Dempsey's environmental practice dates back even before the creation of the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency. Our attorneys regularly exercise the wide range of skills needed in today's practice,  including: litigating before state and federal courts and agencies; counseling on environmental aspects of mergers,  acquisitions,  dispositions,  loans,  and bankruptcies; negotiating with agencies and private parties; and representing clients in administrative proceedings.
<P>
<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Experience and Clients</H3></CENTER>

<P>Squire,  Sanders  & Dempsey has represented clients in more than 100 Superfund matters across the country,  including cases involving interplay of CERCLA with bankruptcy law,  lenders' considerations,  and private-party tort actions. Under the Clean Air Act and Clean Water Act,  we have defended enforcement actions,  challenged rulemaking,  represented permit applicants,  and counseled on compliance and corporate transactions. The firm has counseled and defended clients on hazardous and other solid waste issues under the Resource Conservation and Recovery Act. We have done substantial work under the Toxic Substances Control Act,  the Federal Insecticide,  Fungicide,  and Rodenticide Act,  and the National Environmental Policy Act.<BR><P>We have represented clients on state environmental law matters in more than 35 states. In addition to our private clients,  Squire,  Sanders  & Dempsey represents hundreds of public entities across the country in defense of enforcement actions,  construction grant matters,  and related issues.<BR>
<BR><P>Our international environmental practice is diverse and extensive. Representations span Australia; Canada; Central,  Eastern,  and Western Europe; the Middle East; Mexico; Latin America; and the Caribbean.<BR>
<BR><P>Beyond dealing with regulatory issues,  Squire,  Sanders  & Dempsey has defended clients in numerous environmental toxic tort claims,  which seek to recover for personal injuries,  property damages,  and other harm arising out of alleged pollution. We draw upon strengths of our environmental,  litigation,  and corporate attorneys to present a coordinated defense in these cases,  which typically span several technical areas.<BR>
