Raleigh,  NC 27601<BR>
Tel 919-755-2100  <B>*</B>  Fax 919-755-2150<BR>
<BR>
180 lawyers  <B>*</B>  14 lawyers in the Environmental/Toxic Tort Practice Group<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>
<P>
<P>
<P><B>M</B>embers of Womble Carlyle's Environmental and Toxic Tort Litigation practice group handle a wide range of litigation,  transactional,  and other legal services for a regional,  national,  and international client base. The attorneys in this practice group assist individual and corporate clients and lenders in all aspects of litigation and regulatory matters pending before federal district courts,  state courts,  and administrative agencies under federal and state environmental laws,  including CERCLA,  RCRA,  the Clean Air Act,  SARA Title III,  and North Carolina's OPHSCA. The group also regularly counsels clients with regard to the purchase,  sale,  and financing of problem properties and assists various industrial clients with regard to asbestos and lead management,  air toxics,  right-to-know issues,  hazardous waste,  and water regulations at the local,  state,  and federal levels. Representative clients are Armstrong World Industries,  Inc.,  Ciba-Geigy Corporation,  Duke Power Company,  R.J. Reynolds Tobacco Company,  and VuLCan Materials Company.<BR><BR><UL><LI><B>Cari Lyn Beck </B>(<I>Winston-Salem; 910-721-3577</I>) Cari Lyn's practice focuses on hazardous and solid waste management issues. She is a member of the Environmental and Natural Resources Law Section of the North Carolina Bar Association. Harvard University,  B.A.,  <I>cum laude</I>,  1988; University of Georgia School of Law,  J.D.,  <I>cum laude</I>,  1993. Admitted in North Carolina and U.S. District Courts for the Middle and Western Districts of North Carolina.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Charles S. Carter </B>(<I>Raleigh; 919-755-2167</I>) Charlie was formerly assistant general counsel for the Air and Radiation Division of the U.S. EPA. Member of Carolinas Air Pollution Control Association; American Bar Association (vice-chair and immediate past chair of the Air Quality Committee,  Natural Resources,  Energy and Environmental Law Section,  and member of the Judicial Review Committee of the Administrative Law Section); Air  & Waste Management Association; and Environmental Law Institute Associate. Duke University,  B.S.,  engineering,  1970; University of North Carolina School of Law,  J.D.,  1974. Admitted in North Carolina,  the District of Columbia,  U.S. District Court for the Western District of North Carolina,  U.S. District Court for the District of Columbia,  U.S. Court of Appeals for the District of Columbia,  and the U.S. Supreme Court.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Bradford A. De Vore</B> (<I>Charlotte; 704-331-4941</I>) Brad's practice is concentrated in hazardous waste counseling and environmental and toxic tort litigation. He is a member of the Environmental and Natural Resources Law Section of the North Carolina Bar Association; the District of Columbia Bar Association; and the American Bar Association. Michigan State University,  B.A,  <I>cum laude</I>,  1983; University of South Carolina School of Law,  J.D.,  1986. Admitted in North Carolina and the District of Columbia.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>R. Howard Grubbs</B> (<I>Winston-Salem; 910-721-3537</I>) Howard is head of the Environmental/Toxic Tort Litigation Section at Womble Carlyle and focuses on CERCLA,  RCRA,  and underground storage tanks in both a litigation and transactional context. He is co-editor of the <I>North Carolina Environmental Law Letter</I>. He was recently named in <I>Best Lawyers in America</I> in the area of environmental law. Denison University,  B.A.,  1968; University of South Carolina School of Law,  J.D.,  1977. Admitted in North Carolina,  South Carolina,  U.S. District Court for the District of South Carolina,  and U.S. Court of Appeals for the Fourth Circuit.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Lori Privette Hinnant</B> (<I>Winston-Salem; 910-721-3535</I>) Lori concentrates in lender liability and underground storage tank issues. She is a member of the Council of the Environmental and Natural Resources Law Section of the North Carolina Bar Association. Wake Forest University,  B.A.,  <I>cum laude</I>,  1983,  J.D. <I>cum laude</I>,  1987. Admitted in North Carolina,  U.S. District Court for the Middle District of North Carolina,  and U.S. Court of Appeals for the Fourth Circuit.
