<HEAD>
<TITLE>Amster,  Rothstein & Ebenstein
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>Intellectual Property</H2>
<H3>Amster,  Rothstein & Ebenstein
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<BR>
<B>New York:</B> 90 Park Avenue,  New York,  NY 10016<BR>
Tel 212-697-5995  <B>*</B>  Fax 212-286-0854<BR>
<BR>
37 lawyers  <B>*</B>  All lawyers practice in intellectual property<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>
<P><BR>

<P><BR>

<P><B>A</B>mster,  Rothstein  & Ebenstein has been engaged exclusively in the practice of patent,  trademark,  copyright,  and unfair competition law since 1953. Most of our attorneys have technical degrees in such areas as electrical engineering,  physics,  mechanical engineering,  chemical engineering,  biology,  and computer science,  and are patent attorneys licensed to practice before the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office. Among our partners and associates are also attorneys focusing uniquely in all areas of trademark law,  including licensing and financial transactions
<P><BR><P>We provide a full range of counseling and services in all areas of intellectual property law.<BR><P>In addition to our domestic practice,  we protect our clients' intellectual property throughout the world both on a direct basis and by utilizing the services of a well-established base of foreign attorneys and agents. <BR>
<BR>
<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Patent Litigation,  Prosecution,  and Studies</H3></CENTER>

<P>We are engaged in all phases of patent infringement litigation in federal district courts throughout the United States. Our patent litigation practice spans the range of modern technology.<BR><P>Since the formation of our firm,  we have been preparing and soliciting utility and design patents. Our work in this field covers all aspects of prosecution in patent offices worldwide,  from working with inventors in the preparation of patent drawings and patent specifications,  through appeals of Patent Office decisions. We also handle interference proceedings in the Patent Office.<BR>
<BR><P>We conduct patentability searches and right-to-use searches; advise clients in the design and redesign of products to avoid potential claims of patent infringement; and evaluate patent problems prior to,  and with the objective of avoiding,  litigation.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Trademark and Unfair CompetitionLitigation,  Prosecution,  and Searching</H3></CENTER>

<P>We work with clients to protect and enforce their trademarks and related proprietary rights in the courts and in administrative proceedings in the Patent and Trademark Office. We have had extensive experience in unfair competition,  false advertising,  and trade dress matters,  and were instrumental in establishing Section 43(a) of the Lanham Act as a viable mechanism for asserting unfair competition and trade dress claims.<BR><P>We search trademarks,  and counsel as to their availability for use and registration. We prepare and prosecute trademark applications and maintain a computerized docketing system containing records of our clients' trademark applications and registrations worldwide.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Copyright Litigation and Prosecution</H3></CENTER>

<P>Our copyright practice includes such diverse areas of the commercial and industrial arts as computer software,  publishing,  fabric and product designs,  toys,  advertising,  packaging,  and promotional materials. We also represent book and video publishing companies in this area. Our services include initial client counseling,  the filing of copyright applications,  prelitigation strategy,  trials,  and appeals.<BR><P>We are also active in the related area of obtaining maskwork protection for semiconductor products.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Anticounterfeiting Activities</H3></CENTER>

<P>Even before passage of the Anti-Counterfeiting Act of 1984,  our firm was in the forefront of anticounterfeiting activities on behalf of a number of our clients. We coordinate undercover investigations for our clients,  obtain seizure orders under the Anti-Counterfeiting Act,  and execute those seizure orders at retail and wholesale establishments,  factories,  flea markets,  and on the streets of major cities throughout the United States. We coordinate investigations,  seizures,  and resulting criminal prosecutions in most countries in the Far East. Our experienced anti-counterfeiting attorneys regularly work with law enforcement agencies,  and conduct and participate in anticounterfeiting seminars before such agencies.<BR>
<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Intellectual Property Aspects of Business Negotiations (Licensing,  Mergers,  Acquisitions,  Financing)</H3></CENTER>

<P>In all areas of intellectual property,  we represent licensors and licensees by preparing,  negotiating,  and administering licenses from the simple to the complex in both domestic and international business ventures. Our licensing work includes providing both legal and business-related advice to our clients based on our years of experience in the licensing field.<BR><P>Our firm provides legal services and renders opinions to clients engaged in merger and acquisition activities,  including buyers,  sellers,  and financial institutions,  relative to intellectual property rights which often form the `collateral' for such transactions. We conduct due diligence and intellectual property audits,  negotiate the sale of businesses,  and participate in the preparation of agreements. We have assisted clients in the disposition and acquisition of assets overseen by the bankruptcy courts and have advised clients in the bankruptcy area relative to intellectual property assets.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>Morton Amster</B> is the founding partner. He has been instrumental in developing the law of federal unfair competition through strategic landmark litigation,  and is a seasoned litigator of patent,  trademark,  and copyright cases,  and a veteran of U.S. Patent and Trademark Office prosecution practice.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Jesse Rothstein</B> advises and litigates in the trademark and copyright areas,  having contributed to the development of modern trademark and copyright laws. He also has technical expertise in the field of patent prosecution and has litigated patent and trade secret cases.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Daniel S. Ebenstein</B> maintains a broad practice specialty including areas of high-tech patent litigation and computer technology,  and advises and litigates actively in the patent,  trademark,  and copyright areas. He also actively negotiates and brings to fruition complex licensing and technology-sharing arrangements<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Philip H. Gottfried</B> is active in all areas of patent,  trademark,  and copyright counseling,  litigation,  and prosecution through governmental offices on behalf of a diverse group of clients active in all fields ranging from toys to clothing to high technology areas.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Michael J. Berger</B> actively practices in all intellectual property areas,  specializing in complex technology,  licensing,  patent litigation,  and counseling prosecution in the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Neil M. Zipkin</B> is active in advising and in litigating in all fields of intellectual property and has successfully tried several cases in those areas. He recently succeeded in obtaining a record-setting award of damages and counsel fees in a copyright infringement case.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Anthony F. LoCicero</B> advises and litigates in all areas of patent,  trademark,  and copyright law,  and has been instrumental in developing and enforcing trademark anticounterfeiting laws in the United States and throughout the world. He lectures frequently on trademark and unfair competition law.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Joel E. Lutzker</B> advises and litigates in all areas of patent,  trademark,  and copyright laws and has successfully litigated complex patent cases involving high-technology products and patents. He is also proficient in areas of secured transactions,  licensing,  trademark,  and patent asset valuation,  and has lectured and written on these areas.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Karen Artz</B> <B>Ash</B> has developed broad expertise in the areas of trademark and copyright laws and extending these practice areas to transactions involving security interests,  financing,  bankruptcy,  mergers and acquisitions,  and complex licensing arrangements through the world. She also actively participates in litigation within her practice areas,  has written and lectured extensively in these fields,  and is an active and experienced federal mediator and a member of the Southern District of New York Mediation Panel.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Kenneth P. George</B> is active in advising and litigating in the developing areas of biotechnology,  and has also successfully litigated patent and trade secret cases on diverse products ranging from catheters to tennis rackets and swim goggles. He also devotes his attention to the protection and development of innovative medical technology.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Abraham Kasdan</B> is active in patent practice involving complex technology areas relating to electronics and the physical sciences. He is involved in providing patent opinions in these areas,  as well as litigation and prosecution activities.
</UL>


</UL></BODY>
</HTML>
