<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Banner  & Allegretti,  Ltd.
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>Intellectual Property</H2>
<H3>Banner  & Allegretti,  Ltd.
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>Chicago:</B> 10 South Wacker Drive,  Chicago,  IL 60606<BR>
Tel 312-715-1000  <B>*</B>  Fax 312-715-1234<BR>
<B>Washington:</B> 1001 G Street,  N.W.,  Washington,  DC 20001<BR>
Tel 202-508-9100  <B>*</B>  Fax 202-508-9299<BR>
<B>Boston:</B> 75 State Street,  Boston,  MA 02109<BR>
Tel 617-345-9100  <B>*</B>  Fax 617-345-9111<BR>
<BR>
85 lawyers  <B>*</B>  All lawyers practice in intellectual property<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Patent Prosecution,  Counseling,  Opinions,  and Licensing</H3></CENTER>

<P>Preparation and prosecution of patent applications was the basis for the founding of Allegretti  & Witcoff under names including the highly recognized Bair,  Freeman  & Molinare,  and in combination of the practices of Allegretti  & Witcoff and Banner,  Birch,  McKie  & Beckett,  the firm gains renewed vigor in this area. Counseling,  opinions,  and licensing continue to be central aspects of the firm's practice,  and the firm is pleased to be partnering with a wide variety of clients in the development of their competitive positions.<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Trademarks</H3></CENTER>

<P>Banner  & Allegretti includes numerous lawyers dedicated exclusively to the creation and protection of trademark rights. Among other clients,  Banner  & Allegretti is pleased to represent one of most prominent consumer athletics companies in the world,  and one of the most prominent home publishing companies in the world.<BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>James V. Callahan</B> is the managing director of the firm. He has over 30 years' experience in intellectual property protection and exploitation.
</UL>

<P><BR>

<P>
<P><B>B</B>anner  & Allegretti,  Ltd. merges the capabilities of Allegretti  & Witcoff,  Ltd.,  founded in 1920,  and Banner,  Birch,  McKie  & Beckett,  founded in 1960. The merger,  in 1995,  places 37 lawyers in Chicago,  39 in Washington,  D.C.,  and 9 in Boston.
<P>
<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Practice Overview</H3></CENTER>

<P>Banner  & Allegretti is dedicated to excellence in the specialized practice of intellectual property law,  as were both its predecessor firms. Within our practice,  we are a full-service law firm. We provide legal representation in obtaining,  commercializing,  and litigating intellectual property rights throughout the U.S. and abroad. Our attorneys are knowledgeable and experienced in all technologies,  including biotechnology,  chemistry,  electronics,  computer hardware and software,  and in all intellectual properties,  including patents,  trademarks,  copyrights,  trade secrets,  trade dress,  and the like.<BR><P>We are committed to providing the highest-quality legal services,  efficiently and at a reasonable cost. We pioneered in computerized control of litigation documents,  and our lawyers are highly advanced in computer capabilities for client benefit. Further,  in our experience,  a close working relationship with each client is the best way to ensure that the client's business objectives are achieved within budget constraints. We weLCome the opportunity to work with our clients so that they can better control their budgets and lower their legal costs.<BR>
<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Biotechnology</H3></CENTER>

<P>Banner  & Allegretti lawyers successfully argued the <I>Chakrabarty</I> case in the U.S. Supreme Court,  establishing the patentability of the products of biotechnology. Banner  & Allegretti lawyers then represented the successful party in the erythropoietin (EPO) litigation,  the first fully tried litigation based on a biotechnology patent,  and in the tissue plasminogen activator (t-PA) litigation,  the first litigation based on a biotechnology patent tried to a jury. The firm has numerous attorneys with Ph.D.'s in biotechnology. Emphasis in biotechnology is given to strategic development of patent portfolios covering client technologies.
<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Jury Trials</H3></CENTER>

<P>Attorneys at Banner  & Allegretti have proven skills in conducting jury trials. Banner  & Allegretti lawyers have successfully conducted patent jury trials throughout the United States in all technical fields. Building on six decades of success in patent infringement bench trials,  Banner  & Allegretti lawyers have readily adapted to the jury trial revolution.<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Chemistry and Chemical Engineering</H3></CENTER>

<P>Banner  & Allegretti lawyers have gained numerous preliminary injunctions for chemical industry clients,  thereby rapidly and effectively protecting research and development investments against infringing manufacturers,  both U.S. and foreign. The firm is capable of coordinated activities throughout the world in aid of injunctive remedies.<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Electronics,  Computers and Related Technologies</H3></CENTER>

<P>Banner  & Allegretti lawyers successfully presented the owner of patent rights to object linking and embedding (OLE) as against Microsoft,  gaining a highly favorable settlement. Banner  & Allegretti lawyers are currently developing the patent portfolios of some of the fastest-growing computer communications and electronics companies in the world. Banner  & Allegretti lawyers have a history of protecting and litigating as related to electronics,  computers,  and related technologies extending back to successful invalidation of the ENIAC patent in the late 1960s,  thereby causing history to recognize John Atanasoff as the inventor of the first electronic computer.<BR>


</UL></BODY>
</HTML>
