<UL><LI> RISC technology
<LI> Thin film head semiconductor technology<BR>
<BR></UL><P><I>Semiconductor Chip Protection Act actions including:</I><BR><UL><LI> Layouts for video color display technology (tried to verdict)<BR>
<BR></UL><P><I>All aspects of intellectual property registration and business counseling:</I><BR>
<UL><LI> Computer licensing agreements,  including beta testing site licenses<BR>
<BR><BR></UL>
<LI><B>Claude A. S. Hamrick</B>,  a former U.S. patent examiner,  concentrates on the preparation and filing of complex patent applications,  patent and trademark litigation,  and re-examination challenges of issued patents. He has particular experience in the following areas of technology: lasers,  semiconductor manufacturing equipment,  computers,  electronic instrumentation,  spectrometry and chromatography,  concrete structures,  industrial control,  aeronautics,  and software.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Alexander L. Brainerd</B> has handled numerous complex patent infringement actions involving programmable logic devices,  color video display technology,  and videotape recording,  including the first case ever tried to a jury under the Semiconductor Chip Protection Act of 1984. He also has prosecuted or defended a number of complex trade secret cases,  including cases involving thin film head technology and semiconductor equipment manufacturing technology. Lex is a member of the American College of Trial Lawyers.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Kenneth E. Keller</B> has handled a variety of patent,  trademark and copyright cases,  including three cases tried to verdict: one involving patents on color video display technology (the above-mentioned case tried under the Semiconductor Chip Protection Act),  one involving a patent on a process for purifying monoclonal antibodies,  and a third involving a patent on corrugation manufacturing equipment. He is a member of the American Board of Trial Advocates.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Robert O. Guillot</B> practices in the areas of U.S. and foreign patent,  trademark,  and copyright prosecution and litigation. He has particular experience in the areas of aerospace technology,  laser and fiber optics,  thin films,  magnetic media duplication devices,  plasms and CVD systems,  semiconductor fabrication and mounting,  VOC incineration technologies,  immunoassay test methods and devices,  and computer media storage devices.<BR>
