<HEAD>
<TITLE>Brumbaugh,  Graves,  Donohue  & Raymond
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>Intellectual Property</H2>
<H3>Brumbaugh,  Graves,  Donohue  & Raymond
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>New York:</B> 30 Rockefeller Plaza,  New York,  NY 10112<BR>
Tel 212-408-2500  <B>*</B>  Fax 212-765-2519<BR>
MCI Mail: 611-1063  <B>*</B>  Home page: http\\www.iPCounsel.com<BR>
<BR>
44 lawyers  <B>*</B>  All lawyers in intellectual property practice<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>
<P>
<P>
<P><B>S</B>ince its inception in 1920,  the firm has specialized in all aspects of intellectual property law. This includes the representation of litigants in federal and state courts,  administrative agencies,  arbitration,  alternative dispute resolution,  investigations,  and counseling for the purposes of preparing for or avoiding litigation,  and <I>ex parte</I> and <I>inter partes</I> proceedings before the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office,  the U.S. Copyright Office,  the International Trade Commission,  and the U.S. Customs Office. Our specialties include patent,  trademark,  copyright,  trade secret,  unfair competition,  false advertising,  computer law,  and patent antitrust matters,  as well as licensing and technology transfer,  and Food and Drug Administration and Environmental Protection Agency-related matters. Our lawyers have experience in all levels of trial and appellate work and have been particularly successful in jury trials involving intellectual property issues.
<P><BR><P>Our firm is organized into practice groups broadly focusing on Patents,  Trademarks,  and Copyrights. These groups coalesce,  allowing cases to be appropriately staffed by attorneys possessing the right combination of legal and technical skills. This enables us to bill clients only for necessary services,  yet still provide the winning strategies on which we built our reputation.<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Technical Experience and Our Clients</H3></CENTER>

<P>To serve our clients,  the firm brings together the diverse experience and expertise of lawyers with degrees in all important areas of technology,  including lawyers with medical degrees; Ph.D.s in biotechnology,  electrical engineering,  and chemistry; and master's degrees in physics,  immunology,  computer science,  and mechanical engineering. Others,  before turning to law,  have worked as educators or as scientists and engineers for major corporations.<BR><P>Our clients come to us from throughout the United States,  Canada,  Europe,  and the Far East,  and from many diverse industries,  including the chemical industry,  biotechnology,  computers,  telecommunications,  banking,  transportation,  manufacturing,  cosmetics,  fashion,  merchandising,  marketing and advertising,  and building and construction. In addition,  we represent universities,  hospitals,  and other nonprofit research groups. Our attorneys and technical staff are members of major technical societies such as IEEE,  ASME,  ACS,  and AAAS,  and professional organizations including ABA,  AIPLA,  and INTA. We work closely with clients at the cutting edge of technology to see that their intellectual property rights are preserved and diligently enforced.<BR>
<BR>

