<TITLE>Connolly,  Bove,  Lodge & Hutz
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>Intellectual Property</H2>
<H3>Connolly,  Bove,  Lodge & Hutz
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>Wilmington:</B> 1220 Market Street,  Wilmington,  DE 19801<BR>
Tel 302-658-9141  <B>*</B>  Fax 302-658-5614  <B>*</B>  E-mail: <A HREF="mailto:cseitz98@counsel.com">cseitz98@counsel.com</A><BR>
<BR>
35 lawyers  <B>*</B>  24 lawyers in intellectual property<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>
<P>
<P>
<P><B>C</B>onnolly,  Bove,  Lodge  & Hutz has served a national and international clientele in the field of intellectual property for over a half-century. With its location in Delaware,  it also offers a full range of corporate and commercial law services.
<P><BR><P>The firm's patent and trademark practice involves litigation in district courts throughout the country and appeals before the Federal Circuit,  other circuits,  and the U.S. Supreme Court. It includes prosecution work in the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office and substantial participation in alternative dispute resolution (ADR),  as well as licensing,  copyrights,  and trade dress,  trade secret,  antitrust,  and unfair competition litigation.<BR><P>The firm's success over the years is based on its dedication to both quality legal services and a serious commitment to cost containment. The size of the firm permits personal attention of partners,  streamlined case staffing,  and avoidance of duplicative effort and layers of internal communication.<BR>
<BR><P>Connolly,  Bove,  Lodge  & Hutz consistently ranks among the top national firms in domestic patent application filings. Skilled patent prosecutors have diverse backgrounds and degrees in the chemical,  biotech,  mechanical,  electrical and computer arts.<BR>
<BR><P>Representative clients in the intellectual property field include Abbott Laboratories,  Albermarle Corporation,  Agfa,  ARCO Chemical Company,  Bayer AG,  Colgate-Palmolive Company,  Ethyl Corporation,  Henkel Corporation,  Hoechst AG,  Pfizer Inc.,  Rohm and Haas Company,  SteeLCase Inc.,  University of Delaware,  and WeLCh Allyn,  Inc. Some have been clients since the 1940s.<BR>
<BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>Rudolf E. Hutz </B>has over 30 years of intellectual property litigation experience. He successfully argued the appeal of <I>Dawson Chemical Co. </I>v.<I> Rohm and Haas Co.</I>,  448 U.S. 176 (1980),  before the U.S. Supreme Court,  which established an exception to the antitrust laws for control of unpatented products under contributory infringement standards. He provides invaluable representation in all intellectual property matters and was cited in <I>Guide to the World's Leading Patent Law Experts</I>,  published by Euromoney Publications PLC.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>James M. Mulligan,  Jr.</B>,  with the firm for over 35 years,  participates in patent and licensing work,  and also practices in corporate law,  commercial law,  and Delaware holding companies.<BR>
<LI><B>Arthur G. Connolly,  Jr.</B>,  with the firm for more than 30 years,  couples a corporate law practice and general litigation with the practice of trademark and trade secret litigation and other areas of intellectual property.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Harold Pezzner </B>has over 30 years of experience with the firm in patent and trademark prosecution and litigation,  emphasizing the mechanical arts.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>John D. Fairchild</B>,  over 30 years with the firm,  has engaged in patent litigation,  prosecution,  and licensing; in ADR cases; and in all aspects of trademark practice.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Richard M. Beck</B> has focused on patent prosecution in his 30-plus years with the firm. He has also participated in patent litigation,  copyright,  and ADR matters.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Paul E. Crawford</B> has concentrated on patent,  trade secret,  and trade dress litigation during his 25-plus years in the firm. He also has extensive experience in copyright matters and in ADR.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Stanley C. Macel III</B>,  25 years with the firm,  practices in trademark,  unfair competition,  trade secret,  and trade dress litigation.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Thomas M. Meshbesher</B>,  with 25 years of patent prosecution and interference experience in the chemical and mechanical arts,  is a fertile source of counsel to clients and to the younger patent prosecutors he supervises.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>George Pazuniak</B>,  in his 15 years with the firm,  has done trial and appellate work in numerous patent and trade secret cases involving technology ranging from mechanical inventions to complex chemical products and processes.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>N. Richard Powers</B>,  a former U.S. Magistrate Judge for the District of Delaware,  adds a judicial perspective to his participation in patent litigation.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Richard David Levin</B> brings his 20 years of commercial law background to the area of patent damages. He also conducts a varied business law practice.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Jeffrey B. Bove</B> brings his antitrust,  unfair competition,  licensing,  and commercial transactions background to bear on intellectual property matters.<BR>
<BR>
