<HEAD>
<TITLE>Devine,  Millimet  & Branch
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>Intellectual Property</H2>
<H3>Devine,  Millimet  & Branch
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>Manchester:</B> 111 Amherst Street,  Manchester,  NH 03101<BR>
Tel 603-669-1000  <B>*</B>  Fax 603-669-8547  <B>*</B>  E-mail: <A HREF="mailto:info@dmb.com">info@dmb.com</A><BR>
<BR>
61 lawyers  <B>*</B>  8 lawyers in intellectual property<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>
<P><BR>

<P>
<P><B>D</B>evine,  Millimet  & Branch,  a professional association,  is a general practice law firm serving clients ranging from individuals to multinational corporations. We are one of the largest firms in northern New England.
<P><BR><P>Our intellectual property section assists our clients in the comprehensive protection and management of their intellectual property assets,  including patents,  trademarks,  copyrights,  and trade secrets. Our goal is to help each of our clients maximize the return on its intellectual property assets.<BR><P>Some of the patent-related services that we offer include: searches; patentability evaluations; validity and infringement opinions; and preparation,  filing and prosecution of applications before the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office and in foreign jurisdictions.<BR>
<BR><P>We have an active international trademark registration practice. As such,  we have an extensive network of foreign associates at our disposal in Western and Eastern European,  Pacific Rim,  Middle Eastern,  African and South American countries.<BR>
<BR><P>We also offer copyright registration and enforcement services. In addition,  we help our clients establish in-house copyright registration programs.<BR>
<BR><P>We advise our clients on the preparation of patent and trademark licenses,  joint ventures,  and technology transfer agreements. We also assist our clients with intellectual property issues in the context of mergers and acquisitions.<BR>
<BR><P>The litigators in our intellectual property group have tried numerous cases,  both to the court and to a jury,  involving patents,  trademarks,  trade secrets,  and licensed technology. We have the experience and resources to handle litigation involving requests for immediate relief through expedited hearings and discovery.<BR>
<BR><P>We work hard for our clients. We also understand that our clients would like to be billed for results,  not the number of hours spent on a project. We are pleased to discuss alternative billing arrangements.<BR>
<BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>Paul C. Remus</B> (<I>PCremus@dmb.com</I>) Head of our Patent Group. Experienced in patent prosecution and litigation with some licensing. Registered to practice before the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office. Adjunct professor of law,  Franklin Pierce Law Center. Worked in optics and computer programming. Yale College,  B.S.,  physics,  1967; University of Michigan Law School,  J.D.,  1971.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>George R. Moore</B> Experienced in litigation involving patents,  licenses and trade secrets. St. Lawrence University,  B.A.,  1970; Washington and Lee University School of Law J.D.,  1977.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Donald R. Stacey</B> (<I>drstacey@dmb.com</I>) Head of our Trademark and Copyright Group. Experienced in trademark and copyright registration,  taxation of intellectual property,  and software licensing. State University of New York at Albany,  B.A.,  1980; Albany Law School of Union University,  J.D.,  1984; Boston University,  LL.M.,  taxation,  1988.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>James T. Sullivan</B> (<I>jtsullivan@dmb.com</I>) Experienced in patent and trademark application and prosecution,  software licensing,  and technology transfer. Registered to practice before the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office. Nuclear engineer in U.S. Navy submarine force. Adjunct professor of law,  Franklin Pierce Law Center. University of Notre Dame,  B.S.,  mechanical engineering,  1981; Franklin Pierce Law Center,  J.D.,  1992.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Alexander J. Walker,  Jr.</B> Experienced in litigation involving copyrights and licenses. University of Massachusetts,  B.A.,  1989; Northeastern University,  J.D.,  1992.
</UL>


</UL></BODY>
