<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Dressler,  Goldsmith,  Shore  & Milnamow,  Ltd.
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>Intellectual Property</H2>
<H3>Dressler,  Goldsmith,  Shore  & Milnamow,  Ltd.
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>Chicago:</B> Two Prudential Plaza,  Suite 4700,  Chicago,  IL 60601<BR>
Tel 312-616-5400  <B>*</B>  Fax 312-616-5460<BR>
<B>Other office:</B> Washington,  D.C.<BR>
<BR>
15 lawyers  <B>*</B>  All lawyers practice in intellectual property law<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>
<P>
<P>
<P><B>D</B>ressler Goldsmith has a long history of counseling its clients' teams of business strategists and problem-solvers. In this way,  we carry out our tradition of dedication to service our clients' business goals. Our practice includes:
<P><UL><BR><BR>
<BR><P><LI> Counsel to our clients on developing intellectual property programs that support their business objectives.<BR><P><LI> Litigation on behalf of our clients throughout the world,  with the goal of protecting key assets of their company and ensuring strategic goals.<BR>
<BR><P><LI> Prosecution of patent,  trademark,  and copyright applications,  using our worldwide network of associate firms to most efficiently meet our clients' needs.<BR>
<BR><P><LI> Licensing services,  including the negotiation and preparation of foreign and domestic patent and trademark license agreements,  technology transfer agreements,  patent-related aspects of merger agreements,  or research and development agreements.<BR>
<BR><BR>
</UL>
<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Our Clients</H3></CENTER>

<BR><BR>
<P>Our representative client list includes such long-term clients as Johnson and Johnson,  Weyerhaeuser,  Abbott Laboratories,  Eastman Kodak,  and ALCoa Corporation. The goals of our firm in working with clients on intellectual property matters are the following:<BR><UL><BR><P><LI> achievement of business objectives while minimizing legal risk<BR>
<BR><P><LI> protection of markets and competitive positioning<BR>
<BR><P><LI> an increase in profitability for the client<BR>
<BR></UL><P>Our lawyers are adept at business dealings as well as having exceptionally strong legal and technological backgrounds. Approximately one-half of our professional staff have advanced technical degrees. We work with our clients not just on obtaining and protecting patents,  but also on educational programs for management and technical personnel and on strategies for developing and marketing technology-related assets. The following are representative of recent matters we have handled: a multimillion-dollar divestiture of a product line in the pharmaceutical industry; infringement guidance and product planning for a large consumer goods manufacturer; and the creation of a patent estate for a biotechnology corporation. The firm's litigation practice is available to our clients as a last resort in resolving disputes. We,  of course,  make every effort to find ways to obviate the time-consuming process of litigation. However,  when litigation is required,  our clients receive the best talent available along with a strong commitment to handling litigation matters in a cost-effective and business-oriented manner.<BR>
<BR><P>Our recent litigation results are extremely favorable to the affected clients. For example,  we succeeded in defeating a motion for preliminary injunction in a multi-million-dollar claim for alleged misappropriation of tantalum production trade secrets. Recently,  the plaintiff dismissed with prejudice its case against our client in light of the proofs adduced and the result obtained at the preliminary injunction hearing.<BR>
<BR><P>Also,  in a recent patent infringement jury trial,  the jury found in favor of our client,  an accused infringer,  and the jury's verdict was affirmed on appeal. In the current atmosphere of large dollar damage awards in patent jury trials,  we are especially pleased with this result. Similarly,  in a recent patent infringement jury trial for the patent owner,  the jury found in favor of our client,  resulting in an immediate $3 million settlement without right of appeal.<BR>
<BR><P>We have also obviated a jury trial on behalf of an accused infringer by successfully obtaining a summary judgment determination of noninfringement.<BR>
<BR><P>With attorneys having degrees in such areas as chemistry,  chemical and nuclear engineering,  biotechnology,  and government/political sciences,  as well as doctorates in physiology,  microbiology,  organic chemistry,  and immunology,  the firm is uniquely suited to serving clients in the health care area.<BR>
<BR><UL>
<LI><B>Martin L. Katz</B> is the firm's managing partner. Mr. Katz works with clients in the chemical and pharmaceutical areas and has served as patent counsel for two large drug companies.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Thomas C. Northrup </B>earned his doctorate and practices in the biotech/chemical group; he has expertise in areas ranging from drugs to monoclonal antibodies and genetically engineered plants.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Paul M. Vargo</B> earned his doctorate and taught in electronics and computer systems; his practice includes advising high-tech based clients on computer hardware and software.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>John P. Milnamow</B> leads the mechanical arts practice group and has particular expertise in absorbent product technology and counseling large corporate clients.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Joel E. Siegel</B> is the firm's senior partner in its trademark and unfair competition practice group. Prior to joining the firm,  he was patent and trademark counsel for a Fortune 500 company.<BR></UL><BR>


</UL></BODY>
