<CENTER>
<H2>Intellectual Property</H2>
<H3>Fitzpatrick,  Cella,  Harper  & Scinto
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>New York:</B> 277 Park Avenue,  New York,  NY 10172<BR>
Tel 212-758-2400  <B>*</B>  Fax 212-758-2982<BR>
<B>Washington:</B> 1001 Pennsylvania Avenue,  N.W.,  Washington,  DC 20004<BR>
Tel 202-347-8100  <B>*</B>  Fax 202-347-8136<BR>
<B>Costa Mesa:</B> 650 Town Center Drive,  Suite 740,  Costa Mesa,  CA 92626<BR>
Tel 714-540-8700  <B>*</B>  Fax 714-540-9823<BR>
<BR>
90 lawyers  <B>*</B>  All lawyers in intellectual property<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>
<P>
<P>
<P><B>O</B>ur firm,  founded 24 years ago,  has grown to be one of the country's leaders in intellectual property law,  with expertise in litigation,  prosecution,  licensing,  and counseling. With offices on both coasts and in Washington,  D.C.,  we serve a multinational clientele in all aspects of intellectual property law.
<P><BR><P>Our lawyers combine diverse technological backgrounds with extensive trial experience in complex litigation,  both nationally and internationally. We have litigated patent,  trademark,  counterfeiting,  copyright,  trade secret,  unfair competition,  and related antitrust and international trade law matters throughout the country in state and federal courts,  as well as at the International Trade Com-mission concerning technologies ranging from anticancer drugs,  cameras,  personal computers,  and printers,  to candy.<BR><P>We also handle the preparation and prosecution of patents and trademarks at the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office and have in-depth experience with interferences,  oppositions,  cancellations,  and reexaminations. Currently we are prosecuting thousands of applications. Our docketing and maintenance facilities are fully computerized.<BR>
<BR><P>Our attorneys assist clients in all aspects of intellectual property matters. We provide opinions,  handle licensing,  engage in arbitrations,  and advise concerning the intellectual property aspects of mergers and acquisitions. We actively participate abroad in connection with the patent offices and courts in Europe and Asia.<BR>
<BR><P>Our Washington,  D.C. office is located near the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office,  the ITC,  and the U.S. Court of Appeals for the Federal Circuit. With direct electronic communication from our New York and California offices to our Washington staff,  we can assure immediate action in those forums. We have been successful at the ITC for,  among others,  the complainant E. I. du Pont de Nemours  & Company in <I>In re certain Aramid Fibers</I> and for the respondent Cetus in <I>In re certain Doxorubicin</I>.<BR>
<BR><P>Representative clients: Exxon,  Merck,  Canon,  Mars,  Warner-Lambert,  Bristol-Myers Squibb.<BR>
<BR>
<UL><BR>
