<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>Intellectual Property</H2>
<H3>Fliesler,  Dubb,  Meyer & Lovejoy
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>San Francisco:</B> Four Embarcadero Center,  Fourth Floor,  San Francisco,  CA 94111<BR>
Tel 415-362-3800  <B>*</B>  Fax 415-362-2928  <B>*</B>  E-mail: <A HREF="mailto:atty@fdml.com">atty@fdml.com</A><BR>
<B>Santa Clara:</B> 3945 Freedom Circle,  Suite 770,  Santa Clara,  CA 95054<BR>
Tel 408-748-7300  <B>*</B>  Fax 408-748-7310  <B>*</B>  E-mail: <A HREF="mailto:atty@fdml.com">atty@fdml.com</A><BR>
<BR>
20 lawyers  <B>*</B>  All lawyers practice intellectual property law<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>
<P>
<P>
<P><B>F</B>liesler,  Dubb,  Meyer  & Lovejoy provides a full range of legal services relating to intellectual property law,  including patents,  trademarks,  copyrights,  maskworks,  trade secrets,  and unfair competition. We counsel clients in evaluating,  protecting,  licensing,  and litigating their intellectual property rights. We work with clients from start-up companies and multinational corporations that engage in a broad range of high-technology fields,  particularly computers,  electronics,  semiconductor chip technology,  software,  magnetic storage devices,  telecommunications,  physics,  chemistry,  medical developments,  biotechnology,  and mechanics.
<P><BR><P>All Fliesler,  Dubb,  Meyer  & Lovejoy attorneys practice exclusively in the area of intellectual property law. Our attorneys have advanced engineering and science degrees,  experience in business and technology,  and are registered to practice as patent attorneys before the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office.<BR><P>Representative clients include: Advanced Micro Devices,  Inc.; Amdahl Corporation; Apple Computer,  Inc.; Asyst Technologies,  Inc.; Chevron Corporation; Conner Peripherals,  Inc.; Menlo Care,  Inc.; New Image Industries,  Inc.; Sharp Microelectronics Technology,  Inc.; TelCom Universal,  Inc.; and The 3DO Company.<BR>
<BR><P>Representative litigation includes: <I>Brooktree </I>v. <I>Advanced Micro Devices (`AMD'); Samsung </I>v. <I>AMD; AMD </I>v.<I> Altera; AMD </I>v. <I>Gazelle; AMD </I>v.<I> Atmel; AMD </I>v.<I> Cypress; AMD </I>v. <I>Brooktree; Conner Peripherals </I>v.<I> Western Digital; IBM </I>v.<I> Conner Peripherals; Maxim Integrated Products </I>v. <I>Teledyne; High Tech Medical Instrumentation </I>v.<I> New Image Industries; Asyst Technologies </I>v.<I> Jenoptik GmbH; Auspex Systems </I>v.<I> Apogee Systems; Network Appliances </I>v.<I> Auspex Systems; Nintendo </I>v.<I> TSMC; Pacific Telesis </I>v.<I> Allied Telesis; </I>and<I> Rodime,  P.L.C. </I>v.<I> Conner Peripherals.</I><BR>
<BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>Martin C. Fliesler</B> counsels clients principally in the fields of computer systems architecture and software,  computer peripheral systems and components,  microelectronic circuit designs,  semiconductor chip technology,  telecom and microwave instrumentation,  and other high-technology electronics. B.E.,  1965,  electrical engineering; J.D.,  1968.<BR>
<BR>
