<TITLE>Howrey  & Simon
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>Intellectual Property</H2>
<H3>Howrey  & Simon
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>Washington:</B> 1299 Pennsylvania Avenue,  N.W.,  Washington,  DC 20004<BR>
Tel 202-783-0800  <B>*</B>  Fax 202-383-6610<BR>
<B>Los Angeles:</B> 550 South Hope Street,  Suite 1400,  Los Angeles,  CA 90071<BR>
Tel 213-892-1800  <B>*</B>  Fax 213-892-2300<BR>
<BR>
300 lawyers  <B>*</B> 36 lawyers concentrating in intellectual property matters<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>See this firm's profiles in the following other directories:<BR>
<UL><BR>
   <LI><A HREF="../95ATFolder/howrey.html"> Antitrust</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95CLFolder/howrey.html"> Commercial Litigation</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95ENVFolder/howrey.html"> Environmental</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95PLFolder/howrey.html"> Product Liability</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95WCCFolder/howrey.html"> White Collar Crime</A>
</UL>

<P><BR>

<P>
<P><B>F</B>ounded in 1956,  Howrey  & Simon has a national and international practice with an emphasis on litigation and government regulation. Our work is supported by Capital Economics,  Capital Accounting,  and Capital Environmental,  affiliates with more than 30 economists,  financial analysts,  and environmental specialists.
<P>
<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Intellectual Property Practice</H3></CENTER>

<P>Howrey  & Simon built its reputation around its capabilities of taking the largest and most complex cases to trial. In the process,  we have developed one of the largest groups of experienced counsel dedicated to litigation in the United States. The intellectual property group is an integral part of our litigation practice.<BR><BR><P>Howrey  & Simon represents clients in patent,  trademark,  copyright,  unfair competition,  trade secret,  and other intellectual property disputes in federal and state courts as well as in contested proceedings before administrative agencies such as the U.S. Patent  & Trademark Office (PTO). Utilizing a `team' approach to staff intellectual property,  and particularly patent,  matters,  we combine the skills of experienced litigators and intellectual property lawyers,  as well as draw on our in-house expertise for economic and accounting skills in the damages phases of litigation. Howrey  & Simon's operations are state-of-the-art in the use of computer-based document management and imaging techniques for both day-to-day case management and at trial.<BR>
<BR><P>Our group handles litigation in all areas of technology,  including complex electronic and computer matters,  pharmaceuticals,  and chemical arts. We have a dynamic biotechnology practice,  headed up by a patent lawyer who is also a Ph.D. molecular biologist.<BR>
<BR><P>Howrey  & Simon lawyers have participated in over 55 of the approximately 350 proceedings before the International Trade Commission under Section 337 in which intellectual property issues have formed the basis for a claim of unfair trade practices. We also have expertise in all areas of trademark litigation,  including Lanham Act actions,  gray market goods,  and proceedings before the Trademark Trial and Appeals Board.<BR>
<BR><P>Howrey  & Simon has advised clients including,  among others,  technology companies in over 100 domestic and international mergers,  acquisitions,  joint ventures,  and tender offers as well as in the intellectual property matters associated with these transactions. This representation includes advocacy practice and negotiations with the Department of Justice or the Federal Trade Commission to obtain clearance of such transactions,  and defending challenges to such transactions filed by a governmental agency or a private party.<BR>
<BR><P>Howrey  & Simon is a leader in the use of alternative dispute resolution techniques,  particularly in intellectual property disputes. Our experience and expertise in ADR enables us to offer clients a complete range of methods for resolving cases in lieu of,  or as a complement to,  traditional litigation. We have successfully used ADR methods as an adjunct to litigation,  resolving specific issues or claims to narrow the disputes in litigation and reduce litigation costs. Our experience enables us to tailor the ADR method to the particular case to achieve the most efficient,  economical,  and effective resolution.<BR>
<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Experience and Clients</H3></CENTER>

<P>In recent patent infringement actions we have represented Apple Computer,  Inc.,  Eastman Kodak Company,  Litton Industries,  Inc.,  The Mead Corporation,  Siemens Corporation,  Block Drug Co.,  Inc.,  Dana Corporation,  and Volvo North America Corp. In recent trademark and unfair competition matters,  we have represented Exxon Corporation,  Inc.,  Anheuser-Busch Companies,  Johnson  & Johnson,  The Prudential Insurance Co. of America,  The Quaker Oats Company,  Calvin Klein Cosmetics Company,  and Schering-Plough Corporation.<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Intellectual Property Partners</H3></CENTER>

<BR><BR><UL><LI><B>James F. Davis</B> (<I>Washington; 202-383-6589</I>) Mr. Davis litigates patent,  trademark and copyright suits,  particularly complex technology matters. Law clerk,  Judge Giles S. Rich,  U.S. Court of Customs and Patent Appeals,  1963-1964; trial judge,  U.S. Court of Claims,  1966-1972. Adjunct professor,  Georgetown University Law Center. University of Illinois,  B.S.,  <I>cum laude</I>,  chemical engineering,  1957; Georgetown University,  J.D.,  1963.<BR><BR><LI><B>Joel M. Freed</B> (<I>Washington; 202-383-6977</I>) Mr. Freed litigates patent,  trademark and copyright suits,  particularly complex technology matters. Adjunct professor,  `Patent,  Trademark,  and Trade Secret Law, ' Georgetown University Law Center,  1975- . Lehigh University,  B.A.,  1965,  B.S.,  mechanical engineering,  1966; Georgetown University,  J.D.,  1970.<BR>
