<HEAD>
<TITLE>Middleton  & Reutlinger
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>Intellectual Property</H2>
<H3>Middleton  & Reutlinger
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>Louisville:</B> 2500 Brown  & Williamson Tower,  Louisville,  KY 40202-3410<BR>
Tel 502-584-1135  <B>*</B>  Fax 502-561-0442  <B>*</B>  E-mail: <A HREF="mailto:jhiggi05@Counsel.Com">jhiggi05@Counsel.Com</A><BR>
<B>New Albany:</B> 2365 Charlestown Road,  New Albany,  IN 47150<BR>
Tel 812-944-7215  <B>*</B>  Fax 812-944-7699<BR>
<BR>
41 lawyers  <B>*</B>  12 lawyers in intellectual property/technology<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>
<P><BR>

<P>
<P><B>M</B>iddleton  & Reutlinger (M &R) is a full-service law firm which traces its roots back to 1854. In 1985,  M &R began its Intellectual Property Practice Group,  and integrated it into the Firm. Today,  M &R's Intellectual Property Group is the largest in a multi-state region. M &R practices the full range of intellectual property and unfair competition law.
<P><BR><P>Our Patent Group (presently five registered patent attorneys) includes practitioners with electrical engineering,  chemical engineering,  ceramic engineering,  and computer science degrees. The Patent Group regularly prepares and prosecutes patent applications before the U.S. Patent  & Trademark Office (PTO) in all major examining groups mechanical,  electrical,  chemical,  computer,  etc. In addition,  our Computer Science Group is fully up-to-date on the fast-breaking field of patent protection for computer programs. And,  with our web of world-wide associate firms,  our clients can receive protection for their inventions in every corner of the world.<BR><P>Our Trademark Group performs the full function of trademark practice clearance counseling,  prosecution in the PTO,  oppositions,  cancellations,  licensing,  franchising,  etc. And,  with our own proprietary docket control program,  we assist our clients in maintaining the longevity of their trademarks. We currently assist many clients in management or their worldwide trademark programs,  such as the famous Louisville Slugger &#174; mark.<BR>
<BR><P>Our Literary/Entertainment Rights Group regularly counsels authors,  entertainers,  and literary agents in obtaining,  exploiting,  and enforcing copyright and right of publicity rights. Among our current clients are an author whose book is being made into a major motion picture,  and The Memphis Mafia,  who are on a nationwide tour with their book reminiscing on their many years with Elvis Presley. Our past clients have included The Grateful Dead &#174; and perhaps Louisville's most famous contemporary citizen,  Muhammad Ali.<BR>
<BR><P>Our Litigation Group is active in technology/intellectual property matters. We practice all types of infringement litigation patent,  trademark,  copyright,  trade secret,  and computers regionally,  and nationwide. We recently obtained a $28 million-plus patent infringement judgment in a ceramic engineering technology case,  obtained a trademark injunction for a sporting goods client against a national competitor,  and regularly deal in all types of technology cases.<BR>
<BR><P>Uniquely,  all core members of our IP Group have real world,  private industry experience prior to their legal careers.<BR>
<BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>James R. Higgins,  Jr.</B> Head,  Intellectual Property Practice Group; registered patent attorney; 14 years' engineering experience with Fortune 100 company; appeared before U.S. Courts of Appeals for the Fifth,  Sixth,  and Federal Circuits,  Trademark Trial and Appeal Board,  and many U.S. district and state courts; adjunct professor,  intellectual property law,  University of Louisville. Alfred University,  B.S.,  ceramic engineering; University of Louisville,  J.D.,  <I>cum laude</I>.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Charles G. Middleton III</B> Managing partner; unfair competition and trade secret litigation. University of Virginia,  B.A.; University of Kentucky,  J.D.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Charles G. Lamb</B> Registered patent attorney; holds over 50 patents world-wide; was patent and licensing counsel for a multibillion-dollar corporation,  managing international patent and trademark portfolio; personally argued patentability cases in foreign courts,  including European Patent Office. University of Tennessee,  B.S.,  Chem.E.; University of Louisville,  J.D.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>O. Grant Bruton</B> The firm's senior litigator of unfair trade practice cases; recently led a trade delegation to Mexico where that delegation was hosted by his brother,  executive vice-president of the American Chamber of Commerce of Mexico. Princeton University,  B.A.; Harvard University,  J.D.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>James E. Millman</B> Litigation,  unfair competition,  and business cases; has argued cases before the U.S. Supreme Court,  the U.S. Court of Appeals for the Federal and Sixth Circuits,  and many district and state courts. University of Notre Dame,  B.A.; University of Louisville,  J.D.,  <I>magna cum laude</I>.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Amy B. Berge</B> Trademark prosecution and litigation; prior experience in merchandising. Auburn University,  B.A.; University of Louisville,  J.D.,  <I>magna cum laude</I>.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>James C. Eaves,  Jr.</B> Registered patent attorney; 20 years as Air Force communications officer; patent prosecution and litigation,  electronics and communications. University of Kentucky,  B.S.,  B.S.E.E.; University of Louisville,  J.D.,  <I>cum laude</I>.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>David W. Carrithers</B> Registered patent attorney; prior experience in distillery,  food technology,  and plastics industries; patent and trademark prosecution. University of Virginia,  M.Chem.E.; Northern Kentucky University,  J.D.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Augustus S. Herbert</B> Litigation,  unfair competition/business,  trade secret cases. University of Notre Dame,  B.A.; University of Virginia,  J.D.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Dennis D. Murrell</B> Franchising,  UFOC; litigation,  covenant-not-to-compete,  and trade secrets. University of Kentucky,  B.A.; University of Cincinnati,  J.D.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Thomas P. O'Brien III</B> Litigation,  patent,  trade secrets,  trademark,  and franchising; law clerk to Judge Frederick D. Stamp,  U.S. District Court for the Northern District of West Virginia. Washington  & Lee University,  B.S.,  J.D.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>John F. Salazar</B> Registered patent attorney; prior experience as systems engineer for IBM Corporation at Johnson Space Center; patent prosecution,  electrical and computer science arts. University of Louisville,  B.S.,  computer science and electrical engineering,  M.B.A.,  J.D.
</UL>


