<HEAD>
<TITLE>Pennie  & Edmonds
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>Intellectual Property</H2>
<H3>Pennie  & Edmonds
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>New York:</B> 1155 Avenue of the Americas,  New York,  NY 10036<BR>
Tel 212-790-9090  <B>*</B>  Fax 212-869-9741<BR>
<B>Washington:</B> 1667 K Street,  N.W.,  Suite 1000,  Washington,  DC 20006<BR>
Tel 202-496-4400  <B>*</B>  Fax 202-496-4444<BR>
<B>Menlo Park:</B> 2730 Sand Hill Road,  Menlo Park,  CA 94025<BR>
Tel 415-854-3660  <B>*</B>  Fax 415-854-3694<BR>
<BR>
160 lawyers  <B>*</B>  All lawyers practice intellectual property law<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>
<P><BR>

<P>
<P><B>P</B>ennie  & Edmonds is one of America's oldest and largest national,  full-service law firms practicing exclusively in the areas of intellectual property and technology-related law. Our practice includes patents,  trademarks,  copyrights,  computer law,  trade secrets,  licensing,  technology transfers,  and related counseling and litigations. In addition,  we provide general counseling and financing expertise to start-up enterprises. Clients range from individual inventors to major universities and many of the world's largest corporations.
<P><BR><P>Founded in 1884,  the firm has since grown to include 160 practitioners in offices located in New York City,  Washington,  D.C.,  and Menlo Park,  California,  who service the needs of clients throughout the world. Many of our lawyers hold advanced degrees in such disciplines as the biological sciences,  chemistry,  electrical and mechanical engineering,  metallurgy,  and physics,  as well as economics,  accounting,  and business.<BR><P>Pennie  & Edmonds is organized into practice groups that tailor services to meet the business objectives of clients in specific industries. This approach focuses on the business realities of intellectual property.<BR>
<BR><P>Representative clients include companies in the chemical,  pharmaceutical,  biotechnology,  electronics,  computer sciences,  consumer and industrial products,  and financial services industries.<BR>
<BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>S. Leslie Misrock</B> Primarily litigation and appellate patent practice,  specializing in biotechnology and chemical cases. Joined Pennie  & Edmonds,  1955. Massachusetts Institute of Technology,  S.B.,  chemistry,  1955; Columbia University,  A.M.,  chemistry,  1956; Fordham University,  LL.B.,  1959; Niagara University,  Sc.D.h.c.,  1987. Admitted in New York,  1960.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Harry C. Jones III</B> Primarily prosecution practice with some patent litigation,  specializing in mechanical engineering cases. Registered to practice before U.S. Patent and Trademark Office. Joined Pennie  & Edmonds,  1961. Yale University,  B.S.,  industrial engineering,  1957; George Washington University,  J.D.,  1961. Admitted in the District of Columbia,  1961; and New York,  1962.<BR><BR>
