<BR>
<LI><B>Jonathan A. Marshall</B> Primarily patent and copyright litigation with some prosecution practice,  specializing in electronics,  computer science,  automotive,  and mechanical cases. Registered to practice before U.S. Patent and Trademark Office. Joined Pennie  & Edmonds,  1966. Lehigh University,  B.S.,  mechanical engineering,  1961; New York University,  J.D.,  1964. Admitted in New York,  1964; U.S. Supreme Court,  1974; U.S. Courts of Appeals for the Second (1969),  Third (1980),  Seventh (1973),  Ninth (1990) and Federal (1983) Circuits; and U.S. District Courts for the Southern District (1967) and Eastern District (1974) of New York and the Northern District of California (1985).<BR>
<BR>
