<TITLE>Polster,  Lieder,  Woodruff  & Lucchesi
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>Intellectual Property</H2>
<H3>Polster,  Lieder,  Woodruff  & Lucchesi
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>St. Louis:</B> 763 South New Ballas Road,  St. Louis,  MO 63141<BR>
Tel 314-872-8118  <B>*</B>  Fax 314-991-2178<BR>
<B>Louisville:</B> 2303 Tuckaho Road,  Louisville,  KY 40207<BR>
Tel 502-895-4672<BR>
<BR>
18 lawyers  <B>*</B>  All lawyers in intellectual property<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>
<P>
<P>
<P><B>P</B>olster,  Lieder,  Woodruff  & Lucchesi has a history of over one hundred years of continuous service in the field of patents,  trademarks,  copyrights,  licensing,  and intellectual property litigation.
<P><BR><P>All members of the firm are totally committed to their clients,  and uniquely positioned to serve them. The firm has technical strengths in electrical,  electronic,  computer,  biological,  pharmaceutical,  mechanical,  and chemical fields. The firm also has worldwide,  in-depth trademark experience,  international expertise in the protection of intellectual property rights,  and an extensive litigation practice.<BR><P>Sixteen of the firm's attorneys are registered to practice before the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office.<BR>
<BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>Philip B. Polster</B> Patent preparation and prosecution,  domestic and foreign; counseling in intellectual property matters. Washington University,  J.D.,  1948.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Frederick M. Woodruff</B> Patent preparation and prosecution,  domestic and foreign; counseling in intellectual property matters. St. Louis City College of Law,  LL. B.,  1941.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>J. Philip Polster</B> Patent preparation and prosecution,  domestic and foreign; counseling in intellectual property matters. Washington University,  J.D.,  1967.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Lionel L. Lucchesi</B> Intellectual property counseling,  licensing,  prosecution,  and litigation before federal and state courts and agencies. Electrical,  electronic,  and electrical mechanical background. St. Louis University,  J.D.,  1969.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>William G. Bruns</B> U.S. and foreign patent,  trademark,  copyright,  and trade secret counseling,  licensing,  and litigation before state and federal courts and agencies. Background: chemical engineering,  food chemistry. Washington University,  J.D.,  1958.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Edward A. Boeschenstein</B> Patent and trademark counseling,  contested proceedings before the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office,  preparation of patent applications primarily on mechanical inventions,  and licensing. Washington University,  J.D.,  1962.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>William B. Cunningham,  Jr.</B> Patent counseling,  prosecution of U.S. and foreign patent applications,  patent litigation before federal courts and U.S. Patent and Trademark Office,  and licensing and marketing of inventions and technology. Background: mechanical engineering. St. Louis University,  J.D.,  1970.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Gregory E. UPChurch</B> Protecting computer-based and medical inventions before the courts and in the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office. Yale Law School,  J.D.,  1975. Admitted in Missouri and New York.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Michael Kovac</B> Patent and trademark counseling,  acquisition,  licensing,  and litigation before state and federal courts. George Washington University,  J.D.,  1963. Admitted in Illinois and Missouri.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>J. Joseph Muller</B> Patent and trademark counseling,  acquisition,  licensing,  and litigation before state and federal courts. Patent preparation in the electronic,  electrical,  electromechanical,  and mechanical arts. Washington University,  J.D.,  1975.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>McPherson D. Moore</B> Litigation,  counseling,  and licensing for patent,  trademark,  copyright,  trade secret,  and unfair competition matters. Preparation and prosecution of U.S. and foreign patent and trademark applications. University of Arkansas,  J.D.,  1974.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Martha A. Michaels</B> Intellectual property counseling,  licensing,  prosecution,  and litigation before federal and state courts and agencies. Chemical and general background. University of Indiana at Indianapolis,  J.D.,  1973.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Ralph B. Brick</B> (<I>Louisville</I>) Preparation and prosecution of patent,  trademark,  and copyright applications,  and counseling,  primarily in the mechanical,  electromechanical,  and environmental arts. Washington University,  J.D.,  1948. Admitted in Kentucky,  Missouri,  and the District of Columbia.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Richard J. Sher</B> Patent preparation and prosecution,  domestic and foreign; counseling in intellectual property matters. George Washington University,  J.D.,  1974. Admitted in Virginia and Missouri.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Jonathan P. Soifer</B> Preparation and prosecution of patent and trademark applications,  including patentability and availability search as well as patent,  trademark,  and copyright counseling and litigation. Washington University,  J.D.,  1989.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Ned W. Randle</B> Preparation of patent applications; pharmaceutical and medical device inventions; litigation in all areas of intellectual property; FDA and drug regulatory matters. St. Louis University,  J.D.,  1991. Admitted in Missouri and Illinois.<BR>
