Tel 612-349-8500  <B>*</B>  Fax 612-339-4181<BR>
<B>Other offices:</B> Atlanta,  Boston,  Chicago,  Costa Mesa (California),  Los Angeles, <BR>
San Francisco,  Washington,  D.C.<BR>
<BR>
230 lawyers  <B>*</B>  45 lawyers in intellectual property law<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>See this firm's profile in the following other directory:<BR>
<UL><BR>
   <LI><A HREF="../95CLFolder/robins.html"> Commercial Litigation</A>
</UL>

<P>
<P>
<P><B>R</B>obins,  Kaplan,  Miller  & Ciresi is a national litigation and business practice firm.
<P>
<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Intellectual Property Law Group</H3></CENTER>

<P>Our group consists primarily of trial attorneys with a broad range of trial experience transcending intellectual property issues. This broad experience is essential given the continually expanding scope of intellectual property litigation to include antitrust,  unfair competition,  wrongful termination,  employment law,  and,  at times,  even RICO claims. We have practiced in the intellectual property area since the inception of our business litigation practice,  but in recent years our intellectual property work has become more intense and extensive.<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Experience and Clients</H3></CENTER>

<P>In the wide-ranging area of intellectual property litigation,  we have represented plaintiffs and defendants located throughout the country in courts located throughout the country. In addition we have represented foreign companies,  including Canadian companies,  in U.S. litigation. The claims involved in these cases include patent,  trademark,  copyright,  and trade secret infringement. Moreover,  since intellectual property disputes often arise in the employment context,  our background in handling employment disputes (including trade secret,  employment,  and noncompete agreements) has proved invaluable.<BR><P>We handle the complex intellectual property problems of some of the country's largest companies,  such as Honeywell's patent litigation regarding autofocus camera technologies. The firm has represented intellectual property clients in high-tech industries such as electronics,  telecommunications,  computer software development,  cable television,  medical imaging,  and biomedical,  as well as other fields including the food and beverage industry,  personal services,  publishing,  military weapons and vehicles,  automotive design,  the music and entertainment industry and the design and manufacture of miscellaneous consumer goods.<BR>
<BR><P>The firm's intellectual property clients include Alliant Techsystems Inc.,  American Business Information Inc.,  Canadian Electronics Ltd.,  Fonar Corporation,  Harris Waste Management Group,  Honeywell,  Inc.,  Hollander Inc.,  NordicTrack,  Pitney-Bowes,  UNOCAL,  Veritec Corporation,  and W.R. Grace  & Co. The cases we have handled for these clients have included such expected claims as patent,  trademark,  and copyright infringement,  but have also included Lanham Act,  RICO,  and antitrust violations. The subject matters of these cases include military weapons,  cellular batteries,  camera technology,  electronic musical instruments,  computer software,  and automotive vehicles. Our Intellectual Property group includes the following attorneys;<BR>
<BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>Michael V. Ciresi</B> Lead trial attorney in the <I>Honeywell </I>v.<I> Minolta</I> autofocus patent infringement case. Extensive experience in complex general litigation worldwide.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>James L. Harlow</B> Emphasizes intellectual property litigation,  licensing,  and counseling. Subject matters include patents,  copyrights,  trademarks,  and trade secrets in product categories ranging from computers and military weapons to cameras and food products.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Elliot S. Kaplan</B> Focuses upon antitrust,  trade regulation,  intellectual property,  and securities matters,  having tried copyright,  trademark,  securities,  and unfair trade practice cases in several courts and states.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Martin R. Lueck</B> Specializes in intellectual property trials and complex business disputes,  including intellectual property,  commercial disputes,  and engineering failures. Co-lead counsel for the plaintiff in <I>Fonar </I>v.<I> General Electric</I>.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Ronald J. Schutz</B> A registered patent attorney with extensive experience in intellectual property litigation as well as environmental litigation and general business litigation. Co-lead counsel for the plaintiff in <I>Fonar </I>v.<I> General Electric</I>.<BR>
<BR>
