l litigation and corporate practice groups. This combination offers clients the depth and experience of a boutique firm with the resources and support only a large law firm can provide.<BR><BR><P>In litigation matters,  our intellectual property attorneys act as counsel in state and federal trial and appellate courts,  and draw from other lawyers in the commercial litigation practice group as a case may require. Our attorneys assist clients in prosecuting and defending trademark infringement and counterfeiting cases,  patent infringement and trade secret lawsuits,  copyright infringement and false advertising actions,  and lawsuits to enforce restrictive covenants. Examples of recent engagements include:<BR><BR><UL><P><LI> defending patent and trade secret lawsuits concerning machine tools,  medical instruments,  food products,  and food processing technology;<BR><BR><P><LI> defending a copyright infringement and false advertising action in connection with television commercials;<BR><BR><P><LI> prosecuting a false advertising and unfair competition action involving environmental and product performance claims; and<BR><BR><P><LI> prosecuting a trademark infringement and counterfeiting action relating to the sale of firefighters' rescue tools. <BR></UL><BR><P>We also recognize that disputes need to be resolved as quickly and economically as possible,  and we assist our clients in resolving disputes outside of court using effective settlement and alternative dispute resolution techniques in connection with claims of patent and trademark infringement,  copyright infringement,  and counterfeiting of various artists' works.<BR><BR><P>Our attorneys also assist our clients in developing and exploiting intellectual property by counseling them about the nature and extent of intellectual property protection available to them. We prepare and prosecute patent,  trademark,  and copyright applications in the United States and abroad,  and assist in business transactions involving the licensing or transfer of intellectual property rights. Our intellectual property lawyers also draw on the experience of our business lawyers for assistance in corporate and transactional matters. Some examples of matters we have handled include:<BR><BR><UL><P><LI> negotiating and drafting agreements to license and transfer trademark rights,  including due diligence investigations and trademark portfolio appraisals;<BR><BR><P><LI> working with local counsel in foreign countries to obtain and enforce trademark and patent rights for domestic clients;<BR><BR><P><LI> negotiating and drafting technology development,  confidentiality,  employment,  and licensing agreements;<BR><BR><P><LI> creating trade secret protection programs;<BR><BR><P><LI> negotiating and drafting agreements for the development,  transfer,  and licensing of copyrighted works,  including recording and publishing contracts,  video production agreements,  permissions to publish,  art reproduction agreements,  and music synchronization licenses;<BR><BR><P><LI> counseling clients on the preparation and registration of contests,  sweepstakes,  and promotions in both regulated and nonregulated industries,  including drafting sweepstakes rules and reviewing coupon,  rebate,  and other consumer offers;<BR><BR><P><LI> counseling on antitrust implications of agreements or conduct related to the exploitation of intellectual property rights.<BR></UL><BR><P>Some of the Seyfarth,  Shaw lawyers who work extensively in the Firm's intellectual property practice are:<BR><BR><LI><B>Alan L. Unikel</B> (<I>Chicago</I>) is the chair of the Firm's commercial litigation and intellectual property groups. He is involved in counseling and litigating intellectual property matters,  including patents,  trademarks,  copyrights,  trade secrets,  and unfair competition. He is registered to practice as a patent attorney before the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office.<BR><BR><LI><B>Michael R. Levinson</B> (<I>Chicago</I>) focuses his practice on commercial litigation and intellectual property matters. He has litigated numerous intellectual property matters in state and federal courts,  including trademark and trade dress infringement,  theft of trade secrets,  antitrust,  and patent infringement.<BR><BR><BR><BR></UL></BODY></HTML>
