<HEAD>
<TITLE>Smith Helms Mulliss & Moore,  L.L.P.
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>Intellectual Property</H2>
<H3>Smith Helms Mulliss & Moore,  L.L.P.
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>Charlotte:</B> 227 North Tryon Street,  Charlotte,  NC 28202<BR>
Tel 704-343-2000  <B>*</B>  Fax 704-334-8467<B><BR>
Greensboro:</B> 300 North Greene Street,  Greensboro,  NC 27401<BR>
Tel 910-378-5200  <B>*</B>  Fax 910-379-9558<BR>
<B>Raleigh:</B> 316 West Edenton Street,  Raleigh,  NC 27603<BR>
Tel 919-755-8700  <B>*</B>  Fax 919-828-7938<BR>
<BR>
148 lawyers  <B>*</B>  18 lawyers in intellectual property<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>See this firm's profiles in the following other directories:<BR>
<UL><BR>
   <LI><A HREF="../95CLFolder/smith.html"> Commercial Litigation</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95PLFolder/smith.html"> Product Liability</A>
</UL>

<P>
<P>
<P><B>S</B>mith Helms Mulliss  & Moore was created in 1986 by the merger of two prominent North Carolina law firms with roots going back to 1919. With offices in North Carolina's three major metropolitan areas,  the firm maintains a statewide presence and also provides its clients with regional and national representation. One of the largest law firms based in the Carolinas,  the firm's practice groups offer a complete range of legal services to its clients.
<P>
<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Intellectual Property Practice</H3></CENTER>

<P>Our firm and its predecessors have for many years represented clients in all aspects of intellectual property practice,  with the exception of patent prosecution.<BR><P>We counsel clients about the protection and distribution of intellectual property rights,  including employment and independent contractor issues,  trade secret protection,  registration of trademarks and copyrights,  intellectual property audits,  infringement avoidance,  procedures to maximize protection,  international protection and licensing,  and corporate form and financing arrangements. We draft,  negotiate,  and review agreements involving licensing of intellectual property rights,  technology transfer,  distribution,  dealership or franchise arrangements,  joint ventures,  confidentiality,  employment and noncompetition restrictions,  revenue recognition and tax implications,  and software development and distribution.<BR>
<BR><P>Our litigation practice includes acting as principal or local counsel in all types of infringement disputes; working to obtain injunctions and seizure orders in federal and state courts; appearing before the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office,  the U.S. Copyright Office,  and the U.S. Court of Appeals for the Federal Circuit; and representing plaintiffs or defendants in state and federal court actions involving software licensing,  computer system performance,  trade secrets,  technology ownership,  unfair competition,  employment issues,  and contract interpretation and performance. We promote the usage of alternative dispute resolution methods.<BR>
<BR><P>Representative clients: Automatic Data Processing,  Inc.; Becton Dickinson and Co.; First Data Corp.; Health Systems Group; Kayser Roth Hosiery,  Inc.; Precision Fabrics,  Inc.; Recording Industry Association of America; R.R. Donnelley  & Sons; Stockhausen,  Inc.; Vanguard Cellular Systems,  Inc.<BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>E. Osborne Ayscue,  Jr.</B> (<I>Charlotte; 704-343-2058</I>) Intellectual property litigation,  including patent,  trade secret,  and unfair competition disputes. University of North Carolina,  J.D.,  1960.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>E. Kent Auberry</B> (<I>Greensboro; 910-378-5284</I>) Corporate and intellectual property counseling; trademark registration and opposition; copyright registration. University of North Carolina,  J.D.,  1982.<BR>
