<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Apruzzese,  McDermott,  Mastro  & Murphy
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>Labor</H2>
<H3>Apruzzese,  McDermott,  Mastro  & Murphy
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>Liberty Corner:</B> 25 Independence Boulevard,  P.O. Box 112,  Liberty Corner,  NJ 07938<BR>
Tel 908-580-1776  <B>*</B>  Fax 908-647-1492<BR>
<BR>
15 lawyers  <B>*</B>  13 lawyers practicing in labor and employment law<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>
<P>
<P>
<P><B>F</B>ounded in 1965,  Apruzzese,  McDermott,  Mastro  & Murphy provides a full range of labor and employment law services to management. These services include representation in union organizational campaigns; the conduct of negotiations; representation before the National Labor Relations Board,  state agencies,  and the courts; acting as counsel in arbitration proceedings; and general advice with regard to personnel policies and practices,  contract management,  and administration. The firm has extensive experience in the construction,  pharmaceutical,  banking,  airline,  and health care industries. It also represents public entities in collective bargaining,  interest and grievance arbitrations,  and litigation before the Public Employment Relations Commission.
<P><BR><P>In employment law,  the firm represents management before the Equal Employment Opportunity Commission,  the Division on Civil Rights,  and in the courts in matters involving wrongful termination,  discrimination,  sexual harassment,  and torts arising from the employment relationship. Its principals and associates lecture extensively on the subject of labor and employment law and are actively involved in sections of the American Bar Association and New Jersey State Bar Association devoted to this area of the law.<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Labor Law</H3></CENTER>

<P>The firm brings many years of experience to the field of labor law. In addition to the representation of corporate clients in all phases of labor law,  it has represented national employer organizations such as the U.S. and New Jersey chambers of commerce,  the Edison Electric Institute,  Associated General Contractors of America,  and others before the U.S. Supreme Court in cases involving antitrust labor law issues,  striker benefits,  strike replacements,  secondary boycotts,  and reverse discrimination. The firm's principals and associates include several attorneys who have formerly worked in the legal departments of major corporations and with the National Labor Relations Board.<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Employment Law</H3></CENTER>

<P>The firm is very active in the litigation of wrongful discharge cases,  violations of the New Jersey Law Against Discrimination,  the federal Civil Rights Act,  sexual harassment cases,  and cases arising under state and federal laws prohibiting discrimination against the physically and mentally handicapped. Its philosophy is to help employers avoid such claims by working closely with management and in-house counsel in adopting and modifying policies to assure compliance with state and federal statutes,  and in providing instruction for all ranks of supervision and management in the complex and changing dictates of employment law. Principals and associates of the firm have written extensively in this area of the law and on the subject of alternative dispute resolution as a means of avoiding litigation.<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Representative Clients</H3></CENTER>

<P>Apruzzese,  McDermott,  Mastro  & Murphy represents a wide range of clients,  including First Fidelity Bancorporation,  Public Service Electric  & Gas Company,  General Public Utilities,  Prudential Insurance Company,  Jersey Central Power  & Light Company,  Warner-Lambert Company,  Schering-Plough,  Combustion Engineering,  Inc.,  Foster Wheeler Corporation,  and Forbes,  Inc.<BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>Vincent J. Apruzzese</B> Mr. Apruzzese is a former chair of the Labor and Employment Law Section of the ABA. He is a member of the U.S. Chamber of Commerce Labor Committee and has been a principal witness for the chamber before committees of Congress. He is a former president of the New Jersey State Bar Association and past chairman of its Labor Law Section. He is also a member of the American College of Trial Lawyers. Rutgers University,  A.B.,  1950; University of Pennsylvania Law School,  J.D.,  1953.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Francis A. Mastro</B> Prior to joining Apruzzese  & McDermott,  Mr. Mastro was a supervising attorney and litigator with the National Labor Relations Board,  and in-house labor counsel to the Ingersoll-Rand Company. He is a former chair of the Labor Law Section of the New Jersey State Bar Association. St. Peter's College,  B.S.,  1951; Georgetown University,  J.D.,  1954.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Richard C. Mariani</B> Mr. Mariani heads the firm's employment law and litigation section,  and is a member of the Equal Employment Opportunity Law Committee of the American Bar Association and the Labor and Employment Law and Aviation Law Sections of the New Jersey State Bar Association. He has lectured extensively and authored many articles on employment law topics. Boston College,  A.B.,  1968; Villanova University,  J.D.,  1973.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Frank X. McDermott</B> Mr. McDermott is of counsel to the firm and continues to be active in labor and employment matters. Mr. McDermott has held various leadership positions in both the New Jersey General Assembly and Senate. He was chairman of Governor Kean's Select Committee on the Office of Administrative Law Judges,  and now acts as legislative advisor to several corporations. Columbia University,  B.A.,  1949; New York University,  M.B.A.,  1953,  LL.M.,  1961.
</UL>


</UL></BODY>
