<P>
<P><B>E</B>stablished in 1893,  Alston  & Bird is proud of its history of anticipating and solving the broad range of issues encountered by its clients on a daily basis.
<P>
<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Product Liability Practice</H3></CENTER>

<P>Alston  & Bird is regularly engaged in a variety of product liability litigation cases involving many different products,  including medical products and devices,  pharmaceuticals,  chemicals,  machinery,  motor vehicles and equipment,  marine equipment,  airplanes,  food products,  and household products. This group of experienced trial lawyers has represented more manufacturers and distributors in large,  multiple-plaintiff cases than any other large firm in the Southeast.<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Medical Products  & Services Litigation</H3></CENTER>

<P>Alston  & Bird has attained a high degree of success in the courtroom and a solid reputation for professional excellence widely recognized in corporate and hospital board rooms. In the area of pharmaceutical products,  medical devices,  and medical equipment,  we have considerable experience serving as local,  regional,  and national counsel. We have represented various manufacturers and have handled not only personal injury cases,  but also product performance cases involving breach of contract and breach of warranty claims which arise in the context of the sale of sophisticated medical instruments and equipment.<BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>G. Conley Ingram</B> Mr. Ingram is a former Justice of the Supreme Court of Georgia and a member of the American College of Trial Lawyers,  the International Society of Barristers,  and the American Academy of Appellate Lawyers. His extensive trial and appellate practice includes numerous product liability matters. He has received several awards including the Tradition of Excellence Award from the General Practice and Trial Section of the State Bar of Georgia. Mr. Ingram also serves as a member of the Southeast Panel of JAMS/Endispute and is active in all forms of alternative dispute resolution. Emory University,  LL.B,  1951.<BR><BR><LI><B>Ronald L. Reid</B> Mr. Reid has represented a variety of clients in product liability litigation in,  among others areas,  medical products and devices,  pharmaceuticals,  household products,  amusement rides,  and marine products. Mr. Reid is a member of the American College of Trial Lawyers and a former Atlanta Bar Association President. Emory University,  J.D.,  1963.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Dow N. Kirkpatrick II</B> Mr. Kirkpatrick has served as counsel for major manufacturers in product liability cases involving agricultural chemicals and equipment,  pharmaceuticals,  and medical devices. He is a member of the Defense Research Institute. Before joining Alston  & Bird in 1972,  Mr. Kirkpatrick served as law clerk to Judge Newell Edenfield,  United States District Court for the Northern District of Georgia. University of Georgia,  J.D.,  1969.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Robert D. McCallum,  Jr.</B> Mr. McCallum has represented a variety of clients in real estate litigation (including eminent domain),  insurance regulation litigation and administrative proceedings,  bank-related litigation,  medical malpractice defense,  and general commercial litigation. After joining Alston  & Bird in 1973,  Mr. McCallum was designated as a special assistant attorney general for the State of Georgia and served in that capacity from 1979 to 1987. Yale University,  J.D.,  1973.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Jack H. Senterfitt</B> Mr. Senterfitt is a member of the Litigation Section of the State Bar of Georgia and the National Association of Railroad Trial Counsel (NARTC),  is the Southeast regional vice-president of NARTC,  serves on the National Executive Committee of NARTC,  and is on the Emory University faculty of the National Institute for Trial Advocacy Program. Mr. Senterfitt has represented a variety of clients in general litigation,  focusing on all types of railroad litigation and product liability defense. Vanderbilt University,  J.D.,  1974.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Judson Graves</B> Mr. Graves has represented a variety of clients in general litigation including medical malpractice and other insurance defense,  media law,  and various types of commercial litigation. He also acts as national and regional medical malpractice counsel to various health care providers. Mr. Graves is a frequent speaker on medical malpractice defense. Emory University,  J.D.,  1975.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Jay D. Bennett</B> Mr. Bennett has served as counsel for American and foreign manufacturers in product liability cases,  aviation litigation,  and agribusiness litigation throughout the United States since 1977. He is the chair of the Trial Practice Group at Alston  & Bird and a member of the Trial Attorneys of America,  a nationwide group of manufacturers and attorneys focusing on product liability issues across the United States. Harvard University,  J.D.,  <I>cum laude</I>,  1977.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Bernard Taylor</B> Mr. Taylor is chair of the Medical Products and Services Practice Group at Alston  & Bird. He concentrates on product liability and medical malpractice defense litigation and alternative dispute resolution. He is a member of the Georgia Commission on Dispute Resolution and is a frequent speaker on programs relating to commercial litigation,  product liability,  medical malpractice defense,  and health care issues. He also acts as national and regional medical malpractice counsel for various health care providers. Vanderbilt University,  J.D.,  1982.
