<P>
<P><B>B</B>oehl Stopher  & Graves is one of the oldest firms in the State of Kentucky,  until recently existing under the name of Boehl Stopher Graves  & Deindoerfer. Boehl Stopher  & Graves' growth has been generated internally rather than though merger or acquisition. Over the past 20 years,  Boehl Stopher  & Graves has represented national and international clients in product liability litigation. While we represent our clients in many fields,  including commercial matters,  contracts,  and workers' compensation litigation,  a large part of our practice is devoted to the defense of product liability claims. Our practice in the field of product liability includes aviation and automotive matters,  pharmaceuticals,  breast implants,  farm equipment,  machinery,  aircraft,  asbestos,  food products,  and other claims regarding consumer and industrial equipment.
<P><BR><P>Boehl Stopher  & Graves brings considerable background and expertise to this area of our practice. Three active members of the firm are fellows in the American College of Trial Lawyers. Several of our members have served on various committees,  including the Board of Governors of the ABA,  Federal Judicial Committee of the ABA,  Sixth Circuit Advisory Committee,  and the Kentucky Supreme Court Rules Committee. Our civil litigation experience includes not only the defense of individual personal injury and product liability matters,  but also the defense of class action lawsuits resulting from aircraft accidents,  train derailments,  and mass liability matters.<BR><P>Regardless of the complexity of a case,  Boehl Stopher  & Graves works closely with corporate clients and their staffs. Communication between those attorneys responsible for handling a claim and our clients is of paramount importance to us. A representative sampling of our nationally known corporate clients includes Ford Motor Company,  CSX Transportation,  Inc.,  Kawasaki Motor Corporation,  Eli Lilly and Company,  Bristol-Myers Squibb Company,  AlliedSignal Inc.,  Champion International,  Rockwell,  Chrysler Corporation,  Case Corporation,  Coca-Cola Bottling Company,  W.R. Grace  & Company,  and Navistar International.<BR>
<BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>Edward H. Stopher</B> is the contact for the firm and is a member of the three-person executive committee that manages Boehl Stopher  & Graves. Mr. Stopher's professional associations include: fellow,  American College of Trial Lawyers; National Association of Railroad Trial Counsel; member,  Civil Rules Committee for the U.S. Court of Appeals for the Sixth Circuit (1984-1990); life member,  Sixth Circuit Judicial Conference; and the Kentucky Bar Association's Supreme Court Civil Rules Committee. Mr. Stopher is listed in <I>The Best Lawyers in America</I> (1989-1994). He represents manufacturers in product liability suits,  including companies involved in the manufacturing of aircraft components,  machinery,  and agricultural equipment. Davidson College,  1965; University of Virginia Law School,  J.D.,  1968. Admitted in Kentucky,  U.S. Supreme Court,  U.S. Court of Appeals for the Sixth Circuit,  and U.S. District Courts for the Eastern and Western Districts of Kentucky.<BR>
</UL>


