<TITLE>Bronson,  Bronson & McKinnon
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>Product Liability</H2>
<H3>Bronson,  Bronson & McKinnon
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>San Francisco:</B> 505 Montgomery Street,  San Francisco,  CA 94111<BR>
Tel 415-986-4200  <B>*</B>  Fax 415-982-1394<BR>
<B>Other offices:</B> Los Angeles,  San Jose<BR>
<BR>
140 lawyers  <B>*</B>  22 lawyers in Product Liability Group<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>See this firm's profiles in the following other directories:<BR>
<UL><BR>
   <LI><A HREF="../95CLFolder/bronson.html"> Commercial Litigation</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95IPFolder/bronson.html"> Intellectual Property</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95LABFolder/bronson.html"> Labor</A>
</UL>

<P>
<P>
<P><B>B</B>ronson,  Bronson  & McKinnon is one of the West Coast's leading product liability litigation firms. For more than 75 years,  Bronson trial lawyers have maintained an exceptional winning record before judges and juries. Today,  our product liability lawyers continue that proud tradition,  regularly defending manufacturers and distributors in trials conducted in California and across the country. Because of the depth,  variety,  and national scope of our trial experience,  we are also called upon by our clients to supervise product liability litigation throughout the United States. As a result,  our lawyers have developed rarely found expertise in implementing and coordinating national defense strategies,  and our clients have enjoyed the assurance that their cases will be properly prepared and skillfully tried,  regardless of venue.
<P><BR><P>We have had considerable experience defending manufacturers and distributors of a wide variety of products,  including: aircraft,  automobiles,  buses,  trucks,  industrial equipment,  grape harvesters,  power tools,  printing presses,  lift trucks,  scaffolds,  aerial work platforms,  firearms,  disposable cigarette lighters,  bicycles,  home appliances,  exercise equipment,  furniture,  chemicals,  petroleum products,  drugs,  medical devices,  blood products,  foods,  and beverages.<BR><P>Representative clients include Alpha Therapeutics Corporation; American Airlines; BIC Corporation; The Cessna Aircraft Co.; Cincinnati Incorporated; Crown Equipment Corporation; E.I. du Pont de Nemours  & Company; Giant Bicycle,  Inc.; The Goodyear Tire  & Rubber Company; Gulfstream Aerospace Corporation; Heidelberg Harris Inc.; Hobart Corporation; and UpRight,  Inc.<BR>
<BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>Edwin W. Green</B> (<I>Los Angeles; 213-627-2000</I>) has tried over 300 cases to verdict. He has been responsible for managing worldwide tort litigation for major aircraft companies,  and he has tried cases involving mass aviation disasters. Mr. Green has acted as lead counsel in cases taken to verdict in California and throughout the United States. He has supervised counsel in cases throughout the U.S. as well as in Australia,  Germany,  and England.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Robert C. Gebhardt</B> (<I>San Francisco; 415-986-4200</I>) has tried over 40 cases to verdict. They include a variety of product liability and commercial matters. He has served as national counsel for an aircraft manufacturer,  and as regional counsel for a pharmaceutical company and a lighter manufacturer.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Thomas H. Sloan,  Jr.</B> (<I>San Francisco; 415-986-4200</I>) has tried over 50 cases to jury verdict involving product liability,  construction accidents,  railroad accidents,  general personal injury,  and commercial disputes.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Mary Eileen Reilley</B> (<I>San Francisco; 415-986-4200</I>) was appointed chair of the firm's Product Liability and Toxic Torts Practice Group in 1993. In addition to her extensive trial experience involving a wide variety of industrial and consumer products,  she advises companies on risk management issues,  preventive product liability measures,  labeling issues,  and coordinated litigation strategy.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Bonnie R. Cohen</B> (<I>San Francisco; 415-986-4200</I>) has been a partner in the firm's Product Liability and Toxic Torts Practice Group since 1986. Her trial practice focuses on product liability,  aviation,  professional malpractice,  and commercial disputes. Bonnie has tried cases to verdict in such diverse venues as Dallas,  Ft. Lauderdale,  St. Louis,  and Portland,  in addition to the San Francisco Bay Area. She has managed tort litigation on the worldwide,  national,  regional and statewide levels. The defense of those claims has involved the selection and supervision of local counsel,  coordination of discovery and defenses,  and trial in federal and state courts. In addition to her trial practice,  she advises companies on preventive product liability measures and coordinated litigation strategy.<BR><BR><LI><B>Janine S. Simerly</B> (<I>San Francisco; 415-986-4200</I>) has 14 years of experience in product liability and personal injury defense. She has successfully defended aircraft manufacturers,  makers of medical devices,  and designers of heavy industrial equipment,  with defense verdicts in jury trials throughout California.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Sheldon J. Warren</B> (<I>Los Angeles; 213-627-2000</I>) specializes in product liability and personal injury defense. He has successfully tried to verdict cases involving small planes,  bicycles,  materials-handling equipment,  and toxic metals.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Leo J. Murphy,  Jr. </B>(<I>San Francisco; 415-986-4200</I>) specializes in product liability,  insurance coverage,  and commercial litigation. He has handled litigation for manufacturers of a variety of products,  including scaffolds,  personnel lifts,  grape harvesters,  palletizers,  lift gates,  steam valves,  aircraft,  exercise equipment,  and chiropractic instruments.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Thomas T. Carpenter </B>(<I>Los Angeles; 213-627-2000</I>) has a background and degree in engineering. His trial practice primarily focuses on the defense of product manufacturers and designers. He has handled cases involving a variety of products,  including aircraft engines,  barcarts and baggage loaders,  composite materials,  brakes,  ejection seats,  forklifts,  fuel tanks,  fire extinguishers,  chemical retardants,  and helicopters.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>T. Scott Tate</B> (<I>San Francisco; 415-986-4200</I>) has a practice ranging from product liability and construction defect and commercial actions to real estate and lender liability litigation. He has also handled insurance coverage matters and is versed in all aspects of insurance and commercial bad faith litigation.<BR>
<BR>
