<TITLE>Condon  & Forsyth
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>Product Liability</H2>
<H3>Condon  & Forsyth
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>New York:</B> 1251 Avenue of the Americas,  New York,  NY 10020<BR>
Tel 212-757-6870  <B>*</B>  Fax 212-315-1134<BR>
<B>Other offices:</B> Los Angeles,  Washington,  D.C.<BR>
<BR>
41 lawyers  <B>*</B>  20 lawyers concentrate in products liability<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>
<P><BR>

<P>
<P><B>C</B>ondon  & Forsyth has represented foreign and domestic clients in complex tort litigation for over half a century. Our lawyers have extensive trial and appellate experience in state and federal courts and in administrative proceedings before government agencies. Many of our cases have established important precedents in substantive and procedural law.
<P><BR><P>Widely recognized for its defense of international airlines in mass disaster cases,  the Firm also has nine partners who concentrate on the Firm's products liability clients. These clients include not only aircraft,  engine,  and component manufacturers,  but also manufacturers of construction equipment,  industrial machinery,  aerospace technology,  and consumer goods such as sports equipment,  food products,  and chemical and pharmaceutical products.<BR><P>Condon  & Forsyth has a unique sensitivity to the needs and concerns of manufacturers. We advise our clients on long-term risk management and offer orientation programs on the American legal system,  on establishing integrity programs,  and on prospectively limiting liability.<BR>
<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Partners</H3></CENTER>
<BR><BR><UL>
<LI><B>Desmond T. Barry,  Jr.</B> Mr. Barry is co-managing partner of the Firm and specializes in complex multidistrict insurance and products liability litigation. Princeton University,  B.A.,  1967; Fordham University,  J.D.,  1973.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Christopher Carlsen</B> Mr. Carlsen has extensive experience in all aspects of civil litigation,  with emphasis in complex multidistrict insurance and products liability litigation. Former litigation counsel with The Coca-Cola Company responsible for handling the company's nationwide docket of products liability litigation. University of Notre Dame,  B.A.,  1980,  J.D.,  1983.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Stephen R. Ginger</B> Mr. Ginger specializes in space product liability and is an author and lecturer on the subject. Law clerk to Judge Albert Lee Stephens,  Jr.,  U.S. District Court for the Central District of California,  1982-1984. California State University,  B.A.,  1979; Southwestern University,  J.D.,  1982.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Edward G. Petraglia</B> Mr. Petraglia concentrates his practice on aircraft and industrial product liability and commercial litigation,  and has represented several of the Firm's manufacturing clients in litigation throughout the United States. New York University,  B.A.,  1977; Rutgers University,  J.D.,  1980.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Katherine B. Posner</B> Ms. Posner has experience in the handling of pharmaceuticals,  toxic tort,  and aircraft products liability matters. She also is heavily involved in dispute resolution for the Firm's clients. McNeese State University,  B.A.,  1974; University of Wyoming,  J.D.,  1977.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>David A. Senior</B> Mr. Senior has extensive experience in all phases of civil litigation with special emphasis on the preparation and trial of products liability cases. Texas Christian University,  B.S.,  1979; Southwestern University,  J.D.,  1982.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Frank A. Silane</B> Mr. Silane,  senior partner in the Firm's Los Angeles office,  specializes in complex multidistrict tort litigation including products liability claims. He also represents the Firm's clients in aerospace cases. Fordham University,  B.A.,  1967,  J.D.,  1970.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Stephen R. Stegich III</B> Mr. Stegich represents several aircraft manufacturers in products liability litigation. He is a rated commercial pilot with instrument rating and a member of the National Aeronautical Association. He is also a member of Tau Beta Pi Engineering Honor Society and Tau Sigma Delta Architectural Engineering Honor Society. University of Notre Dame,  B.S.,  1965,  J.D.,  1972.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Marshall S. Turner</B> Mr. Turner defends,  throughout the United States,  products liability claims made against domestic and Japanese manufacturers and has extensive trial experience and national product risk management experience as a result. He is a member of the National Transportation Safety Board Bar Association. Queens College,  B.A.,  1968; Fordham University Law School,  J.D.,  1972.<BR>
<BR>

</UL>

