<HEAD>
<TITLE>Crosby,  Heafey,  Roach  & May,  P.C.
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>Product Liability</H2>
<H3>Crosby,  Heafey,  Roach  & May,  P.C.
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>Oakland:</B> 1999 Harrison Street,  Oakland,  CA 94612<BR>
Tel 510-763-2000  <B>*</B>  Fax 510-273-8832  <B>*</B>  E-mail: <A HREF="mailto:lxa@chrm.com">lxa@chrm.com</A><BR>
<B>Los Angeles:</B> 700 South Flower Street,  Suite 2200,  Los Angeles,  CA 90017<BR>
Tel 213-896-8000  <B>*</B>  Fax 213-896-8080  <B>*</B>  E-mail: <A HREF="mailto:lxa@chrm.com">lxa@chrm.com</A><BR>
<BR>
194 lawyers  <B>*</B>  42 lawyers in Product Liability Group  <B>*</B>  64 lawyers in Insurance Group<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>
<P>
<P>
<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Product Liability Group</H3></CENTER>

<P><B>C</B>rosby,  Heafey,  Roach  & May has been in the forefront of product litigation since product liability law was recognized in California more than 30 years ago. Representing prominent manufacturers in the medical equipment,  pharmaceutical,  and automotive industries,  we have helped develop the law of product liability in California and nationally. The firm also represents manufacturers of a broad range of other products,  including airplanes,  boats,  contact lenses,  elevators,  food products,  chemicals,  industrial equipment,  machinery,  and consumer goods. Representative clients include American Suzuki Corporation,  Baxter Healthcare Corporation,  Chevron Corporation,  The Coca-Cola Company,  Minnesota Mining  & Manufacturing Company,  Pfizer Inc.,  Sofamor Danek Group,  Inc.,  Syntex Corporation,  and United States Surgical Corporation.
<P><BR><P>We not only defend product liability lawsuits involving personal injury and property damage but also represent our manufacturing clients in commercial litigation involving warranty and economic loss. We serve as national and regional coordinating counsel for some of our corporate clients,  supervising litigation in federal and state courts. In addition,  we counsel manufacturers with respect to legislation and regulation by federal and state agencies,  and we assist in preparing warnings and instructional literature and recall campaigns.<BR><P>Representative matters include: American Suzuki Motor Corporation trial counsel in California and national counsel coordinating litigation venued outside California; Baxter Healthcare Corporation regional counsel for silicone breast implant litigation and multidistrict litigation liaison counsel in the Gammagard litigation; Minnesota Mining  & Manufacturing Company trial counsel for silicone breast implant litigation in California and other Western states; polyvinyl chloride (PVC) pipe litigation defended multiparty cases involving allegations of failure to warn,  product labeling defects,  and advertising misrepresentations; and DES litigation regional coordinating defense counsel.<BR>
<BR><P>The 17 partners and 25 associates in the Product Liability Group include some of the most experienced trial attorneys in the nation. The practice group is chaired by <B>Stephen G. Blitch</B> (<I>510-466-6703</I>),  who has substantial experience handling cases with significant compensatory damage exposure and punitive damages,  and has litigated more than 100 cases involving severe neurologic injury or death. Other directors in the group: <B>Michael K. Brown</B> (<I>213-896-8018</I>) served as the managing partner of our Los Angeles office for four years. His focus has been on complex pharmaceutical and other product liability issues. <B>Colleen T. Davies </B>(<I>510-466-6738</I>) has substantial litigation and trial experience involving various product liability matters,  focusing on pharmaceutical and medical device litigation. <B>James DeRoche</B> (<I>213-896-8030</I>) served as trial counsel and as national counsel coordinating litigation for a major Japanese automobile manufacturer. <B>Roy Goto</B> (<I>213-896-8031</I>) focuses on complex product liability litigation with a special emphasis in all-terrain vehicle product liability litigation. <B>Joan M. Haratani</B> (<I>510-466-6774</I>) is currently national coordinating trial counsel for an international medical device company,  and is responsible for all phases of that litigation. <B>Richard J. Heafey</B> (<I>510-466-6720</I>) has served as the lead coordinating counsel and trial counsel for major national product suits involving DES,  Oraflex,  oral contraceptives,  and Neo-Mull Soy. He is co-author of <I>Product Liability: Winning Strategies and Tactics</I> (Law Journal Seminars Press,  1994). <B>B. Clyde Hutchinson</B> (<I>510-466-6768</I>) has tried in excess of 100 civil jury trials. He serves as one of the national counsel for an international automobile manufacturer. <B>Howard A. Janssen</B> (<I>510-466-6782</I>),  a former assistant district attorney for the Alameda County District Attorney's Office,  has tried hundreds of cases to juries. He has extensive civil jury and court trial experience involving product liability,  and served as national trial counsel for a major manufacturer of all-terrain vehicles. <B>William P. Kannow</B> (<I>213-896-8032</I>) has substantial trial experience in automotive product liability defense. <B>John M. Kern</B> (<I>510-466-6780</I>) focuses primarily on pharmaceutical and product liability litigation. He is an advocate of the American Board of Trial Advocates. <B>Steven M. Kohn</B> (<I>510-466-6727</I>) has served as lead counsel for a multinational pharmaceutical company in two trials involving the issue of market share in product liability litigation. <B>F. Ronald Laupheimer</B> (<I>510-466-6790</I>) focuses on personal injury and product liability litigation. He is admitted to practice before the U.S. Supreme Court. <B>Mary C. Oppedahl</B> (<I>510-466-6788</I>) has represented a major Japanese automobile manufacturer,  handling cases in California and acting as national coordinating counsel for cases venued in other states. <B>Richard SaLCido</B> (<I>213-896-8016</I>) has focused on product liability defense and environmental and toxic tort law. <B>Philip L. Siracuse</B> (<I>213-896-8052</I>) represents many Japanese companies and has served as lead American counsel for American Suzuki Motor Corporation in litigation in North America and Europe. <B>James M. Wood</B> (<I>510-466-6758</I>) focuses on pharmaceutical and medical device product liability litigation. A large part of his practice has involved the diethylstilbestrol litigation,  which has given rise to a number of landmark decisions involving pharmaceuticals. Scientific consultant Gloria S. Caldwell,  who received her Ph.D. in zoology from the University of California at Berkeley,  has been an indispensable member of the pharmaceutical and medical device litigation team since 1985.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Insurance Practice Group</H3></CENTER>

<P>Crosby,  Heafey,  Roach  & May is actively involved in litigation that defines the boundaries of insurance,  and has been for nearly a century. Representing such insurance companies as Allstate Insurance Company,  Farmers Insurance Group of Companies,  The ITT Hartford Group of Insurance Companies,  Reliance Insurance Company,  Risk Enterprise Management Limited (The Home Insurance Company),  and Transamerica Group of Insurance Companies,  we have helped this area of law evolve. Thus,  we understand where it is heading and how to protect our clients' interests in the face of change.<BR><P>The Insurance Practice Group's services to insurers go well beyond providing advice as to the interpretation and application of policies and defending against bad faith claims. We also provide counseling with respect to the handling of large or particularly sensitive claims and fraud investigations. We represent insurers in actions involving regulatory bodies and governmental entities. Further,  Crosby Heafey's commercial litigators are able to work with the Insurance Practice Group to handle general commercial problems on behalf of insurance companies,  such as contractual disputes and claims of unfair competition. We also represent managing general agents,  brokerage firms,  third-party administrators,  and claims adjusting organizations.<BR>
<BR><P>The Insurance Practice Group handles coverage matters involving both first-party (property,  business interruption,  health,  life,  and disability) and third-party (comprehensive general liability,  environmental,  homeowner,  worker's compensation,  professional liability,  and specialty lines) issues. The Group's attorneys are thoroughly experienced as well with issues unique to excess coverage and reinsurance. Members of the Group lecture frequently to industry trade associations and within the legal community. Several Crosby Heafey attorneys have qualified numerous times as expert witnesses on insurance matters.<BR>
<BR><P>Unlike almost any other firm with a significant insurance practice,  Crosby Heafey's Insurance Practice Group is able to work closely with our 15-member Appellate Practice Group,  which represents not only individual insurers in state and federal appeals throughout the nation,  but also insurance industry groups who ask us to appear on their behalf as <I>amicus curiae</I> in matters critical to the welfare of the industry.<BR>
<BR><P>There are 25 directors and 38 associates in the Insurance Practice Group,  chaired by <B>Jack R. Nelson</B> (<I>510-466-6838</I>). Mr. Nelson has extensive experience in complex civil litigation. His practice focuses on insurance coverage and bad faith defense,  business disputes,  and professional liability matters. Other directors in the group: <B>Terry B. Bates</B> (<I>213-896-8012</I>) focuses on insurance bad faith and professional liability litigation,  and has tried matters in state and federal courts. <B>Hector J. Chinchilla</B> (<I>510-466-6844</I>) has focused on the defense of insurance bad faith,  coverage,  legal malpractice,  and complex and commercial litigation. <B>Bruce E. Copeland</B> (<I>510-466-6820</I>) practices in the areas of insurance coverage and commercial litigation,  with an emphasis on environmental contamination. <B>Steve W. Cusick</B> (<I>510-466-6763</I>) has defended many prominent attorneys and law firms in Northern California against claims for malpractice and in fee dispute litigation. <B>John E. Dittoe</B> (<I>510-466-6712</I>) has handled numerous insurance coverage matters involving environmental claims and personal and commercial lines of insurance. <B>Thomas M. Freeman</B> (<I>510-466-6813</I>) has extensive experience in insurance coverage and bad faith involving environmental,  commercial,  construction,  intellectual property,  advertising injury,  and first-party issues. <B>Michael H. Grubman</B> (<I>510-466-6814</I>) focuses on insurance law,  including coverage and bad faith disputes. <B>Jacqueline M. Jauregui</B> (<I>510-466-6762</I>) has handled a broad spectrum of insurance-related litigation,  including coverage cases,  reinsurance and contribution disputes,  and bad faith. <B>Raoul D. Kennedy</B> (<I>510-466-6726</I>) handles complex civil litigation at both the trial and appellate level. In 1991 he was cited by the <I>National Law Journal</I> as one of the 30 most influential insurance defense lawyers in America. He is a fellow of the American College of Trial Lawyers,  a member of the American Board of Trial Advocates,  and a past president of the California Academy of Appellate Lawyers. <B>Steven M. Kohn</B> (<I>510-466-6727</I>) has successfully defended multimillion-dollar professional malpractice claims against law firms and regularly represents insurers in coverage and bad faith litigation. <B>Anna Segobia Masters</B> (<I>213-896-8051</I>) focuses on the representation of the insurance industry in coverage disputes,  primarily involving liability and property policies. <B>Louise M. McCabe</B> (<I>510-466-6828</I>) practices in the areas of insurance and environmental coverage litigation,  professional malpractice,  and commercial litigation. <B>Stephen A. McFeely</B> (<I>510-466-6733</I>) is the managing partner of the firm. He has litigated hundreds and tried dozens of cases,  including complex cases against insurance industry defendants. <B>Marilyn A. Moberg</B> (<I>213-896-8035</I>) focuses on commercial litigation involving business torts and contract disputes,  such as professional liability and insurance litigation. <B>Kurt C. Peterson</B> (<I>213-896-8041</I>) has litigated numerous cases involving insurance bad faith and coverage,  and legal malpractice. He has represented over 100 law firms,  ranging from sole practitioners to some of the largest and best-known firms in California and other Western states. <B>Linda Margolies Salem</B> (<I>213-896-8005</I>) has substantial experience handling complex commercial,  insurance coverage,  and bad faith litigation. <B>Gregory M. Schopf</B> (<I>510-466-6801</I>) has handled insurance coverage litigation involving federal and state Superfund sites and other environmental contamination. <B>Stephen G. Schrey</B> (<I>510-466-6746</I>) acts as national and regional counsel on various environmental coverage matters for major casualty insurers. <B>Robert S. Schulman</B> (<I>213-896-8047</I>) has handled a wide variety of civil litigation including unfair competition,  libel and slander,  professional errors and omissions,  major insurance coverage and bad faith matters,  and regulatory matters involving the California and New York Departments of Insurance. <B>Boyd C. Sleeth</B> (<I>510-466-6781</I>) routinely handles both first-party and third-party coverage matters in areas such as environmental pollution coverage,  earth movement and fire losses,  wrongful termination,  fraudulent claims,  and bad faith. <B>Marshall C. Wallace</B> (<I>510-466-6808</I>) has substantial experience defending complex commercial cases, including multiparty insurance coverage cases.

</UL></BODY>
