<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Crowell  & Moring
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>Product Liability</H2>
<H3>Crowell  & Moring
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>Washington:</B> 1001 Pennsylvania Avenue,  N.W.,  Washington,  DC 20004<BR>
Tel 202-624-2500  <B>*</B>  Fax 202-628-5116<BR>
<B>Irvine:</B> Suite 1200,  2010 Main Street,  Irvine,  CA 92714<BR>
Tel 714-263-8400  <B>*</B>  Fax 714-263-8414<BR>
<B>London:</B> Denning House,  90 Chancery Lane,  London WC2A 1ED<BR>
Tel 44-71-413-0011  <B>*</B>  Fax 44-71-413-0333<BR>
<BR>
209 lawyers  <B>*</B>  30 lawyers in the Torts and Insurance Practice and Litigation Group<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>
<P><BR>

<P>
<P><B>C</B>rowell  & Moring is a firm of over 200 lawyers dedicated to solving legal problems in an effective and cost-efficient way.
<P><BR><P>The Firm's product liability practice involves litigation,  government relations,  and product liability loss prevention counsel.<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Defense Litigation</H3></CENTER>

<P>Our defense litigation experience includes automotive,  aviation,  pharmaceutical,  electrical,  asbestos,  chemicals,  and agricultural products and toxic substances matters. Our success rate has been sound. Representative clients include DuPont; Cigna; Cooper Tire  & Rubber Company; and United Technologies Corporation.<BR><P>We have pioneered in multistate litigation and authored the principal text in the field. Our goals are to reach a successful result and use effective cost control. Our best results have come about by working with inside counsel and exchanging thoughts and ideas in regard to reaching these goals.<BR>
<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Government Relations</H3></CENTER>

<P>Crowell  & Moring has been involved in virtually every major tort reform issue at the state and federal level. We are counsel to the products liability coalition on federal reform. Working with others,  we have helped to pass product liability reform statutes in a number of states. We helped design the General Aviation Revitalization Act,  which was enacted in 1994. We have helped stop legislation that could have unfairly expanded liability. We have worked with the Executive Branch on civil justice issues. Representative clients include Asarco; CIGNA,  Eli Lilly and Company; The Product Liability Coordinating Committee; and The American Tort Reform Association.<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Loss Prevention Counsel</H3></CENTER>

<P>Our lawyers helped pioneer the field of product liability loss prevention and compliance with CPSC obligations. Working with clients,  we have provided guidance with respect to warnings and design. Thus far,  products we have worked on have not resulted in liability exposure. Representative clients include Eagle-Picher and Harris Corporation.<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Principals in our Team</H3></CENTER>
<BR><UL>
<LI><B>Victor E. Schwartz</B> Victor E. Schwartz heads the product liability practice group. He is co-author of the most widely used torts casebook in the United States Prosser,  Wade and Schwartz,  <I>Cases and Materials on Torts</I> and author of the leading text on comparative negligence.<BR><P>Mr. Schwartz is counsel to the American Tort Reform Association (ATRA). He is on the Advisory Committee to both the American Law Institute's Third Restatement of Torts Product Liability and Apportionment of Liability projects. In 1994,  he was cited by the <I>National Law Journal</I> as one of the 100 most influential lawyers in the United States.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Patrick W. Lee</B> Patrick Lee has over 20 years of practical litigation experience. He is a member of the Managing Counsel Association,  the Litigation Section of the American Bar Association,  the Product Liability Advisory Council,  and the Defense Research Institute. He has co-authored,  with others in the practice group,  <I>Guide to Multistate Litigation</I>,  <I>Product Liability Cases and Trends</I>,  and <I>Product Liability: A Practical Guide</I>.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Fred S. Souk</B> Fred Souk specializes in product liability loss prevention counseling,  litigation,  and federal regulatory work relating to consumer products. He has written and lectured extensively regarding product liability and is a member of the Civil Justice Reform Committee of the District of Columbia. He has helped develop the field of product liability loss prevention and is co-author of <I>Product Liability: A Practical Guide</I>.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Richard McMillan,  Jr.</B> Rick McMillan specializes in complex multistate litigation and has extensive experience bringing about successful results for clients. He chairs the Litigation Management and Economics Committee of the American Bar Association Litigation Section.
</UL>


</UL></BODY>
