<P>
<P><B>W</B>ith historical roots extending back to the 1870s,  the San Antonio firm of Groce,  Locke  & Hebdon,  a Professional Corporation,  currently consists of 38 lawyers,  of whom 20 are shareholders and 18 associates or of counsel. The support staff includes nine legal assistants and a law librarian.
<P>
<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Products Liability Litigation</H3></CENTER>

<P>Groce,  Locke  & Hebdon,  P.C. has a regional civil trial practice covering all of central and south Texas in state and federal courts. In the products liability area,  the firm represents clients who are engaged in product design,  manufacturing,  and marketing. Current clients include manufacturers and retailers in the automotive,  aviation,  construction,  consumer product,  medical devices,  pharmaceuticals,  and chemical and toxic substance areas. Representative clients include Bridgestone Firestone,  Inc.,  Baxter Healthcare,  Helena Chemical Company,  Becton Dickinson  & Company,  The Stanley Works,  Inc.,  Associated Aviation Underwriters,  and United States Aviation Underwriters.<BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>Charles L. Smith</B> Mr. Smith chairs the Litigation Section and has successfully tried numerous product liability cases during his 40-year career as a trial lawyer. Mr. Smith is a past President of the State Bar of Texas and is a Fellow in the American College of Trial Lawyers and in the International Academy of Trial Lawyers.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>James D. Guess</B> Mr. Guess has 27 years of jury trial experience in the products aviation area and has tried many cases in the state and federal courts. Mr. Guess is a past President of the Texas Association of Defense Council,  a Sustaining Member of the Products Liability Advisory Council,  Inc.,  a member of the American Board of Trial Advocates,  and the Texas Representative of the Defense Research Institute.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>John Alex Huddleston</B> Mr. Huddleston has 18 years of experience and is board certified by the Texas State Board of Legal Specialization in civil trial law and personal injury trial law. He has defended a wide variety of serious personal injury,  wrongful death,  and property damage cases involving negligence,  product liability,  premises liability,  and toxic torts. Mr. Huddleston regularly represents motor carriers and other transportation companies as well as construction industry clients.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Mark G. Sessions</B> Mr. Sessions has 14 years' experience as a trial attorney in the areas of product liability,  commercial litigation,  personal injury defense,  and toxic tort litigation. Mr. Sessions is a past chairperson of the American Bar Association/Young Lawyers Division.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Edward F. Valdespino</B> Mr. Valdespino has many years of jury trial experience. He has tried many cases involving product liability,  negligence,  premises liability,  first-party insurance,  aviation,  and medical/psychiatric malpractice.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Lisa A. Vance</B> Ms. Vance has over 14 years of jury trial experience in the medical products area and in medical malpractice cases. Currently responsible for the management of highly complex cases,  Ms. Vance is concerned with the provision of high-quality defense and cost containment. In addition to the medical field,  her caseload involves many different kinds of products,  as well as the construction industry,  toxic torts,  and multiple manufacturing concerns. She is involved in numerous civic and legal organizations and has been recognized for her volunteer efforts to improve indigent representation by the private bar. She is currently involved in the Section of Litigation of the American Bar Association.<BR>
<BR>
