<P>
<P><B>F</B>ounded in 1956,  Howrey  & Simon is the fourth-largest firm in Washington,  D.C.,  with a national and international practice. The firm specializes in litigation and government regulation. Our work is supported by Capital Economics,  Capital Accounting,  Capital Environmental,  and Capital Litigation Support,  affiliates with more than 40 economists,  financial analysts,  environmental specialists,  and litigation support specialists.
<P>
<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Products Liability Practice</H3></CENTER>

<P>Our products liability practice focuses on litigation in federal and state courts and before federal and state administrative agencies. The practice has significant experience in defending product liability claims against pharmaceutical companies including DES,  aspirin Reye Syndrome,  and L-tryptophan claims. We also represent policyholders in claims and litigation concerning insurance coverage for products liability claims,  and we counsel our clients on all aspects of products liability matters.<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Experience and Clients</H3></CENTER>

<P>Howrey  & Simon has represented companies such as Dana Corporation,  Nippon Kayaku Co.,  Ltd.,  Chugai Boyeki Corp.,  Armstrong World Industries Inc.,  and Schering-Plough Corporation in various types of products liability litigation in federal and state courts. The firm has represented companies such as Gerry Baby Products Co. and Fisher-Price,  Inc. before the CPSC and NHTSA. In addition,  Howrey  & Simon has represented a number of large corporations,  including 3M,  Armstrong World Industries Inc.,  SCM Corporation,  Atlanta Gas  & Light Company,  and Gulf States Utilities in litigation concerning insurance coverage for claims of product liability.<BR>
<UL><BR>
