<P>
<P>
<P>
<P><B>L</B>ane Powell Spears Lubersky is a Pacific Northwest-based firm that has provided corporate and insurance defense services since 1887. The firm's 45 lawyers practicing in product liability have broad trial experience. The firm has handled the defense for several class action claims against national companies and has served as lead counsel in a mass tort claim in Washington state. The firm's product liability lawyers have experience in defending automobiles,  chemicals,  medical devices,  pharmaceuticals,  tires,  and many other products. With offices in Alaska and along the West Coast,  the firm is well positioned to handle a number of product liability claims.
<P><BR><P>Clients for the firm in the products liability area include the following companies and their insurers: AIG,  Ashland Chemical,  Bridgestone/Firestone,  Chevron USA,  CNA,  Dow Corning,  Eli Lilly,  Exxon,  Fleetwood Enterprises,  General Motors,  Kmart,  Murray Ohio,  Pace,  Sears Roebuck,  Teledyne,  Unocal,  Upjohn,  and The Hartford.<BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>Bruce C. Hamlin</B> (<I>Portland; 503-778-2158</I>) Mr. Hamlin concentrates his practice in product liability and insurance defense matters. Mr. Hamlin is Oregon counsel for a tire manufacturer and for pharmaceutical companies. He is a member of the Defense Research Institute,  the Oregon Association of Defense Counsel,  and the National Association of Railroad Counsel. He is chair of the firm's tort and insurance group in Portland. University of Oregon,  J.D.,  1979.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Laurence F. Janssen</B> (<I>Los Angeles; 213-680-1010</I>) Mr. Janssen specializes in the defense of toxic tort injury cases involving multiple plaintiffs and multiple defendants,  with extensive trial experience in matters involving chemical and petroleum products. Mr. Janssen is past chair of the Oregon State Bar Toxic Tort Section Executive Committee and is co-chair of the firm's Tort and Insurance Department. University of Oregon,  J.D.,  1967.<BR><BR>
<LI><B>Robert E. Maloney,  Jr.</B> (<I>Portland; 503-778-2105</I>) Mr. Maloney heads the firm's general litigation practice group in Portland and is co-chair of the commercial litigation department for the firm. He is involved extensively in regional and national defense counsel organizations,  and has served as co-chair of national product liability committees of the American Bar Association. Willamette University,  J.D.,  <I>summa cum laude</I>,  1967.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>D. Michael Reilly</B> (<I>Seattle; 206-223-7051</I>) Mr. Reilly primarily limits his practice to the defense of product liability claims. He has a special emphasis on medical and consumer products and has served as lead counsel for a joint product manufacturers' committee in tort claims involving medical products in Washington. He is chairman of the Products Liability Section of the Washington Defense Trial Lawyers. Catholic University of America,  J.D.,  1984.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>James L. Robart</B> (<I>Seattle; 206-223-7031</I>) Mr. Robart's emphasis is on complex litigation. He is co-chair of the firm's general litigation department,  and works extensively in litigation matters regarding product liability for corporations at all steps of the manufacturing and distribution chain. Georgetown University Law Center,  J.D.,  1973.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Lawrence P. Riff</B> (<I>Los Angeles; 213-680-1010</I>) Mr. Riff handles civil litigation,  with emphasis on toxic tort,  railroad,  and commercial matters. He is managing partner of the firm's Los Angeles office. University of Michigan,  B.A.,  with high honors and highest distinction,  history,  1978; University of Oregon,  J.D.,  1982. Admitted in Washington,  Oregon,  and California,  and numerous district courts in those three states.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Warren E. Babb,  Jr.</B> (<I>Seattle; 206-223-7089</I>) Mr. Babb handles negligence litigation,  products liability,  and professional liability matters. As a member of the firm's tort and insurance department,  he is extensively involved with identifying limits of manufacturer,  wholesaler,  and retailer liability. He is a member of the Washington State Defense Trial Lawyers,  the Tort and Insurance Section of the American Bar Association,  and Phi Beta Kappa. Rutgers University Law School,  J.D.,  1983.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Brewster H. Jamieson</B> (<I>Anchorage; 907-277-9511</I>) Mr. Jamieson handles product liability defense of distributors and manufacturers,  as well as insurance litigation,  including coverage issues and maritime personal injury,  cargo,  and transactions. He is a member of the Torts and Insurance Practice Section of the American Bar Association. Willamette University,  J.D.,  <I>magna cum laude</I>,  1984.
