<HEAD>
<TITLE>McCarter  & English
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>Product Liability</H2>
<H3>McCarter  & English
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>Newark:</B> Four Gateway Center,  100 Mulberry Street,  Newark,  NJ 07102<BR>
Tel 201-622-4444  <B>*</B>  Fax 201-624-7070<BR>
<B>Other offices:</B> New York,  Wilmington,  Cherry Hill (New Jersey),  Boca Raton (Florida)<BR>
<BR>
200 lawyers  <B>*</B>  75 lawyers in product liability and insurance coverage<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>
<P><BR>

<P>
<P><B>M</B>cCarter  & English is New Jersey's oldest and largest law firm with 200 attorneys in its five offices. Established in 1845,  the firm engages in general practice representing both large and small companies. Lawyers in the firm practice in the areas of litigation,  tax,  bankruptcy,  environmental,  labor and employment,  corporate,  intellectual property,  trusts and estates,  computer and high technology,  real estate,  and public finance law. Approximately 19 partners and 56 associates devote a substantial portion of their practice to product liability and related matters.
<P><BR><P>McCarter  & English has the largest product liability practice in New Jersey,  and one of the largest product liability practices in the United States. The lawyers in our group have extensive trial experience,  and try to verdict approximately 20-35 cases each year. We also have vast experience in handling product liability appeals,  and our firm has been counsel in over 120 reported decisions. One of our partners is the lead author and several others were contributing authors in a leading treatise on New Jersey product liability law entitled <I>New Jersey Product Liability Law</I>. McCarter  & English serves as regional and national coordinating counsel for a number of Fortune 500 companies. Our experience includes the representation of major pharmaceutical and medical device manufacturers; aircraft manufacturers; nuclear electric utilities; and distributors and manufacturers of asbestos,  silica,  pesticides,  and chemicals as well as industrial machines,  machine parts,  and consumer and automotive products. McCarter  & English also provides its clients with state-of-the-art litigation support including in-place computer hardware and software readily available for litigation and document management. In addition to management on the individual case level,  McCarter  & English has vast experience in providing clients with national organization and counseling in areas of mass product litigation,  document retention,  and regulatory compliance. McCarter  & English also represents a number of major manufacturers and suppliers in claims against their liability insurance carriers for coverage totaling in excess of $5 billion.<BR>
<BR><P><B>Eugene M. Haring</B> is the senior partner of McCarter  & English and has an extensive product liability background. He is a member of the American Law Institute and Product Liability Advisory Council. <B>Thomas F. Daly</B> has tried numerous product liability cases involving a variety of products. He is a fellow of the American College of Trial Lawyers.<BR>
<BR><P>McCarter  & English has been retained by some of America's largest pharmaceutical and medical device manufacturers for representation on a local,  regional,  and national basis. <B>John F. Brenner,  Richard M. Eittreim,  Frederick B. Lehlbach,  Lisa M. Goldman,  John C. Garde,  </B>and<B> Linda A. Willett</B> have broad hands-on litigation,  trial,  and appellate experience and have been involved in the coordination of the industry's defense in almost every state in the country. Representative clients and industry groups have called upon McCarter  & English to represent them in the appeal of many of the country's leading medical products cases in such complex areas as nonidentification and third-generation liability. Our firm currently acts as national coordinating counsel and as trial counsel for large pharmaceutical manufacturers in various cases involving high-profile products,  such as breast implants. Clients faced with extensive nationwide litigation have called upon McCarter  & English to provide them with strategic litigation management and organization in discovery coordination and expert development and selection. In addition to experienced partners and associates,  McCarter  & English has employees who are Ph.D.s in pharmacology and related fields ready to provide immediate technical assistance in most areas of the practice.<BR>
<BR><P>McCarter  & English maintains a comprehensive national and regional toxic tort/mass tort practice which includes the defense of claims by consumers,  employees,  bystanders,  and residents who claim exposure to industrial and chemical products such as asbestos,  silica,  dioxin,  formaldehyde,  and radiation. McCarter  & English has also served as national counsel for one of the largest treaters of fire-retardant treated plywood used in the roofs of thousands of residential dwellings. We also act as national coordinating counsel to one of the largest chemical and petroleum companies for benzene and other chemical exposure litigation,  and to a consortium of nuclear electric utilities for radiation injury claims litigation. Partners <B>Andrew T. Berry,  James F. Hammill,  John E. Flaherty,  Gita F. Rothschild,  Lanny S. Kurzweil,  Michael A. Tanenbaum,  Richard P. O'Leary,  Therese M. Keeley,  Nathan A. Schachtman,  Frederick T. Smith,  </B>and<B> Charles F. Rysavy</B> have extensive experience in the trial and management of multijurisdiction mass tort cases. In the past year,  McCarter  & English attorneys have tried major product liability cases in a number of jurisdictions and have argued significant appeals in state and federal appellate courts involving issues such as federal regulatory preemption,  `junk science, ' punitive damages,  and the use of epidemiological evidence in product liability litigation and the ability of juries to apportion liability between concurrent causes of injury.<BR>
<BR><P><B>John E. Flaherty,  David R. Kott,  </B>and<B> James H. Keale</B> have large practices in defending retailers and manufacturers of consumer and industrial products. They regularly defend and try cases for a number of national retailers,  and also represent manufacturers of industrial equipment,  outdoor power equipment,  childrens' toys,  automotive products and components,  bicycles,  and a wide variety of consumer products. They regularly litigate issues concerning contractual indemnities and related issues,  such as coverage under vendors' endorsements.

</UL></BODY>
</HTML>
