<HEAD>
<TITLE>Morrison,  Mahoney & Miller
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>Product Liability</H2>
<H3>Morrison,  Mahoney & Miller
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>Boston:</B> 250 Summer Street,  Boston,  MA 02210<BR>
Tel 617-439-7500  <B>*</B>  Fax 617-439-7590<BR>
<B>Other offices:</B> Raynham,  Springfield,  Worcester,  and Yarmouth Port (Massachusetts);<BR>
New York; San Francisco; Grand Rapids and Southfield (Michigan);<BR>
Providence; Hartford; London<BR>
<BR>
200 lawyers  <B>*</B>  20 lawyers in Product Liability and Toxic Tort<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>See this firm's profile in the following other directory:<BR>
<UL><BR>
   <LI><A HREF="../95ENVFolder/morrison.html"> Environmental</A>
</UL>

<P>
<P>
<P><B>O</B>ur experience in product liability defense has included a broad range of products,  from consumer products,  electronics and electricals,  and industrial machinery,  to alleged toxic materials and pharmaceuticals,  where we have defended manufacturers,  distributors and retailers,  and repairers and installers. 
<P><BR><BR>
<BR><P>Through our experience in defending and trying product liability cases in state and federal courts throughout New England,  we have gained considerable familiarity with plaintiffs' counsel in the area and their varying abilities and inclinations. In our national coordination work,  such as in the asbestos litigation,  we have become familiar with plaintiff and defense firms across the country.<BR><P>Our experience has also given us a good deal of knowledge about manufacturing systems and processes; the great range of regulations,  such as OSHA and state regulations,  governing safety in a variety of workplaces; and voluntary standards applicable to various types of products. Finally,  we have worked with a number of technical experts engineers,  human factors experts,  and others who provide helpful direction in the development of a defense of a lawsuit,  and sometimes-necessary expert testimony at trial.<BR>
<BR><P>In addition,  members of the firm serve as coordinating counsel for various clients with numbers of similar cases pending in multiple jurisdictions. The practice of the product liability defense group also includes advice in product liability prevention,  including warnings and instructions. Examples include:<BR><UL>
<BR><P><LI> A surface-treatment chemical manufacturer national coordinating counsel for product liability litigation.<BR>
<BR><P><LI> A national warehouse retailer of home improvement products and food and general merchandise prevention advice; product liability coordinating counsel.<BR>
<BR><P><LI> A safety-eyewear manufacturer coordination of products lawsuits; advice on warnings and other written materials; general prevention advice.<BR>
<BR><P><LI> An asbestos cement and insulation manufacturer nationwide coordination of asbestos lawsuits.<BR></UL>
<BR><P>We are accustomed to working closely with our clients in planning litigation strategy that is as cost-effective as possible,  while maximizing the achievement of the client's goals in the particular case.<BR>
<BR><P>Knowledge of a client's personnel,  products,  and processes is a valuable commodity,  and so we maintain the same lawyer or lawyers on all of the client's cases. One partner is responsible for and works on a client's cases,  and directly supervises any other lawyer who may work on the case. Within this framework,  most of our cases are handled by a single attorney,  with necessary supervision,  to avoid duplication of effort and expense.<BR>
<BR><P>Morrison,  Mahoney  & Miller is a defense firm composed of over 200 attorneys licensed to practice in numerous jurisdictions,  including all six New England states. Our Boston office and other offices located in Raynham,  Springfield,  Worcester,  and Yarmouth Port,  Massachusetts; Hartford,  Connecticut; Providence,  Rhode Island; Southfield and Grand Rapids,  Michigan; San Francisco; and New York City permit the firm to handle matters throughout New England. The firm's London office enhances our ability to serve clients with international interests. As a complement to our strong New England presence,  the firm is a member of the American Law Firm Association (ALFA),  a national network of legal counsel,  enabling the firm to obtain counsel for its clients in other parts of the country as the need arises.<BR>
<BR><P>The firm handles a full range of tort litigation,  including architects and engineers and construction cases,  workers' compensation,  subrogation cases,  and insurance policy coverage analysis,  opinions,  and litigation. Our litigation services cover all phases from pre-complaint,  through discovery and trial,  to post-appeal. The firm provides advice and service to a number of businesses,  mostly insurance agencies and companies,  in such areas as mergers and acquisitions,  licensing and regulatory matters,  and pension planning.<BR><BR>
<LI><B>Stephen J. Paris</B> Mr. Paris has worked extensively with many manufacturers and other defense interests and has long advocated and participated in tort and product liability reforms. Sustaining member,  Product Liability Advisory Council; past chair and president,  Defense Research Institute and National Society of Chartered Property  & Casualty Underwriters. University of Massachusetts at Amherst,  A.B.,  1960; Boston College,  J.D.,  1963. Admitted in Massachusetts,  1963.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Joel F. Pierce</B> Mr. Pierce has successfully defended a wide range of product manufacturers and distributors. Appellate results include the unreasonable use defense case,  <I>Allen </I>v.<I> Chance Manufacturing</I>,  398 Mass. 32 (1986). Principal practice areas are product liability and toxic tort defense and prevention. Member of the ABA's Product Liability Committee and the Defense Research Institute. Carleton College,  A.B.,  1968; University of Michigan,  J.D., <I> cum laude</I>,  1975. Admitted in Massachusetts,  1975.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Peter C. Knight</B> Mr. Knight has substantial trial and defense experience in the product liability area,  including medical devices and teratology. Principal practice areas are product liability and medical malpractice. Member of the Federation of Insurance and Corporate Counsel and the Lawyer-Pilots Bar Association. Boston University,  B.A.,  1970; Suffolk University,  J.D.,  1974. Admitted in Massachusetts,  1975.<BR>
<BR>
</UL><BR>


</UL></BODY>
</HTML>
