<HEAD>
<TITLE>Peterson,  Johnson  & Murray,  S.C.
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>Product Liability</H2>
<H3>Peterson,  Johnson  & Murray,  S.C.
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>Milwaukee:</B> 733 North Van Buren Street,  Milwaukee,  WI 53202<BR>
Tel 414-278-8800  <B>*</B>  Fax 414-278-0920<BR>
<B>Madison:</B> 150 East Gilman Street,  Madison,  WI 53703<BR>
Tel 608-256-5220  <B>*</B>  Fax 608-256-5270<BR>
<BR>
20 lawyers  <B>*</B>  18 lawyers in Product Liability,  Tort and Insurance Defense Group<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>
<P>
<P>
<P><B>P</B>eterson,  Johnson  & Murray,  S.C. was founded in 1982 by a group of experienced trial lawyers dedicated to providing competent,  aggressive,  and ethically sound litigation defense to the manufacturing and insurance industries. In surveys of Milwaukee County judges and attorneys the firm is consistently chosen as the finest civil defense law firm in the area. All shareholders in the product liability and insurance defense group have `high' to `preeminent' <I>Martindale-Hubbell </I>ratings,  and the firm as a whole is rated `Av.'
<P><BR><P>The firm's reputation is our clients' most valuable asset when entering the courtroom or sitting down at the negotiation table. Our clients' litigation adversaries are acutely aware of the firm's absolute commitment to try cases that cannot be settled reasonably.<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Product Liability Practice</H3></CENTER>

<P>The firm defends a broad spectrum of manufacturers,  ranging from local concerns to multinational corporations. The products involved in this litigation have been as varied as our clients,  and range from simple personal care products to large-scale industrial machinery. The firm is involved in all phases of toxic tort litigation. We have extensive experience in the defense of cases involving alleged defects in medical and pharmaceutical products. On the national scene our attorneys frequently participate in multidistrict,  complex litigation which crosses jurisdictional lines,  such as aircraft disasters.<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Insurance Defense Practice</H3></CENTER>

<P>The firm has handled thousands of personal injury cases,  representing the largest insurers in the nation. We defend individual and corporate insureds who have coverage under a broad range of insurance contracts,  from simple homeowner's policies to complex commercial general liability policies. The types of cases which arise under these policies and which we defend are virtually limitless,  and include everything from simple slip-and-fall or fire loss cases,  to complex business construction disputes,  to commercial and business litigation,  to pollution cases. The attorneys who work in these areas also have substantial experience with respect to insurance coverage disputes and `bad faith' litigation,  enabling the firm to handle multifaceted cases comprehensively yet economically.<BR><P>The legal and medical communities consistently turn to the firm for professional malpractice defense. The firm also plays a leading role in major legal developments on the appellate level,  and has been chosen by organizations of insurers to submit <I>amicus curiae</I> briefs in significant appellate cases involving issues of general importance to the defense bar.<BR>
<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Clients and Exemplar Products</H3></CENTER>

<P>Agricultural products,  including tractors and farm equipment (Avco,  Case Corporation,  New Idea,  Textron); automotive products,  including gas filters and others (Genuine Parts Company,  C.F. Bender Company); aviation products (British Aerospace,  Cessna,  Hamilton Standard,  Pratt  & Whitney); construction equipment,  including front-end loaders and backhoes (Case Corporation); consumer products,  including food,  bicycles,  laundry products,  and Rely tampons (Procter  & Gamble,  PEL Associates); industrial equipment,  including conveyors,  overhead cranes,  and scrap processing equipment (Logemann Brothers Company); machine tools (Dries  & Krump,  Textron); medical equipment,  including latex gloves,  breast implants,  and other prosthetic devices (Smith  & Nephew,  Dow); outdoor products,  including chainsaws,  golf carts,  outboard motors,  and lawn mowers (Homelite,  E-Z Go,  Outboard Marine); pharmaceutical products,  including Bactrim and L-tryptophan (Boeringer Inglehim,  Dow-Corning,  Hoffman-LaRoche,  Showa Denko); transportation equipment,  including tachographs and winch bars (C.F. Bender Company).<BR>
Virtually all of the firm's attorneys have extensive insurance defense and product liability experience. The following shareholders practice exclusively in those areas:<BR><UL>
<BR><LI><B>Donald R. Peterson</B> 37 years of trial experience,  over 200 cases tried to verdict. Fellow,  American College of Trial Lawyers; member,  American Board of Trial Advocates. University of Wisconsin,  B.B.A.,  1955,  J.D.,  1958.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Terry E. Johnson</B> 20 years of trial experience,  over 100 cases tried to verdict. Member,  American Board of Trial Advocates. University of Wisconsin,  B.A.,  1972,  J.D.,  <I>cum laude</I>,  1975.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>James T. Murray,  Jr.</B> 20 years of trial experience,  over 100 cases tried to verdict. Member,  American Board of Trial Advocates. University of Wisconsin,  B.A.,  1971; Marquette University,  J.D.,  <I>cum laude</I>,  1974.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Mary K. Wolverton</B> 16 years of trial experience,  over 50 cases tried to verdict. Michigan State University,  B.A.,  1971; Marquette University,  J.D.,  1978.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Mary Lee Ratzel</B> 14 years of trial experience,  over 40 cases tried to verdict. Marquette University,  B.A.,  <I>magna cum laude</I>,  1978,  J.D.,  1981.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Randy S. Parlee</B> 12 years of trial experience,  over 50 cases tried to verdict. University of Wisconsin at Milwaukee,  B.A.,  with distinction,  1976,  M.A.,  1981; Marquette University,  J.D.,  1983.<BR>
<BR><LI><B>Timothy J. Pike</B> 9 years of trial experience,  over 20 cases tried to verdict. Oberlin College,  B.A.,  1983; University of Wisconsin,  J.D.,  1986.<BR>
</UL>
</UL></BODY>
