<HEAD>
<TITLE>Ruden,  McClosky,  Smith,  Schuster  & Russell,  P.A.
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>Product Liability</H2>
<H3>Ruden,  McClosky,  Smith,  Schuster  & Russell,  P.A.
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>Miami:</B> 701 Brickell Avenue,  Suite 1900,  Miami,  FL 33131<BR>
Tel 305-789-2700  <B>*</B>  Fax 305-789-2793  <B>*</B>  E-mail: <A HREF="mailto:76077, 521@Compuserve.com">76077, 521@Compuserve.com</A><BR>
<B>Other offices:</B> Ft. Lauderdale,  Naples,  St. Petersburg,  Sarasota, <BR>
Tallahassee,  and Tampa (Florida)<BR>
<BR>
150 lawyers  <B>*</B>  6 lawyers specializing in product liability law<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>
<P>
<P>
<P><B>R</B>uden McClosky has dedicated experience in handling all phases of product liability cases,  so much so that today it represents 25 percent of the firm's litigation practice. The members of this practice group represent a broad spectrum of domestic and international manufacturers ranging from Fortune 100 companies to family-owned businesses.
<P><BR><P>For 20 years,  our attorneys have represented numerous automobile,  agricultural equipment,  and aviation manufacturers in product liability lawsuits in all state and federal courts. Among our clients are Porsche Cars of North America,  John Deere  & Co.,  Fiat,  Volkswagen of America,  Chrysler Corporation,  Emerson Electric,  The Dial Corp.,  Werner Co.,  Raytheon,  Beechcraft,  Cessna Aircraft,  and Teledyne. In addition,  we counsel clients worldwide in the following product areas: pharmaceutical products,  medical devices,  ladders,  consumer and household products,  forklifts,  and LP gas.<BR><P>The firm offers particular experience in complex cases involving issues such as biomechanics,  accident reconstruction,  human factors,  and occupant kinematics. Specifically,  we are experienced in the following areas of liability: product design and manufacturers' defects,  accident reconstruction,  seat belt defense,  crashworthiness of vehicles,  crashworthiness of aircrafts,  forensic pathology,  fires,  metallurgy,  and mechanical engineering.<BR>
<BR><P>Our attorneys are skilled in product liability issues including,  but not limited to,  federal preemption and discovery under The Hague Convention,  punitive damages,  the new federal rule on discovery,  protective orders,  depositions of CEOs,  and admissibility of tests and experiments.<BR>
<BR><P>Attorneys in this practice are active in organizations directly related to product liability issues. Among them are the Product Liability Advisory Council,  the Defense Research Institute,  the Society of Automotive Engineers,  the Association for the Advancement of Automotive Medicine,  the Society of Automotive Engineers of Japan,  the International Association of Defense Counsel,  the American Board of Trial Advocates,  the Torts and Insurance Practice Section of the American Bar Association,  and the Latin-American Aviation and Space Law Association (ALADA).<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>Peter L. Wechsler</B> Mr. Wechsler concentrates his practice in tort,  product liability,  and insurance defense matters. He represents numerous major manufacturers,  with a focus on automotive product liability. He has lectured in the areas of advanced auto torts and has offered testimony before the Florida Senate and House of Representatives on proposed legislation dealing with confidentiality agreements in litigation,  the Sunshine Litigation Act,  and seat belts. He is a member of the Product Liability Advisory Council,  Society of Automotive Engineers and Defense Research Institute. Long Island University,  B.S.,  1965; Suffolk University School of Law,  J.D.,  1969.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Calvin F. David</B> Mr. David concentrates his practice in civil litigation with an emphasis on product liability cases involving aircraft accidents,  medical and drug liability,  torts,  and insurance practice. Mr. David has lectured extensively at programs including those sponsored by the Florida Bar,  the American Bar Association,  Journal of Air Law and Commerce,  American Society of Mechanical Engineers,  Insurance Counsel Trial Academy,  and International Association of Defense Counsel. He has been published on issues including crashworthiness,  maritime and aviation deaths,  defective design,  the Warsaw Convention,  death on the high seas,  and government contractor defense. University of Miami,  B.B.A.,  1965,  J.D.,  1968.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Nancy W. Gregoire</B> Ms. Gregoire began her practice in insurance defense litigation and has gone on to specialize in appellate litigation. A certified appellate practitioner in the State of Florida and a charter member of the Appellate Practice and Advocacy Section of The Florida Bar,  she has been a consistent advocate for appellate issues in the state and county bar. Ms. Gregoire has handled insurance defense matters at the appellate court level including statute of repose,  contribution and indemnity,  and joint and several liability. University of Florida,  B.A.Ed.,  with honors,  1965; Florida Atlantic University,  M.Ed.,  with honors,  1970; University of Miami School of Law,  J.D,  with honors,  1984.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>M. Gary Toole</B> Mr. Toole represents product manufacturers throughout the State of Florida in litigation involving automobiles,  farm equipment,  ladders and step stools,  bicycles,  and propane gas equipment. He is a member of the Society of Automotive Engineers,  the Tort and Product Liability Section of the American Bar Association,  and the Florida Defense Lawyers Association. University of Alabama,  B.S.,  1984,  J.D.,  1987.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Mark J. Dearman</B> Mr. Dearman is an associate in the tort,  product liability and insurance department. He has handled product liability and insurance defense matters involving consumer goods,  automotive parts,  and amusement park rides. University of Florida,  B.A.,  1990; Nova University School of Law,  J.D.,  1993.
</UL>


</UL></BODY>
