<HEAD>
<TITLE>Skadden,  Arps,  Slate,  Meagher  & Flom
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>Product Liability</H2>
<H3>Skadden,  Arps,  Slate,  Meagher  & Flom
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>New York:</B> 919 Third Avenue,  New York,  NY 10022<BR>
Tel 212-735-3000  <B>*</B>  Fax 212-735-2000<BR>
<B>Other offices:</B> Boston,  Chicago,  Houston,  Los Angeles,  Newark,  San Francisco,  Washington,  D.C.,  Wilmington,  Beijing,  Brussels,  Frankfurt,  Hanoi,  Hong Kong, <BR>
London,  Moscow,  Paris,  Prague,  Sydney,  Tokyo,  Toronto<BR>
<BR>
1, 115 lawyers  <B>*</B>  50 lawyers in the Products Liability Department<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>
<P>
<P>
<P><B>S</B>kadden,  Arps is an international firm with over 1, 100 lawyers in more than 40 practice areas. Attorneys in the firm's products liability and toxic torts practice area handle matters nationwide and are based in New York,  New Jersey,  Delaware,  Illinois,  and California. The firm defends class actions and mass tort proceedings as well as individual suits involving personal injury,  property damage,  and economic loss claims,  including trials in MDL,  mass tort,  and complex product liability contexts. These actions typically include complex or novel theories of liability and damages,  often raising questions on the cutting edge of science and law. The firm also handles a broad range of insurance coverage litigation.
<P>
<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Experience and Clients</H3></CENTER>

<P>Skadden,  Arps has a national trial practice and has been national coordinating counsel in litigation involving automotive,  chemical,  food,  medical,  pharmaceutical,  and consumer products. It has represented defendants in actions involving aLCoholic beverages,  asbestos,  breast implants,  DDT,  dioxin,  ethylene oxide,  food poisoning,  motor vehicles,  prescription drugs,  and repetitive stress injury. The firm also has represented clients in an array of insurance coverage disputes as well as reinsurance regarding environmental coverage litigation.<BR><P>The firm's practice frequently involves cases subject to federal and statewide coordination. Skadden,  Arps has represented the largest manufacturer of silicone breast implants as national co-counsel,  MDL litigation liaison co-counsel,  regional counsel in the East Coast,  and local counsel. Skadden attorneys have defended important test cases for particular industries or products. The firm also has an active appellate practice and often briefs important legal issues for <I>amici curiae</I>.<BR>
<BR><P>The firm regularly counsels clients on the adequacy of warning labels,  recalls,  retrofit programs,  indemnity agreements,  warranties,  and insurance coverage.<BR>
<BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>Sheila L. Birnbaum</B> heads the firm's products liability practice area and practices primarily in the areas of products liability,  toxic torts,  and insurance coverage litigation. She has been national counsel for Dow Corning in the breast implant litigation. Ms. Birnbaum was formerly associate dean of New York University's Graduate Division and professor of law at its School of Law. Ms. Birnbaum lectures and publishes extensively on products liability and insurance issues,  and is a columnist for <I>The National Law Journal</I>.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Irene Sullivan</B> works primarily on insurance coverage litigation and advises clients on various insurance-related matters. Ms. Sullivan currently is national coordinating counsel for a major domestic reinsurer in environmental coverage litigation. She frequently lectures at Practising Law Institute and other continuing legal education programs on insurance coverage and pre-trial case preparation.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Barbara Wrubel</B> defends clients in products liability and toxic tort cases,  in addition to coordinating litigation pending in multiple courts around the country. She has been a member of the ABA's Commission on Mass Torts and is former co-chair of the ABA Litigation Section's Committee on Products Liability. In addition to the appellate practice,  Ms. Wrubel recently has directed major complex litigations involving toxic chemicals and building products,  and issues concerning property damages and class action certification. She lectures frequently on products liability and toxic torts and has written extensively in the field.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Edward M. Crane</B>,  resident in the Chicago office,  represents a variety of corporations in products liability,  toxic tort,  and complex litigation nationally. He recently tried a major pharmaceutical class action in an MDL context. He serves as co-lead counsel in a nationwide class action and related opt-out litigation arising from a major milk contamination. He has published a variety of articles on products liability and trial practice and has served as a vice-chair of the Civil Procedure and Evidence Committee of the ABA's Tort and Insurance Practice Section.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Peter J. McKenna</B> represents corporate defendants in personal injury and toxic tort cases on a national basis involving a range of products and devices. Mr. McKenna also defends serious individual claims of personal injury. Mr. McKenna acts as both national coordinating counsel and national trial counsel for a client defending against claims of fraud and conspiracy throughout the country.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Timothy G. Reynolds</B> represents parties in insurance coverage litigation and advises clients on a number of insurance-related issues. Mr. Reynolds acts as national coordinating counsel to an insurer regarding major environmental claims. He has also represented manufacturers in challenging class certification and in litigating class actions involving alleged product defects.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Jeffrey S. Lichtman</B> has represented clients with regard to pharmaceuticals,  medical devices,  chemicals,  heavy metals,  tools,  telephones,  and food products,  as well as automobiles and theatrical products. He has defended the largest manufacturer of silicone breast implants and served as liaison counsel for the New York manufacturers' defense group. Mr. Lichtman is national coordinating counsel for a pharmaceutical company and an international food company.
</UL>


</UL></BODY>
