<HEAD>
<TITLE>Smith Mazure<\n>Director Wilkins Young Yagerman   & Tarallo
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>Product Liability</H2>
<H3>Smith Mazure Director Wilkins Young Yagerman   & Tarallo
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>New York: </B>111 John Street,   New York,   NY 10038<BR>
Tel 212-964-7400  <B>*</B>  Fax 212-374-1935<BR>
<BR>
40 lawyers  <B>*</B>  All lawyers in product liability and insurance defense practice<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>
<P><B>S</B>mith Mazure has been a liability defense firm for insurance companies and self-insurers for over a quarter-century. Today,   Smith Mazure represents its many and varied clients in a full range of defense cases,   from the ordinary automobile accident and premises suit to the most complex construction,   labor law,   and products liability matters. Our defense practice includes demolition and related construction suits; 1-B coverage under workers' compensation policies; suits against landlords,   including assaults,   burglaries,   security breaches,   lead paint liability,   bailments,   rapes,   and standard accident cases; malpractice in related professions; automobile,   car and truck rental and leasing businesses; and defense of product manufacturers,   retailers,   and distributors. In addition to matters of liability,   Smith Mazure also handles coverage issues,   assignments by excess carriers,   and subrogation cases.
<P><BR>The firm has adopted and published a formal cost containment program which removes many ancillary costs from the billing procedure. It has been flexible in adapting to specific billing and reporting requirements and remains open to innovative billing programs tailored to volume litigation.<BR>Smith Mazure has grown considerably during the past few years,   primarily due to our responsiveness to our clients and their needs. Our list of clients includes AIG Risk Management,   Allstate Insurance Co.,   Blackmoor Group,   the City of New York,   CSC Insurance Services,   Claims Service Bureau,   Crawford   & Co.,   Crum   & Forster,   Inc.,   Embassy Suites,   HCM Management Corp.,   Hertz Corporation,   K  &K Insurance Agency,   Knudsen Elevator Corporation,   Long Island Railroad,   Maryland Insurance Group,   Metro North Commuter Railroad,   Metropolitan Transportation Authority,   New York City Housing Authority,   New York State Dormitory Authority,   North American Specialty Insurance Company,   P.M.A. Group,   Reliance Insurance Co.,   Selective Insurance Co.,   Wausau Insurance Co.,   and Zurich American Insurance Co.<BR>
<BR>Smith Mazure has 40 attorneys,   all of whom devote their time to handling various aspects of insurance defense work. The members of the executive committee are: <BR>
<BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>David E. Mazure</B> began his legal career in the ranks of two major insurance carriers,   advancing from property adjuster to evaluator to claims attorney. He founded the firm over 25 years ago with David Smith and gained prominence as president of the Association of Trial Lawyers of the City of New York. He has been involved as litigation attorney in most major catastrophe cases in New York.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Gerald Director</B> is on the boards of governors for both the New York State Trial Lawyers Association and the Association of Trial Lawyers of the City of New York since 1981,   as well as an associate of the American Board of Trial Advocates. Mr. Director is one of the founding members of the firm. He is a lecturer on medical-legal topics to attorney organizations,   the insurance industry,   and law schools. He received his LL.B. and J.D. from Brooklyn Law School,   where he was on the law review.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Stanley Wilkins</B> is an experienced litigator and a founding member of the firm. He is a past president of the Small Claims Association of Arbitrators of the City of New York and a member of the New York State Trial Lawyers Association,   the Association of Trial Lawyers of America,   and the Association of Trial Attorneys. He earned his LL.B. from New York University after graduating <I>cum laude</I> from City College of New York.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Jacob Jay Young</B> joined Smith Mazure in 1985. His experience is varied and ranges across the automobile,   construction,   and products liability fields. Mr. Young lectures frequently on various topics relevant to New York and New Jersey defense practice,   and is a member of local bar and professional associations. He received his bachelor's degree from Rutgers College and his J.D. from New York Law School. Admitted in New York and New Jersey.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Mark Yagerman</B>'s cases are often cited in the <I>New York State Jury Verdict Reporter</I> (<I>Hendricks</I> v. <I>Kempler</I>,   548 NYS 2d 544,   and <I>Brueckner </I>v.<I> Simpson</I>,   New York State Supreme Court,   Orange County,   April 13,   1992,   among others). His extensive experience in personal injury litigation and the insurance industry have qualified him for the highest rating in <I>Martindale-Hubbell</I>. An often-published author on industry-relevant legal issues,   Mark joined Smith Mazure in 1985. He received his law degree from Cardozo School of Law after graduating <I>magna cum laude</I> from Brooklyn College. Admitted in New York and in New York and Connecticut federal courts.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Nicholas Tarallo</B> joined the firm in 1983. His expertise crosses the spectrum of defense work from automobile to labor law to construction. Mr. Tarallo serves as the firm's chief financial officer and personally supervises the client billing process. He graduated <I>magna cum laude</I> from Iona College in 1975 and with honors from St. John's University Law School in 1979.
</UL>


</UL></BODY>
