<CENTER>
<H2>Product Liability</H2>
<H3>Vinson  & Elkins L.L.P.
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>Houston:</B> 2300 First City Tower,  1001 Fannin,  Houston,  TX 77002-6760<BR>
Tel 713-758-2222  <B>*</B>  Fax 713-758-2346<BR>
<B>Washington:</B> The Willard Office Building,  1455 Pennsylvania Avenue,  N.W., <BR>
Washington,  DC 20004-1008<BR>
Tel 202-639-6500  <B>*</B>  Fax 202-639-6604<BR>
<B>Dallas:</B> 3700 Trammell Crow Center,  2001 Ross Avenue,  Dallas,  TX 75201-2975<BR>
Tel 214-220-7700  <B>*</B>  Fax 214-220-7716<BR>
<B>Austin:</B> One American Center,  600 Congress Ave.,  Austin,  TX 78701-3200<BR>
Tel 512-495-8400  <B>*</B>  Fax 512-495-8612<BR>
<B>Other offices:</B> Moscow,  London,  Mexico City,  Singapore<BR>
<BR>
526 lawyers  <B>*</B>  50 lawyers in product liability and insurance defense<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>See this firm's profiles in the following other directories:<BR>
<UL><BR>
   <LI><A HREF="../95ATFolder/vinson.html"> Antitrust</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95CLFolder/vinson.html"> Commercial Litigation</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95ENVFolder/vinson.html"> Environmental</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95IPFolder/vinson.html"> Intellectual Property</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95WCCFolder/vinson.html"> White Collar Crime</A>
</UL>

<P><BR>

<P>
<P><B>V</B>inson  & Elkins L.L.P. is one of the largest general practice law firms in the world,  representing clients in substantially all areas of law. Firmwide,  over 160 attorneys have traditional litigation practices in such areas as admiralty and special risk insurance; antitrust; appeals; banking,  including lender and general liability; bankruptcy; commercial litigation,  including contract,  warranty,  fraud,  and DTPA matters; condemnation; construction; fiduciary responsibility; insurance coverage; intellectual property; natural resources; officer and director liability; oil and gas; personal injury; premises liability; products liability; professional malpractice; securities and other corporate issues; and title- and land-related disputes. More than 40 Vinson  & Elkins attorneys practice in the area of tort and insurance-defense litigation,  including personal injury,  medical malpractice,  and product liability litigation. Our experience includes cases involving medical,  legal,  architectural,  and engineering malpractice; products liability; environmental torts; false arrest and malicious prosecution; industrial and maritime accidents; insurance policy disputes; libel and slander; life insurance claims; motor-vehicle accidents; occupational diseases; premises liability; and worker's compensation claims.
<P><BR><P>Our representation includes insureds and insurers in the U.S. and abroad in cases arising in the medical,  construction,  energy,  transportation,  retail,  manufacturing,  maritime,  and other industries. These cases typically involve complex medical,  mechanical,  engineering,  and economic issues.<BR><P>Representative clients include: BMW; Chicago Bridge and Iron Co.; DuPont; Elf Atochem North America,  Inc.; Firestone; FMC Corporation; Foxboro; Freightliner Corporation; Great Dane Trailers,  Inc.; Marathon Letourneau Co.; Navistar International Transportation Corp.; and Sears,  Roebuck  & Company. Insurance industry clients include Liberty Mutual,  Continental,  CNA,  Crum  & Forester,  Royal,  and Travelers.<BR>
<BR><P>Our experience includes: serving as Texas coordinating counsel on personal injury and products liability cases for a major cigarette manufacturer; serving as regional counsel for several manufacturers and retailers on personal injury and products liability actions,  including those involving nationwide or industrywide exposure; and serving as national counsel for a pharmaceutical retailer on nationwide products liability matters. We successfully defended a major truck manufacturer in the largest personal injury suit ever brought against that company. We defended a major oil company in the liability side of a bifurcated maritime ship casualty and oil spill case stemming from what was then the largest oil spill ever along the Texas Gulf Coast.<BR>
<BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>David H. Brown</B> (<I>Houston</I>) Experience in insurance and liability matters,  including litigation involving coverage and `bad faith' insurance allegations. Law clerk,  Judge James L. Noel,  U.S. District Court for the Southern District of Texas,  1975-1977. Northwestern University,  B.S.,  1972; The University of Texas,  J.D.,  1975; note and comment editor,  <I>Texas Law Review</I>.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Morgan L. Copeland,  Jr.</B> (<I>Houston</I>) Extensive experience in tort litigation,  including products liability,  environmental,  and toxic tort litigation. Fellow,  Texas and Houston Bar Associations; member,  International Association of Defense Counsel,  Defense Research Institute,  and Texas Association of Defense Counsel. Certified by the Texas Board of Legal Specialization in personal injury and civil trial law. The University of Texas,  B.A.,  1978,  J.D.,  1981.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Elena F. DiIorio</B> (<I>Houston</I>) Extensive experience in multiple plaintiffs litigation for toxic tort clients; product liability matters; medical and dental malpractice cases; and hospital liability cases. Lecturer on such topics as extra-contractual liability and effective claims negotiations at professional and trade group meetings. University of Rhode Island,  B.A.,  1979; University of Houston,  J.D.,  1983.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Phillip B. Dye,  Jr.</B> (<I>Houston</I>) Extensive experience in products liability and insurance coverage litigation. Member,  Maritime Law Association,  National Institute for Trial Advocacy,  and Houston Mariners Club. Louisiana State University,  B.S.,  1982,  J.D.,  1986; managing editor,  <I>Louisiana Law Review</I>.<BR>
<BR>
