<P>
<P>
<P><B>V</B>orys,  Sater,  Seymour and Pease offers national and international representation in all areas of law,  including antitrust,  bankruptcy,  commercial,  corporate,  energy,  government contracting,  health care,  insurance,  intellectual property,  international,  labor,  legislation,  litigation,  product liability,  real estate,  and white collar defense.
<P>
<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>The Product Liability Law Practice</H3></CENTER>

<P>Our firm has broad experience in representing national companies in lawsuits involving allegations of design or manufacturing defects in a wide range of products. These have included pharmaceuticals,  road and construction equipment,  automobiles,  motorcycles,  tow motors,  forklifts,  cranes,  aircraft,  presses,  machine tools,  and a variety of consumer products. We have defended cases involving DPT,  DES,  oral contraceptives,  asbestos,  aLCohol,  and tobacco. Examples of our vehicle practice include experience in defending claims based on allegations of defect in transmission,  throttle,  cruise control,  exhaust,  steering,  braking,  and electrical systems. We have experience in defending against claims of fuel tank defects involving post-collision fires,  and other claims related to vehicle crashworthiness. Our firm has been selected as regional or supervising counsel in product liability cases involving all 88 counties in Ohio,  giving us experience with most of the judges and courts throughout the state.<BR><P>Our attorneys are involved in large toxic tort class actions and environmental matters. Our firm currently serves as lead trial counsel in defending three separate class action suits pending in Ohio and Tennessee involving U.S. Department of Energy nuclear facilities,  with the potential class members totaling nearly 100, 000. We have been involved in similar toxic tort class actions involving chemical disposal facilities. These cases involved complex medical and toxicological related issues.<BR>
<BR><P>Representative clients include General Motors Corporation,  Clark Equipment,  Yokohama Tire Corporation,  Kimble Glass Division of Owens-Illinois,  Inc.,  Purex,  Inc.,  Coca-Cola Company,  Ford Motor Company,  American Cyanamid,  Inc.,  Goodyear Tire and Rubber Company,  Inc.,  Honda of America Manufacturing,  Inc.,  Navistar International Transportation Corp.,  and Dresser Industries,  Inc.<BR>
<BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>Edgar A. Strause</B> (<I>Columbus</I>) Senior partner. Primary areas of practice are civil litigation,  products liability law,  commercial litigation,  aviation litigation,  and toxic tort defense in state and federal courts. Member: American College of Trial Lawyers,  International Academy of Trial Lawyers,  International Association of Defense Counsel,  Association of Defense Trial Attorneys,  and Defense Research Institute. Listed in <I>Best Lawyers in America</I>. University of Michigan,  J.D.,  1953. Admitted in Iowa and Ohio.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Mary Ellen Fairfield</B> (<I>Columbus</I>) Automotive product liability design defect litigation involving brakes,  fuel tanks,  and transmissions; and personal injury and employment litigation. Adjunct professor of trial advocacy,  The Ohio State University College of Law. Fellow,  American College of Trial Lawyers; member,  Defense Research Institute. The Ohio State University College of Law,  J.D.,  1972; <I>Ohio State Law Journal</I>. Admitted in Ohio.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>C. William O'Neill</B> (<I>Columbus</I>) Automotive product liability design defect litigation including brakes,  steering systems,  suspension,  cruise control,  electrical systems,  crashworthiness design,  exhaust systems,  and passenger restraints; and drug litigation. Member: Defense Research Institute. University of Michigan,  J.D.,  1971; <I>Michigan Law Review</I>. Admitted in Ohio.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Alan T. Radnor</B> (<I>Columbus</I>) Personal injury,  product liability,  medical malpractice,  and asbestos litigation. Member: International Association of Defense Counsel,  Defense Research Institute; Association of Insurance Attorneys. Listed in <I>Best Lawyers in America</I>. The Ohio State University,  M.S.,  1969,  J.D.,  1972;  <I>Ohio State Law Journal</I>. Admitted in Ohio.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Bruce L. Ingram</B> (<I>Columbus</I>) Personal injury and product liability litigation involving motor vehicles,  agricultural machinery,  and mining equipment. University of Michigan,  J.D.,  1978. Admitted in Ohio.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Gerald P. Ferguson</B> (<I>Columbus</I>) Primary areas of practice in product liability litigation involve electrical,  industrial,  and construction equipment; motor vehicles; farm equipment; and consumer appliances. Member: Product Liability Committee,  Litigation Section,  ABA. Capital University,  J.D.,  1979. Admitted in Ohio.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Stephen J. Petras,  Jr.</B> (<I>Cleveland</I>) Design safety and international product liability law and litigation involving tooling,  aviation,  automotive,  industrial,  and construction machinery,  and a variety of technical products. Case Western Reserve University,  J.D.,  1979. Admitted in Ohio.<BR>
