<P>
<P><B>W</B>illiams  & Montgomery limits its practice to tort and commercial litigation,  concentrating on cases involving death,  paralysis,  amputation,  burns,  brain damage,  and large property losses. It provides defense work to insurance companies and self-insured corporations nationwide.
<P>
<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Products Liability Practice</H3></CENTER>

<P>The firm's product liability work is led by six partners,  in association with 30 other firm members who have extensive product liability experience.<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Experience and Clients</H3></CENTER>

<P>Examples of products with which we have experience are airplanes,  alarms,  appliances,  balers,  bicycle carts,  blood,  boats,  bottles,  breast implants,  chemicals,  construction equipment,  conveyors,  drugs,  electrical equipment,  elevators,  escalators,  farm implements,  firearms,  flammable clothing,  food,  football helmets,  forklifts,  furnaces,  gas tanks,  hand tools,  incubators,  ladders,  lawn mowers,  medical devices,  motorcycles,  natural gas,  paint and varnish,  punch presses,  race track railings,  ropes,  safety glasses,  seat belts,  slicing machines,  swimming pools,  tires,  toboggans,  trampolines,  truck trailers,  and whirlpools.<BR><P>Product liability corporate clients include Amoco Corp.,  Archer-Daniels-Midland,  Black  & Decker,  Brown  & Root,  Chemlawn,  Deere  & Co.,  Enron,  Ericsson Radio,  Fisher-Price,  Gehl Company,  General Electric,  Goodyear Tire  & Rubber Co.,  Honda,  Katy Industries,  Kimberly-Clark Corp.,  Lennox Industries,  Muskin,  Inc.,  Osram Sylvania,  Sears,  Roebuck,  Snap-On Tools,  Square D Company,  Sunbeam Corp.,  Timet,  Inc.,  and Zenith Electronics.<BR>
