<TITLE>Winston  & Strawn
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>Product Liability</H2>
<H3>Winston  & Strawn
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>Chicago:</B> 35 West Wacker Drive,  Chicago,  IL 60601<BR>
Tel 312-558-5600  <B>*</B>  Fax 312-558-5700  <B>*</B>  E-mail: <A HREF="mailto:info@winston.com">info@winston.com</A><BR>
<B>Other offices:</B> New York,  Washington,  D.C.,  Geneva,  Paris,  Riyadh<BR>
<BR>
450 lawyers  <B>*</B>  12 lawyers in product liability law<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>See this firm's profiles in the following other directories:<BR>
<UL><BR>
   <LI><A HREF="../95CLFolder/winston.html"> Commercial Litigation</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95CSFFolder/winston.html"> Corporate Securities</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95LABFolder/winston.html"> Labor</A>
</UL>

<P><BR>

<P>
<P><B>W</B>inston  & Strawn,  founded in 1853,  is one of the nation's oldest and largest law firms.
<P><BR><P>The firm's practice encompasses virtually every major legal discipline and includes assistance to a wide range of clients throughout the United States and abroad,  including Fortune 500 companies and major commercial and financial institutions,  as well as small and midsize companies,  individuals,  and entrepreneurs.<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>The Product Liability Practice Group</H3></CENTER>

<P>The W &S Product Liability Practice Group has decades of combined trial and appellate experience in product liability cases. Our partners regularly teach trial advocacy courses for law schools,  law firms,  bar associations,  and the National Institute of Trial Advocacy. Our younger lawyers are trained at in-house trial advocacy programs. We invest in training our lawyers to ensure the continued excellent service our clients have come to expect.<BR>

<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Experience And Clients</H3></CENTER>

<P>Our product liability trial lawyers have helped many prominent,  international corporations with complex and serious product liability exposure.<BR><P>We represent our clients both as local and national trial counsel. We have defended a broad range of products,  including tobacco products,  AIDS diagnostic products,  pharmaceutical drugs and medical devices,  material-handling equipment,  automobiles,  construction equipment,  consumer products,  packaging equipment,  asbestos products,  and weight-loss programs. We recognize that product liability cases today typically involve substantial,  often multimillion-dollar exposure for clients. We have been successful in obtaining defense verdicts in product liability jury trials involving death and serious injury.<BR>
<BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>Kimball R. Anderson</B> Mr. Anderson has handled all types of product liability matters,  trying cases in the state and federal courts,  and arguing before the U.S. Supreme Court. He acts as national and local product liability trial counsel for several Fortune 100 companies. Mr. Anderson is a member of Winston  & Strawn's Executive Committee. He regularly teaches and writes on the areas of trial advocacy and product liability law. Mr. Anderson has been involved in alternative dispute resolution as an advocate and a mediator,  and has been appointed a `distinguished neutral' by the Center for Public Resources.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Anthony J. D'Auria</B> A former assistant U.S. attorney,  Mr. D'Auria is a litigation partner in the firm's New York office. In product liability,  he has supervised the defense of hundreds of asbestos cases,  and numerous industrial equipment cases.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Alexis MacDowall</B> Ms. MacDowall has substantial experience with product cases involving diagnostic products,  medical devices,  computer keyboards,  and weight-loss products. Ms. MacDowall has worked on national counsel engagements and has handled major jury trials with senior partners.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Samuel Mendenhall</B> Concentrating in tort defense litigation,  Mr. Mendenhall has been involved with numerous product liability cases for large equipment manufacturers,  as well as hazardous waste litigation for Fortune 100 companies.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Gay R. Schreiber</B> Among other clients,  Ms. Schreiber represents computer equipment and automotive equipment manufacturers. She brings extensive knowledge of product liability law to complex national engagements.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Stephen C. Schulte</B> Mr. Schulte has represented such companies as Black  & Decker,  Whiting Corporation,  and Ford Motor Company in product liability and related construction injury cases. Prior to joining Winston  & Strawn in 1983,  he concentrated his practice in the representation of injured plaintiffs.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Daniel C. Murdock</B> Mr. Murdock heads the firm's New York Litigation department and has represented major corporations in tort and contract litigation across the country. He also has served as settlement master for all asbestos personal injury litigation in the U.S. District Courts for the Southern and Eastern Districts of New York,  and has arbitrated matters under the AAA and NASD.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Dan K. Webb</B> Mr. Webb is the chairman of Winston  & Strawn's litigation department and a member of the firm's Executive Committee. His trial experience includes the defense of a 150-claim class action and 20 related lawsuits arising out of an outbreak of hepatitis associated with one of a major chain's grocery stores. He is also national trial counsel in connection with a tobacco manufacturer's product liability litigation.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
