<TITLE>Bondurant,  Mixson & Elmore
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>White Collar Crime</H2>
<H3>Bondurant,  Mixson & Elmore
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>Atlanta:</B> 1201 West Peachtree Street,  N.W.,  3900 One Atlantic Center,  Atlanta,  GA 30309<BR>
Tel 404-881-4100  <B>*</B>  Fax 404-881-4111<BR>
<BR>
21 lawyers  <B>*</B>  5 lawyers in white collar crime and corporate compliance practice<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>See this firm's profiles in the following other directories:<BR>
<UL><BR>
   <LI><A HREF="../95ATFolder/bondurant.html"> Antitrust</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95CLFolder/bondurant.html"> Commercial Litigation</A>
   <LI><A HREF="../95ENVFolder/bondurant.html"> Environmental</A>
</UL>

<P>
<P>
<P><B>B</B>ondurant,  Mixson  & Elmore concentrates in litigation,  with a strong emphasis on the handling of complex commercial disputes. The firm regularly handles antitrust,  fraud,  RICO,  and securities law cases that pose the threat of both civil and criminal litigation. This familiarity with both the civil and criminal aspects of complex commercial litigation enables the firm to work with its clients to anticipate and minimize all aspects of potential liability.
<P>
<CENTER><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>White Collar Crime and Corporate Compliance Practice</H3></CENTER>

<P>BME represents business entities and individuals before grand juries and state and federal trial and appellate courts. The firm also has extensive experience with administrative investigations,  debarment proceedings,  internal corporate investigations,  antitrust compliance programs,  and antitrust audits. In many instances the firm has simultaneously handled both criminal and civil matters on behalf of the same client before multiple tribunals.<BR><P>The firm's attorneys combine excellent academic credentials with practical experience. For example,  every BME attorney has served as a law review editor or federal law clerk,  or both. Every BME attorney has concentrated in litigation from the inception of his or her career and understands the need to achieve the client's specific objectives in the most efficient manner possible.<BR>
<BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>Emmet J. Bondurant II</B> Mr. Bondurant is a member of the American Law Institute,  the American College of Trial Lawyers,  American Academy of Appellate Lawyers,  and a fellow of the American Bar Foundation. In 1992 Mr. Bondurant was named trial lawyer of the year by the Georgia Chapter of the American Board of Trial Advocates. He has extensive experience in both civil and criminal defense litigation in the antitrust and unfair competition field. In addition,  he has represented defendants in white collar criminal prosecutions involving allegations of mail fraud,  perjury,  antitrust,  bribery,  and public corruption,  among others. Law clerk to Judge Clement F. Haynesworth,  Jr.,  U.S. Court of Appeals for the Fourth Circuit. University of Georgia,  B.A.,  <I>cum laude</I>,  1958; Phi Beta Kappa; J.D.,  <I>magna cum laude</I>,  1960; assistant editor in chief,  law review; Harvard University,  LL.M.,  1962.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Edward B. Krugman</B> Mr. Krugman has represented clients in grand jury investigations and white collar prosecutions involving allegations of mail fraud,  bribery,  antitrust violations,  and public corruption. Law clerk to Judge H. Emory Widener,  U.S. Court of Appeals for the Fourth Circuit. Northwestern University,  B.A.,  1975; University of Georgia School of Law,  J.D.,  <I>summa cum laude</I>,  1979; articles editor,  law review.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Jane E. Fahey</B> Ms. Fahey is a member of the American Law Institute. She has represented clients in grand jury investigations and criminal proceedings in the antitrust field. She also has experience in conducting antitrust audits and structuring antitrust compliance programs designed to reduce antitrust exposure. Law clerk to Associate Justice Sandra Day O'Connor,  U.S. Supreme Court; law clerk to Judge James C. Hill,  U.S. Court of Appeals for the Eleventh Circuit. Rhodes College,  B.A.,  with distinction,  1976; Phi Beta Kappa; College of William and Mary,  J.D.,  1981; editor in chief,  law review.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Michael A. Sullivan</B> Mr. Sullivan has served as associate independent counsel in an investigation of the U.S. Department of Housing and Urban Development. He has represented clients in grand jury investigations and white collar criminal prosecutions involving allegations of mail fraud,  antitrust violations,  perjury,  obstruction of justice,  and public corruption. He also has experience in federal debarment proceedings. Mr. Sullivan was selected to write the <I>Georgia Jurisprudence</I> criminal law sections on perjury and other offenses relating to obstruction of judicial proceedings,  to be published by Lawyers Co-Operative Publishing Company. Law clerk to Judge Marvin H. Shoob,  U.S. District Court for the Northern District of Georgia. University of North Carolina,  A.B.,  1977; Vanderbilt University,  J.D.,  1984; senior articles editor,  law review.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>P. Richard Game</B> Mr. Game has represented clients in grand jury investigations,  criminal actions,  and related civil and debarment proceedings concerning alleged violations of federal and state antitrust laws. He also has experience in conducting antitrust audits and in constructing corporate antitrust compliance programs. Law clerk to Chief Judge William C. O'Kelley,  U.S. District Court for the Northern District of Georgia. Vanderbilt University,  B.A.,  <I>cum laude</I>,  1983; University of Florida College of Law,  J.D.,  with honors,  1986; articles editor,  law review.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>J. Scott McClain</B> Mr. McClain has represented clients in grand jury investigations and criminal proceedings in the antitrust and general criminal defense fields,  as well as preparing internal antitrust compliance programs and policies. Law clerk to Judge William L. Garwood,  U.S. Court of Appeals for the Fifth Circuit. Trinity University,  B.A.,  <I>summa cum laude</I>,  1985; Phi Beta Kappa; University of Texas School of Law,  J.D.,  with high honors,  1989; articles editor,  law review.<BR>
