<HEAD>
<TITLE>Greensfelder,  Hemker & Gale,  P.C.
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><UL>

<CENTER>
<H2>White Collar Crime</H2>
<H3>Greensfelder,  Hemker & Gale,  P.C.
</H3>

</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<B>St. Louis:</B> 1800 Equitable Building,  10 South Broadway,  St. Louis,  MO 63102<BR>
Tel 314-241-9090  <B>*</B>  Fax 314-241-4245<BR>
<B>Belleville:</B> 4715 West Main Street,  Belleville,  IL 62223-5209<BR>
Tel 618-257-7308  <B>*</B>  Fax 618-257-7353<BR>
<BR>
89 lawyers  <B>*</B>  10 lawyers in white collar criminal defense and<BR>
civil and criminal government compliance<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>
<P>
<P>
<P><B>G</B>reensfelder,  Hemker  & Gale,  P.C. proudly celebrated its one-hundredth year anniversary in 1995.
<P><BR><P>The Firm has expanded steadily to become and remain one of St. Louis' largest law firms. The Firm is dedicated to providing its clients with legal services of the highest quality in a timely and cost-effective manner.<BR><P>Included among Greensfelder's 13 specialized practice departments is litigation,  which is itself comprised of 20 attorneys. Litigation in turn encompasses the specialties of white collar crime and civil and criminal government compliance.<BR>
<BR><P>We provide white collar criminal defense services nationwide and have represented clients in investigations in criminal and quasicriminal proceedings in New Jersey,  Washington,  D.C.,  Tennessee,  Chicago,  Portland,  San Francisco,  Arkansas,  Indiana,  Texas,  and the local federal districts of the Eastern District of Missouri and Southern and Central Districts of Illinois.<BR>
<BR><P>Our white collar practice has included the substantive areas of antitrust,  environmental,  real estate fraud,  food and drug,  health care fraud,  RICO,  securities fraud,  insider trading,  civil and criminal forfeiture,  labor racketeering,  immigration,  bank fraud,  public corruption,  customs,  government contracts,  and a multitude of miscellaneous fraud investigations. We specialize in the defense of investigations conducted by federal agencies,  including,  for example,  local U.S. Attorney's Offices,  Department of Justice,  SEC,  RTC,  FDA,  EPA,  Federal Reserve Banks,  and IRS. We have represented individuals as well as large corporations and have advised witnesses subpoenaed before federal grand juries,  as well as tried cases to verdict before U.S. district courts in both Missouri and Illinois.<BR>
<BR><P>The Firm's white collar criminal defense section began when J. Roger Edgar joined Greensfelder in 1980. The area was bolstered by the addition of Jeffrey T. Demerath in 1984 and most recently with Jane E. Dueker's employment in 1995.<BR>
<BR><P>Following are the resumes of the members of the white collar crime practice group at the Firm:<BR>
<BR>
<UL><BR>
<LI><B>J. Roger Edgar</B> Mr. Edgar has been a member of the Firm since 1980. He specializes in federal white collar criminal defense and governmental compliance. Mr. Edgar was employed by the Department of Justice in St. Louis as an assistant U.S. attorney in the Criminal Division of that office (1967-1970) and by the Department of Justice,  Civil Division,  Washington,  D.C. (1974-1980). From 1974 to 1975,  Mr. Edgar worked at the Office of Counsel of the White House under President Ford. He is a member of the Bar Association of Metropolitan St. Louis and the American Bar Association (Litigation Section). St. Louis University,  B.S.,  1960; St. Louis University Law School,  LL.B.,  <I>cum laude</I>,  1963; Yale University,  LL.M.,  1964; Sterling Graduate Fellowship. Admitted in Missouri.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Jeffrey T. Demerath</B> Mr. Demerath focuses on the defense of both corporations and individuals in federal white collar criminal cases as well as a variety of state and federal governmental compliance matters. Before entering private practice,  Mr. Demerath served as legal assistant to Senator Stuart Symington of Missouri from 1973 to 1974 and as an assistant U.S. attorney for the District of Columbia from 1974 to 1980,  the last three years in that office's Fraud Section. Mr. Demerath is a member of the American Bar Association (Criminal,  Litigation and Antitrust Sections),  the Bar Association of Metropolitan St. Louis,  and the National Association of Criminal Defense Lawyers. Dartmouth College,  B.A.,  1970;  Boston University School of Law,  J.D.,  1973. Admitted in Missouri,  the District of Columbia,  and Massachusetts.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><B>Jane E. Dueker</B> Ms. Dueker specializes in state and federal white collar criminal and governmental compliance matters. In 1991-1992,  Ms. Dueker worked in the U.S. Public Defender's office for the Eighth Circuit as a law clerk. From 1992 until joining Greensfelder in 1995,  she served as an assistant attorney general for the State of Missouri in the Litigation and Governmental Affairs Divisions. She is a member of the American Bar Association and the Bar Association of Metropolitan St. Louis. University of Missouri,  B.A.,  1987; St. Louis University,  J.D.,  1992. Admitted in Missouri.<BR>
<BR></UL>
<BR><P>All of the above attorneys practice in the Firm's St. Louis office.<BR>
<BR><P>While Messrs. Edgar and Demerath and Ms. Dueker practice in both the white collar criminal defense and civil and criminal government compliance areas,  an additional seven attorneys at Greensfelder work on civil government compliance issues involving a variety of state and federal agencies.<BR>
<BR><P>Requests for further information are welcome and should be addressed to Jeff Demerath at the above address and/or telephone number.<BR>



</UL></BODY>
</HTML>
